Location_Description: Willowdale Road to Foote Brothers Dam
Habitat_Comment: Shallow water.  Wide gravel/rock channel.  Mature overstory.  Some silt in pockets bby bank.  Deepest spot was the plunge pool in front of the breeched concrete dam.  Saw one dead brown trout (12") near shore.  Lots of emergent vegetation near dam pools directly behind Foote Bros.

Location_Description: Started 238 meters downstream of Mill Road
Habitat_Comment: Riffles and shallow pools.  One big bend in sample reach.  All gravel/rocky bottom.  Silver maple-dominated forest.

Location_Description: Downstrem of Middlesex Turnpike
Habitat_Comment: Ten to fifteen feet wide, two to four feet deep. Muddy, lots of overhang

Location_Description: Downstream of Ballardvale Dam
Habitat_Comment: Stretch had slight bend. Cobble, boulder, some vegetation. Tree lined
Riffle reach downstream of bridge to dam. Rocky Stretch

Location_Description: Upstream of Washington St.
Habitat_Comment: Very sandy stretch, not much wood or other substrate in stream

Location_Description: Lockwood Lane
Habitat_Comment: Low water, some riffle, little woody debris

Location_Description: Big Alum
Habitat_Comment: Very narrow littoral zone.  Many fish out of reach on dropoff. A lot of boat traffic. Rocky, steep shoreline

Location_Description: Big Alum
Habitat_Comment: One gill net ruined by a boat encounter

Location_Description: Plympton Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Water very dark, poor visibility

Location_Description: Upstream of Hill Rd. bridge
Habitat_Comment: Water very dark, poor visibility

Location_Description: Cooper Property
Habitat_Comment: poor visibility

Location_Description: Upstream of Dennison Rd. ext. bridge
Habitat_Comment: heavy siltation

Location_Description: Field across from Spooky World
Habitat_Comment: muddy bottom, dense stands of Elodea and Potamogeton

Location_Description: Mouth of Fuller Brook to Shawinigan Dr.
Habitat_Comment: Sampled sandy stretch at mouth between 2 beaver dams ~40m, then the rest of the reach was cobble, boulder & gravel. Many small pool/riffle reaches, few runs, good wooded canopy except under powerlines.

Location_Description: North of Station Street
Off W .River Street
Habitat_Comment: All wild  EBT , BT stocked

Location_Description: North of Route 140
Habitat_Comment: Good efficiency, pools shallow, all EBT wild, wood turtle

Location_Description: South of Shady Lane
Habitat_Comment: Very tannic; 5 fish observed - all EBT

Location_Description: East side , Bridge Street
Habitat_Comment: Very tannic, All EBT wild

Location_Description: South of Harris Street
Habitat_Comment: High deep pools, fair efficiency, BT stocked; poor fish population for habitat quality

Location_Description: South of Route 68
Habitat_Comment: Old beaver dam upstream of station; stream exposed; water extremely tannic, EBT wild

Location_Description: South of Butterworth Road
Habitat_Comment: Good efficiency, all EBT wild; Slimy  Sculpin still here

Location_Description: South of Ward Road extension
Habitat_Comment: 90% of trout below spring @ approx. 75 meters, EBT wild, BT stocked, good efficiency

Location_Description: South of Wheeler Avenue
Habitat_Comment: Fair efficiency, BT stocked, all EBT wild

Location_Description: East of Tully Road
Habitat_Comment: Beaver- low head dams, fair efficiency, EBT all wild

Location_Description: West of Canal Street
Habitat_Comment: Urban - industry on both sided obvious street runoff problems, trash; water quality apparently o.k.

Location_Description: South of Webber Rd. @ Sturbridge-Warren Line
Habitat_Comment: No comments entered

Location_Description: Upstream of Old Stafford Road
Habitat_Comment: Beavers upstream; locals report no flow n 1999; very tannic

Location_Description: Mashapaug Road
Habitat_Comment: High water; poor efficiency, rookie crew in training; sample influenced by Hamilton Reservoir just downstream and beaver flowage upstream; one BT probably wild, remainder stocked, 6-10 BT missed

Location_Description: Off Maybrook Road
Habitat_Comment: Many crayfish, beavers upstream, BT stocked

Location_Description: South of Holland Road
Habitat_Comment: Moderately high water, good efficiency, all EBT apparently wild. Beavers downstream preclude further sampling

Location_Description: East of Upton Road
Habitat_Comment: All EBT wild; thick cover, fair efficiency sample area limited by heavy cover

Location_Description: Downstream of Green Street
Habitat_Comment: Crew from DEP & OAR

Location_Description: Airport Access
Habitat_Comment: Dark water with only visible fish rising to w/in 2" of surface

Location_Description: Gravel  Access Ramp - off West St.
Habitat_Comment: Seine netting done near ramp  yielded no fish; Gillnets set at 6:20pm

Location_Description: 2nd Bridge before WMA;  shocked upstream at bridge pool
Habitat_Comment: No comments available

Location_Description: Under electric high voltage electric lines
Habitat_Comment: High water; low efficiency with one pass only

Location_Description: Off Maxwell Road
Habitat_Comment: Nothing but salmon and brook trout

Location_Description: Dirt road off of W.Meadow Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Fast moving - gravel and rubble bottom

Location_Description: 50' ft. above & below bridge crossing off Greenville Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Good flow- recent rains; rocks & rubble slippery at Willard Brook State Park

Location_Description: 300' Downstream of bridge crossing-below State Park
Habitat_Comment: Deep water-sample reflects upstream beaver dam activity

Location_Description: 300' downstream of bridge on Locke Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Rubble and rubble/sand; moderate flow

Location_Description: 300' downstream of brook crossing on West Rd.
Habitat_Comment: No comments available

Location_Description: 300'above brook crossing on Mason
Habitat_Comment: No comments available; Crew was sleeping

Location_Description: Sample started upstream 350' from brook crossing on Turnpike Rd.
Habitat_Comment: No comments available

Location_Description: Behind Norwood Garden Apts off Plymouth Drive off Summer St. in Norwood; 40' from paved parking lot
Habitat_Comment: Deep pools 2-3' deep, spring-fed brook, well-shaded, excellent trout water, frogs and crayfish common, still a nursery for wild trout and large trout too.

Location_Description: Off Liberty Sq. Rd. downstream of bridge - Boxboro
Habitat_Comment: Stocked trout were upstream of road; Lots of crayfish

Location_Description: Rt. 62   ( Upstream 220')
Gravel road; 3/10 mile from water plant off Winter St.
Habitat_Comment: Sampled target species - trout, lmb, ae & b for mercury sampling at Lawrence Lab - Town of Burlington stocks 1000-1500 10-12" trout annually, town sticker required but not enforced apparently

Location_Description: Gravely Book Rd.
Harrington Pool to Dam
Habitat_Comment: Very vegetated

Location_Description: Downstream of Palmer Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Recent beaver dam breach upstream; attempted to work upstream to Palmer Rd. but battery died

Location_Description: Davis mine road upstream
Habitat_Comment: Began at Davis Mine Rd. and shocked upstream 800-1000'; stopped due to beaver obstruction. Low gradient stream. Boulder 15%, gravel/cobble 60%, sand/fines 25%. Lots of vegetation, small woody debris. Mature canopy.

Location_Description: From Hazelton Road upstream ~200'
Habitat_Comment: Shocked upstream to diversion; stream channel breaks off due to high flow, flagged. Moderate gradient; mature forest canopy. Much LND. Boulder 20%, gravel 30%. Pebble/sand/fines 50%. Small plunge pools and root wad pools. Ave stream width 6'.

Location_Description: Upstream of Zoar Road
Habitat_Comment: Shocked from Rowe Rd. to log Dam barrier at lodge. Nice brook, must dry up some. Culvert downstream from road is barrier. Boulder 20%, Cobble 30%; Gravel 20%, sand/fines 30%. Stream width 20', depth 2'.

Location_Description: Along Todd Mtn. Road
Habitat_Comment: A few days after heavy rains; high gradient, many pools and cascades. Probable barrier at mouth of stream preventing access from Deerfield. Good habitat w/ many natural barriers. Mature vegetation but close to road.

Location_Description: Below and above Culvert-River Road
Habitat_Comment: Sampled small section of river up to culvert then did ~200' stretch above culvert. YOY's were probably all EBT except those marked as BT.

Location_Description: Both up and downstream of River Rd. culvert crossing
Habitat_Comment: Couldn't shock through culvert; decent brook cobble (40%); Gravel (40%); Sand (20%). Small trees and shrubs along banks. Vehicle crossing thru property across brook. Stream width 15', shallow 2' depth. Median flows.

Location_Description: Riddell Road access-pull over on grass
Habitat_Comment: Rice Brook in Charlemont center; rip rap and chute-like; some structure w/ step pools. Access from Riddell Rd. Clear passage up from Deerfield. Cobble 60%, gravel 40%. 10' wide.

Location_Description: Road just above house above dumping area
Habitat_Comment: Nice high gradient brook; clear water w/many pools and good cover; nice wild brook stream

Location_Description: From Deerfield to Dam
Habitat_Comment: Not much at lower end; weed growth on rocks; large cobble boulder substrate. Marginal trout hab. Above road slightly better. Old dam about 400' upstream from mouth. Low flow impediment.

Location_Description: Rt. 8A crossing from breached stone dam upstream
Habitat_Comment: Raining; worked up from old damat dirt road; nice pools good cover

Location_Description: From Tunnel  Rd. upstream including pool bend culvert
Habitat_Comment: Land owned by PG&E; small brook - widthof 5" probably dries up most years. Cobble 60%, gravel 20%, Boulder 20%. Mature forest canopy, moderate gradietn, small plunge pools and undercut banks.

Location_Description: Chapter 90 work, Taylor Brook Rd.
Habitat_Comment: High gradient stream near road washout; substrate cobble/boulder, plunge pools, riffles. Stream width 19'. Many stoneflies. Mature canopy. Rocky banks. Above ave. flow.

Location_Description: From Road crossing upstream at washout- log dam
Habitat_Comment: Area near washout, left bank; rip-rapped in lower section; heavy willow trees on other side

Location_Description: Along Hoosic tunnel
Habitat_Comment: Either conductivity is high or new battery is acting up

Location_Description: From fenceline upstream
Habitat_Comment: Lower portion is pasture; Active livestock eroded banks, no cover, wide streambed 5' wide. Culvert above pasture is major barrier, section above also grazed. Has mature canopy. Very few fish caught in this section. Culvert from Deerfield is partial barrier, <2'.

Location_Description: From River Rd.
Habitat_Comment: High gradient stream. Boulders ledge pools. LWD. Clean. Boulder cobble gravel substrate. Full canopy cover and stable rocky banks. Mature veg. Ave width 15' varies. Riffle depth <1'. Max pool depth 3'.

Location_Description: From Charlemont upstream
Habitat_Comment: Road culvert is upstream barrier; EBT looked fat and healthy; boulder/gravel substrate, good spawning & hodling hab. Ledge pools, large woody debris, good mature canopy.

Bearswamp outlet accessed from track; all yoy trout caught below stag. Cascading falls. Must be reproduction in main Deerfield to that point. Gravel/cobblein lower stretch. Steep high gradient above tracks. Culvert is semi-passable.

Location_Description: From E.Buckland Rd. crossing upstream
Habitat_Comment: Nice moderate gradient stream; cobble/gravel, nice undercut banks, root wads. Wider stream above 20+ feet wide up to small access beach. Wild Rainbow Trout. Cobble 30%, Gravel 40%, fines/sand 30%. Mature canopy.

Location_Description: Upper stretch from Dodge Rd. up to junk truck & natural log dam
Habitat_Comment: High gradient; large ledge pools; boulders; clean water, lots of LWD. Pool riffle hab. Beautiful high gradient river at medium flows.

Location_Description: Large pulloff just after Heath/Charlemont line
Habitat_Comment: Very high flow; just salmon & brookies;

Location_Description: Small pulloff
Habitat_Comment: Logging road by telephone pole

Location_Description: Large picnic area
Habitat_Comment: Flow a bit high but water clear

Location_Description: Downstream from Hazelton Road
Habitat_Comment: Access through property below private pond; creek reportedly dried up last year

Location_Description: From river upstream through culvert and bridge
Habitat_Comment: From Deerfield up under tracks to southside road crossing; good canopy cover, shrubs debris in brook, cobble mostly. Upstream passage not good during low flow. Not much in first section near road.

Location_Description: East & West of Hamlet Mill Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Deep station; turbidity reduced efficiency, generally poor;

Location_Description: Worked n. of bridge to park
Habitat_Comment: Lots of nice EBT; one eel ~24" not collected; water flow ok

Location_Description: Just S. of VT. Border
Habitat_Comment: Flow was high for season

Location_Description: Confluence@Taylor Brook
Tree across brook s. of bridge
Habitat_Comment: None given by this crew

Location_Description: Commune winery ford, above
Habitat_Comment: None given

Location_Description: South of Royalston Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Strong sewage smell; 200 yds. Below treatment plant; few pools

Location_Description: Off McLaughlin Trail
Habitat_Comment: All BT stocked; newts present

Location_Description: Persick Road crossing upstream, including the pool at the base of the culvert downstream
Habitat_Comment: Heavy overgrowth in early sections, widens out upstream

Location_Description: Confluence of Millers River
Fernald School - north of "private road"
Habitat_Comment: Stream high, fair efficiency, sampled within Fernald School, all EBT wild

Location_Description: Birch Hill
Habitat_Comment: Nice area, all EBT stocked

Location_Description: North of Tully Road
Habitat_Comment: Deep section, intermittent shocking, poor efficiency, all trout apparently stocked

Location_Description: started at Bondsville I and continued to just north of red bridge
Habitat_Comment: Fish were very localized, Many of the big LMB's were caught in a 50 meter stretch.  Saw one school of about 50 white suckers (10-18") at one location

Location_Description: Dublin Steel access
Habitat_Comment: Very poor efficiency, wide, fairly deep section with riffle at top and bottom of reach.  Fairly impossible to capture trout or other large fish.

Location_Description: Started 169m downstream of Bondsville I, shocked up to Dam Pool
Habitat_Comment: Very wide stretch, not very effective in pool section. Shocked only one (road)side of pool section (first 60m of section). Zig-zagged in riffle section below dam pool. All trout in riffle below dam pool. Heavy beaver activity, 20 felled trees to 12" diameter.

Location_Description: Downstream of George Hill Road
Habitat_Comment: Very shallow, rocky, some riffle, touched the edge of the bridge pool.  Got the EBT in the riffle just below the bridge.

Location_Description: Downstream or route 140, Behind Precision Paving, between two bridges
Start downstream of Prescott Street
Habitat_Comment: Rubble Bottom, good overhead canopy, mostly riffle habitat with pool last 50 meters before bridge.  Very inefficient pick-up - many fallfish uncaptured.  Stream very low - fish concentrated, most of stretch < 1 foot deep.

Location_Description: Route 13 behind the feed store, sampled riffle below dam skirt and dam skirt
Habitat_Comment: We sampled only the riffle/rock stretchbelow the dam downstream of the route13/119 intersection behind the feed store (not the trestle dam log jam)

Location_Description: Downstream of Route 13
Habitat_Comment: Beaver dams, sand, gravel, pushed lots of fish without capture.  Very inefficient sample.  Spot-shocked the cover and woody debris.

Location_Description: Off Townsend Road, W. Groton, end of dirt access road in Groton Conservation Area
Habitat_Comment: Boulders, ledge, and rubble - weed covered (slippery).  Partly open canopy, tall trees on shoreline. 8-24" deep stretch, lots of fallfish, frogs, crayfish

Location_Description: Junction of Sucker Brook and Nissitissit
Habitat_Comment: Sampled a small stretch of the Niss, then turned up Sucker Brook.  The stream was loaded with cyprinids and catastomids, literally thousands of them. All trout sampled came from Sucker Brook.

Location_Description: Shocked up to but not including Bondsville II
Downstream of Summer Street
Upstream of West River Street
Habitat_Comment: White pine/red maple canopy, dogwood, alder, ivy shrub cover, aquatic plant: sparganium, callictryche, ceratophylum, rock mosses

Location_Description: Upstream of Gilboa Pond
Downstream of 129 from 144 meters downstream of abandoned bridge abutment to abutment
Habitat_Comment: Start of stretch was sand/silt bottom with enclosed canopy, upper portion of reacg was stone/rubble bottom with open canopy.  Stream width almost doubled from downstream to upstream.

Location_Description: Quabog Transfer
Habitat_Comment: Shallow riffle section, few 18' deep pools but otherwise very shallow

Location_Description: Up from Beach
Between two bridges, ending at "Roaring Brook Construction" - 111 Gosnold's Lane
Up 325' from Clark Brook confluence
Habitat_Comment: Tributary to Clark Brook.Forested, moderate gradient stream.Good habitat, plunge pools, lateral scour pools.  Not many fish, some YOY but not as many as expected.  Also many of the fish smaller than predicted by habitat.River seems to have moved sediment recently.

Location_Description: Upstream of Baptist Road crossing
Habitat_Comment: Some of the nicest trout in the area.  Good plunge pools, nice bank buffer from pasture

Location_Description: Upstream of Persick Road
Habitat_Comment: Nice river, clean gravel substrate, some cobble.  Box culvert at road is partial barrier

Location_Description: Upstream of Williams Road Crossing
Habitat_Comment: Good habitat, corner scour pools, solid banks, mature vegetation.  Impressive-looking EBT stream. 5-15' wide, clean gravel, cobble

Location_Description: Upstream of Williamsburg Road Crossing
Habitat_Comment: Stream flows through trustees of reservation lands.  Lots of ledge, large boulders, cascade just downstream of crossing.

Location_Description: Downstream of Hallockville Road
Habitat_Comment: Lots of old beaver activity.  70% Gravel/pebble substrate, 30% fines.  Woody shrubs on both banks, decent shading, not many mature trees, some aquatic vegetation

Location_Description: Upstream of West Hill Road
Habitat_Comment: Clear water. Nice habitat, plunge pools, 40% boulder, 40% gravel, 20% cobble.  Has seen high flows recently.Sterile, not many fish, large falls just downstream of sample reach.
All trout recently stocked, about 1/2 w.s. picked up, good efficiency, YOY B., G.S. common, few YOY LMB, good all around LMB population

Location_Description: Fish Park
Habitat_Comment: Too wide, 75% of river shocked, fair efficiency, 3 large BT missed.  Good SMB habitat and population

Location_Description: Athol Conservation Area
Habitat_Comment: All BT stocked, good habitat (all run), end at riffle

Location_Description: Downstream of Robbins Road Bridge
Habitat_Comment: Quick survey done to coincide with flash fllod bridge washout remediation advisory

Location_Description: Along Route 8A upstream of crossing
Habitat_Comment: Original Cover Sheet Lost, Collected half of dace in stream

Location_Description: Upstream of Monroe Road Crossing
Habitat_Comment: Upper position of Cascade Brook before flows down by tunnel. Access upstream of road, below is private land.

Location_Description: Downstream of Route 105
Gravel  Access Ramp - off West St.
From pull off below County Road, Western side down path
Habitat_Comment: Lots of LWD, plunge pools, 50% boulder, 10% cobble, 40% gravel.  Strange brook trout captured with no spots, no vermiculations.  Deep gorge, heavily forested with mature hemlock, etc.

Location_Description: From Clesson Road Upstream
Habitat_Comment: Lot of sand sediment, high degree of embeddedness

Location_Description: Above Route 181 to low-head dam
Habitat_Comment: Steep Banks both sides of river. Wide, boulders, riffles and runs.  Good pocket water with steep banks on both sides of the river.  West side forested, good canopy.  East sidedirt, grass with scrub banks.  Very innefficient sample.  Only saw one fish that we missed.

Location_Description: First bridge at gate downstream
M+M trail crossing upstream
Habitat_Comment: High flow

Location_Description: 200 yards east of dam
Habitat_Comment: High water much reduced efficiency(<2 of 5), good habitat

Location_Description: West of Brattle Street, Tributary to Indian Lake
Habitat_Comment: Excellent habitat, pool silt and sand covered

Location_Description: Boundary Street
Habitat_Comment: Habitat degraded by sediment (sand and silt), few rooted aquatics.

Location_Description: Downstream of Fruit Street
Habitat_Comment: Very different habitat than upstream.  Diversion channel (2-3 meters wide) diverts 20% of flow for 200 meters.  Old dam in diversion channel is breached.

Location_Description: Snowmobile bridge on River Road
Indian Hollow gate pull-off
Habitat_Comment: Awful Shocking conditions, runs through rocks, many crevaces.  One run only, 16 salmon total - stocked in high water conditions.

Location_Description: West of River Street
Habitat_Comment: One of few riffle sections on West, all trout stocked

Location_Description: N. of RR tracks off Grove Street
Habitat_Comment: Good habitat, little EBT spawn habitat in section.  Good pools, should have been nice EBT.  Lots of apparent road run-off probably impacts spawning

Location_Description: Upstream of Shaker Road crossing
Habitat_Comment: Shocker displayed a warning/malfunction indicator so we stopped short of the 100 meters. Very good habitat

Location_Description: Bridge crossing Pochassic St.
Habitat_Comment: Spotted turtle sighting.  Large illegal gravel dam downstream of sample site.  Report filed with DEP (Karen Hirshberg).

Location_Description: Loomis Road crossing off Route 9
Crossing at Abbott Hill Road from small confluence at camp upstream.
Habitat_Comment: Shallow, moderate gradient stream.  Average depth 6".  50% cobble, 20% boulder, 20% gravel, some fines in pools, series of small, steep pool and riffles, one large pool at culvert,  Cold, clear water.  Levels probably reduced to pools and trickles in summer.  Mature canopy, stable banks

Location_Description: Upstream from Northwest Road
Habitat_Comment: Very low flow, small riffles.  Flow was huge on 7/25 and very low 7/24.  Habotat is great - flow issues are prevalent.

Location_Description: Adjacent to Loomis Road
Habitat_Comment: Lots of woody debris, goo low gradient stream with lots of undercuts and deep pools

Location_Description: First Bridge on Route 23 heading upstream
River Road Bridge (middle)
Rt. 57, pulloff just below bridge
Habitat_Comment: Microdace able to elude nets

Location_Description: 300 feet downstream of old dam; DS of West Hartland Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Shocked in state park up to old dam. Good crayfish population, many sizes, good canopy cover, tannic water. 50% boulder, 50% gravel, some pool/riffle habitat

Location_Description: US of Skyline Trail crossing from old dam to old dam
Habitat_Comment: Moderate gradient stream.  Mature canopy, 100% shaded.  30% Boulder, 30% cobble, 40% gravel and smalls.  Lot of overhanging vegetation.  Pools sandy and 8" deep

Location_Description: Loop road crossing upstream
Habitat_Comment: 10% ledge, 70% cobble, high gradient, a few barriers.  Not much water, average depth a couple of inches. Mature canopy, some LWD.  Spring-fed maintains low-flow in summer.

Location_Description: From old main road crossing.  Below bridge upstream
Habitat_Comment: 20% boulder, 40% cobble, some embedednes and fines probably from pond or beavers.  Moderate to high gradient, short riffles, average depth 9".  High water temperature, mostly warmwater fish.

Location_Description: 2nd road crossing above bridge pool below culvert upstream
Habitat_Comment: Included pool below culvert through upstream mostly large boulder, high gradient plunge pools, some gravel/pebble substrate.  Good canopy cover.

Location_Description: Shaw Road crossing, 60 meters downstream up to culvert
Habitat_Comment: Large stream with small plunge pools.  Average depth 3".  Full of sediment, probably from dirt road.  Not much water.  Poorly built road for sediment control

Location_Description: N. Blandford road crossing, next to swampy acres home
Habitat_Comment: Boulder, cobble, gravel.  High conductivity looks like levels fluctuate greatly. Currently pretty close to low flow conditions.

Location_Description: Indian oven crossing begin at bottom of culvert upstream
Habitat_Comment: Low gradient stream, slow moving, runs shallow.  Substrate 70% fines, 20% cobble, average depth, 8".  Many small dace

Location_Description: From confluence with the Westfield upstream
Habitat_Comment: Shocked from confluence upstream.  At tributary, main channel was dry so we proceeded up feeder additional 50'.  60% cobble, 10% boulder, 30% gravel/pebble. Wide, rocky brook probably flows high in spring.  Not much water now.  Limited habitat mostly riffle, pocket water.

Location_Description: Road crossing at route 183 under bridge, upstream
Habitat_Comment: Good crayfish population.  Moderate gradient stream.  30% boulder, 40% cobble, 30% gravel, shallow pools, 80% canopy cover, stable banks with good vegetation.

Location_Description: Buffington Hill Road crossing.  Begin at sharp turn below road, work to culvert
Habitat_Comment: Low water conditions.  Boulder 30%, cobble 30%, mature canopy, some fines and embeddedness in pool.  LWD 10%.  Reported to dry up almost completely in summer.

Location_Description: From windsor Bush Road crossing upstream.
Habitat_Comment: Began at pool 10 m above culvert.  Followed stream channel to left until beaver dam.  Brook has recently split into channels from beaver activity.  10% Boulder, 50% cobble/gravel, 40% silt/fines, average depth 4".  Small stream which flows into Windsor Jambs Brook.

Location_Description: Bank Road Bridge crossing from natural barrier below bridge up to confluence with freeder
Habitat_Comment: Extraordinary high macroinvertebrate presence.  Numerous mayflies, some stoneflies.  20% ledge, 15% boulder, 50% cobble, remainder gravel.  Some fines and imbeddedness in spots.  Mature canopy covers 80%.  Ave. depth = 1'

Location_Description: Along Stage Road
Downstream of Littleville Dam
Habitat_Comment: Lots of crayfish

Location_Description: Schoolhouse Road bridge

Habitat_Comment: Very clear water, no structure along shore

Location_Description: Downstream of Hiram Blair Road crossing (private road) off Route 23.
Habitat_Comment: Brook must be very flashy.  We sampled one 90 meter stretch, then shocked the pool at the base of the cliffs.

Location_Description: Pull-off below Walker Island
Lower Valley Road paved bridge
Habitat_Comment: One run only for lack of salmon
Used 2 backpacks, I with 2 probes, 1 with rat and probe

Location_Description: North of Route 85
Habitat_Comment: Good efficiency (4), few pools, mainly riffle habitat, low flow.  BT wild, EBT stocked, sparse fish population.

Location_Description: Ward Hill off route 20, east of STTP Road
Habitat_Comment: Good habitat, very good efficiency (4) low flows.  Spring flooding probably limited YOY EBT.  Habitat should support more EBT.  Station length limited by heavy growth.

Location_Description: Yellick Park off Solomon Pond Road
Habitat_Comment: Good habitat pool-riffle ration excellent.  High water reduced efficiency

Location_Description: North of Randall Street
Habitat_Comment: Poor habitat, few pools, entire section sand and small gravel, silt bottom.  Spring flooding probably limits EBT.  Excellent efficiency (5 of 5). All trout wild, excellent water quality, clear cold.

Location_Description: off Lancaster Road
Habitat_Comment: All EBT wild. +- 50% of YOY EBT, fair habitat, especially juvenile, lack of pools

Location_Description: Middle of nowhere
First bridge on main road heading downstream
Habitat_Comment: Many, many, many sculpins

Location_Description: Pulloff below bridge upstream of Ireland
250 meters downstream of first bridge on heath road
Habitat_Comment: Only rainbow trout was vouchered

Location_Description: Lover's Lane
Below Bear Creek Store Bridge
Field upstream of falls
Upstream from road culvert near horse barns
Habitat_Comment: Most trout caught near 8" deep root wad.  Channel starting to braid.  Thick sediment deposits, sand over silt.  Almost all trout had parasites (learnia).  Examples are preserved in the watershed voucher collection.

Location_Description: Brook Street
Habitat_Comment: Even mix of substrate from cobble to silt

Location_Description: Below Brook Street
Habitat_Comment: water was high

Location_Description: Worthington Rod and Gun Club
Down stream of sample conducted by NE District off fruit street.  We sampled this adjacent stretch because NE Dist. Reported faulty sampling gear in the last sample.
Habitat_Comment: Good bend pools, some sedimentation present.  EBT was probably stocked and had a spinal deformity.

Location_Description: Dump road crossing, downstream
Habitat_Comment: Fast flow - wide

Location_Description: 300 feet above Old Connecticut Path
Habitat_Comment: worked excellent, 90% efficiency, gravel bottom, cut banks, EBT nursury, many crayfish

Location_Description: West of Manchaug Street
Habitat_Comment: Fair efficiency, high flows, too wide for backpack.  Good habitat but few pools with depth.  All BT stocked.

Location_Description: East of Gilboa Street
Habitat_Comment: Good habitat, boulders, deep pools.  BT stocked.

Location_Description: South and North of Hartford Ave.
Habitat_Comment: Excellent habitat, high fertility, poor fish population for habitat. Depth and flow-impacted sample. BT stocked (not at this site). Downstream of Hopedale WWTP and Draper Mill. Many crayfish.

Location_Description: South of Hatrford Ave.
Habitat_Comment: Few fish for excellent habitat

Location_Description: off old 146 - 100 yards south of bridge
Habitat_Comment: All BT stocked, larger holdover from 2000.  All EBT wild.  Heavy Spring flow probably reduced # of fish.  Should have been more given habitat.

Location_Description: West of River Road
Habitat_Comment: Good habitat, heavy sand and silt from floods eliminated YOY habitat in 2001.  Sample East of large Spring, EBT and BT wild

Location_Description: East of Gravel Pit Road, off Follette Street

Location_Description: South and North of Fowler Street crossing

Habitat_Comment: 1 brown trout measured (56mm) was likely a n ATS.  Repeat of survey site done 2 years ago.  Sample in 2001 was during heat wave and low water extreme so the sample was repeated to see the comparison.

Location_Description: HA George Propane Company
Habitat_Comment: Potamogeton crispus growing in river.  Many dace missed.  Flow moderately high.  Some pools too deep to accurately sample.  Surprised not to see some bigger BT.  May have missed some in deep pools.

Location_Description: Green River Confluence
Habitat_Comment: Kept a couple unidentified cyprinids, may be CS but looked different. Missed a few large fish in deep pool.  Flows high (2X average).  This is a repeat of 2002 sample site.  Missed some dace because of high water.

Location_Description: Coles Field, Williams College
Habitat_Comment: Flows high, about 2X average flow, according to USGS.  Visibility in water marginal.  5 Huge brown trout.  Deep-bodied impressive fish may not have been caught at low flow conditions.  Kept three cyprinids which may be CS.  This is a repeat of same stationas last year.  Pictures of trout taken.

Location_Description: Shell Station off Route 2 end of flood shutes
Habitat_Comment: 2 Backpacks.  River wide, sampling not complete even wi th two packs.  River smelled like sewerage.  Collecting samples for Williams College student for PCB analysis.  Sampling was more spot shocking than complete survey.

Location_Description: Zylonite Station Road
Habitat_Comment: Stopped to work up fish halfway through.  Flow conditions relatively high.  Overcast, visibility not great.  Some pools too deep but pretty accurate sample.  Probably some dace missed.  High conductivity.  Some odor to water probably from WWTP.  Lots of toys in river - balls, skateboards, etc.  One of the Areas looked at by K. Simmons in 2000.

Location_Description: View Bridge Konkapot Road Crossing.
Habitat_Comment: Used 2 Backpacks.  Good flow, nice habitat.  Surprised to see low # of trout.  Couldn't sample pool below bridge completely because of depth, sampled rest of area well.

Location_Description: First Bridge crossing river road
Habitat_Comment: Repeat of station done in '97, '98.  Low flow, clear and sunny.  Used two backpacks.  Worked up to riffle.

Location_Description: Southfield Road sheep pasture
Habitat_Comment: Should come back for Barge site.  Too deep to accurately sample.  Not an efficient sample, river too wide and deep.  Saw some bigger fish including trout which we did not catch.  Data should be used with caution.

Location_Description: Hudson Brook Road
Habitat_Comment: Skipped many dace.  Note LNS only, no WS.  Worked from top of natural bridge pond to steep falls.  Lots of big stonefly nymphs.  RT stocked this spring.  Smaller suckers tough to ID so vouchered.

Location_Description: 1896 house below foot bridge
Habitat_Comment: Nice clear water.  Plenty of sculpins.  Lots of caddis, stoneflies, mayflies.  Check versus past surveys, less EBT now, low flow.  Nice water better holding habitat downstream.

Location_Description: Tyringham Road, above spring and sewerage outlet.
Habitat_Comment: Began above sewer outlet.  Half run, half riffle.  Missed a few BT and RB.  This site is further upstream of last year's site.  Odor from plant strong.  Big LNS.

Location_Description: Winsock Industrial Park
Habitat_Comment: Missed one 9" BT.  Unable to fully sample deep corner pool.  Could have picked up some additional RB.  Odor from sewerage treatment plant.

Location_Description: Division Street Upstream
Habitat_Comment: High water conditions.  About twice average flow.  Missed at least 2 big carp.  Missed multiple smallmouth bass.  All BNM correct except one with a question mark.  Unknown sunfish pumpkinseeds or bluegills.

Location_Description: Old Pleasant Street Bridge to Turnpike Bridge
Habitat_Comment: Missed 4 Brown Trout. Pobably missed smaller fish.  Fats water and high flow conditions.

Location_Description: Behind Sunset Motel Route 20
Habitat_Comment: High flow for September.  Clear, cool weather.  Visibility reduced by high flow.  Missed some fish.  Not as many small baitfish.  Caught black crappie.

Location_Description: Route 183 Pulloff
Habitat_Comment: 2 Backpacks, not a complete, sample because of river width.  Let 7 carp go by.

Location_Description: Capen Road gravel bar; NE of road and betweer Stevens and Childs Bk confluences
Habitat_Comment: 2 trout dead in stream before.  1 month after major flow event.

Location_Description: Path from Fisher and Woodcock Road

Location_Description: Upstream from Route 25

Location_Description: Up from Sampsons Mill Road
Habitat_Comment: Sand bottom, large amounts of woody debris, salter trout research.

Mountain Rd.

I took scales on 3 trout.

Location_Description: 1st stocking bridge. Turner Hill Rd

Br Mill R Hampden 17 degrees highly developed Lat 42.10071  Lon. 72.43200

waterbody: UNT to East Branch Tully River (1)

Location_Description: US of W. Mountain Rd.

Location_Description: US of Tully Brook Rd.

Location_Description: US of Adams St. (100 m); off Main Poland Rd.
Habitat_Comment: potential ref site; rd xing DS is dirt rd w/ perched culvert and large pool below; flows lower and no US passage possible; dirt rd along left bank; sampled US of yard area adj to right bank; nice brook, clear water; nice shaded riparian; several undercuts and pools holding EBT.

Location_Description: walked up from Mill Bk.
Habitat_Comment: rock/boulder substrate, clear water, good flow, riffle/pool; unimpaired stream; on list of potential ref. site.

Location_Description: US of Rt. 2 (~30 m)

Location_Description: US of Rt. 7 (~75 m)
Habitat_Comment: Nice, clear water, cobble/boulder substrate; some sedimentation covering substrate; unpaved driveway along left bank and house on above hill; several downed trees over brook; eroded banks both sides; barbed-wire fenced pasture along right bank.

Location_Description: Adj. to Main Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Last 15 m above falls had no fish; stopped at larger falls; staircase series of pools; boulder/rock substrate; on list of potential ref sites; original GPS coord. incorrect, so changed afterward.

waterbody: UNT to W. Br. Of Green R.
Location_Description: US of dirt rd xing (~20 m), N of Rt. 43 S xing
Habitat_Comment: Nice brook; runs along maintained dirt rd; 1 house along other side of rd and possible new house construction upstream; no signs of disturbance within stream; cobble substrate and very clear water; riparian around stream channel good but buffer not wide; on list of potential ref sites.

Location_Description: Off Petersburg Rd., US of trib crossing
Habitat_Comment: Clear water, clay bottom; started ~50 m US of trib that crosses road;  all US of last rd xing; salamanders, BT found; EBT coloring light; good pool/riffle frequency; some exposed bedrock; 1 BT vouchered, very pale (no markings).

Location_Description: US of Mass. Ave.
Habitat_Comment: Nice stream; sampled US of 2nd AT bridge xing (~50 m); thought we were above "impact" zone, but found and a large circular raised cement holding pond; water is able to flow through and over a spillway, but no US passage is possible; habitat US of pond very similar to DS; cobble, small boulder substrate, pools/runs, very clear water; rocks covered in algae and piles upon piles of newly hatched "caterpilars"; variations in coloring on EBT (shocking or light substrate).

Location_Description: US of Churchill St.; N. of Hancock Rd. intersection.
Habitat_Comment: Nice small stream, very clear water; good flow, nice riffles with some nice pools around old blow downs; at end of reach barbed wire fence across channel, possible pasture area, but riparian and stream not immediately affected; also sampled both sides of island at end of reach; lost 1 large BT (200+ mm)--may have jumped out of live well; sample started ~100 m US of rd xing; on list of potential ref sites.

Location_Description: US of pond on Snowy Owl (Brodie Mtn.) Ski Area
Habitat_Comment: US of pond ~50 m; fire rd and pipeline along right bank;most of stream high gradient, exposed bedrock w/ 1 large pool and couple of smaller pools; good flow coming through but only fills 50% of channel; steep-sided banks and riparian width <10 m on right bank.

Location_Description: US of Potter Mountain Rd. xing in Pittsfield State Forest
Habitat_Comment: High gradient, big boulders and large bedrock, moss covered rocks, relatively steep-sided banks on both sides; spring salamander (~7") found (very light coloration; not many fish, missed a few, some nice plunge pools; ATV activity in vicinity (in state park); started sample ~50m US of rd xing(dirt rd); on list of potential ref sites.; original GPS coord. incorrect, so changed afterward.

Location_Description: US of South Rd. (~100 m)
Habitat_Comment: Decent flow, moss covered rocks, moderate siltation in pools; deep pools holding large EBT; started ~100 m US of rd.; old wooden foot bridge 1/2-way through sample reach; lots of frogs; sampled right branch of stream US of bridge--looked like main channel; some historical channelization; most fish were in section below bridge; US of bridge became higher gradient w/ smaller pools connected by small cascades.

Location_Description: DS of fire road (~20 m)
Habitat_Comment: some EBT caught in backwater/side channel; gravel/cobble substrate w/ some boulders; log jams common and good riparian cover over stream; more gravel and different stream channel than previous samples in Douglas State Forest; sampled across confluence of smaller trib.

Location_Description: US of Curtin Rd.
Habitat_Comment: 100 m US from gravel rd xing; forested watershed; sand/gravel substrate; large fish all from one large pool section/LWD; signs of selective logging on left bank, but not major impact; on list of potential ref sites.

Location_Description: Windsor Rd. off Notch Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Decent efficiency, little cascades all around, clear water; road parallels stream and may have channelized stream on left bank; sampled above last stream xing, but could not go to location farther US as planned due to housing along stream; passing neighbors mentioned complaint about horse farm w/ too many horses for farm size and possible run-off from over-sized manure pile near stream; Jeff Reynolds (WD intern) mentioned that stream may be used as ref site by Hoosic River Watershed Assoc. for their own IBI work.

Location_Description: adj to dirt 4X4 rd (left off Route 7, past Brodie Mt. Rd.), part of ski area
Habitat_Comment: High gradient bedrock, lots of cascading waterfalls, decent sampling efficiency; fallen trees in the way; large waterfall at 97 m, end of large, deep  pool;  wind farm construction along top of mountain was mentioned (pose problem for stream?)

Location_Description: Upstream of Moore Hill Rd. crossing
Habitat_Comment: Site is old pond, but stream is defined and runs through old pond; pools prevalent w/ some silty substrate, gets better upstream; lot of sediment covering in pools and rocks/boulders; runs through DAR forest; old stone dam ~20 m downstream of sample reach; stream channel flows through tumbled boulders from old dam.

Location_Description: Downstream of Hell's Kitchen Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Up from road; falls followed by marshy area; half-mile from road small pond; gravel/roack bottom w/ some mud; riffle/pool habitat; (State Forest Land).

Location_Description: Upstream of Monroe Rd.
Habitat_Comment: 100 m up from road; roack/gravel substrate; big eyes on fish (abnormally large-M.D.); clear water; 2 deep pools.

Location_Description: Upstream of Watson Rd.
Habitat_Comment: beaver activity upstream (dam, lodge); remains of dam just upstream from road; large fish in deep pools; large rock substrate.

Location_Description: US of trail xing, beneath powerlines off Rattlesnake Gutter Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Spring salamander (170 mm) found; loose cobble substrate; worked US of powerline clearing; clearwater; connects to Sawmill R. through powerline rd. (runs on powerline rd.); nice stream, shaded woody area; doesn't appear to be intermittent; good flow.

Location_Description: Along side of Dodge Rd., N. of E. Hawley Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Clear water, large boulders, sandy substrate, lots of small plunge pools, cool water; brook runs next to road, some large fallen trees over brook, missed a few EBT; doesn't appear to be intermittent, some channelization b/c of road (old stone wall); could not sample US of Dodge Rd. xing b/c little flow and swampy.

Location_Description: ~75 m US of confluence with Dudleyville Bk (behind house)
Habitat_Comment: Nice, clear, high gradient stream; several plunge pools; neighbor says stream dries up nearly every year; only a few fish, but may be able to find refuge in pools during drier years; flow is decent in stream and plenty of habitat to support fish otherwise.

Location_Description: US of last Dry Hill Rd. xing (~100 m)
Habitat_Comment: Nice stream, small, clear water; low, but decent flow; portion of stream reach skipped b/c entire channel underneath large root wad/debris mat, added extra at end; mostly gravel, cobble, and some boulder substrate, and sandy/silt substrate in larger pools; sampled US from house/yard area; lots of CWD.

Location_Description: US of 2nd (may be 3rd--not shown on map) rd xing on Cross Place Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Man-made pond ~75 m upstream of sample reach; worked up to pond; started sample ~100 m US of rd xing; GS, BB found; some very silty areas, moss covered rocks, more pool and run habitat, few riffles, some slightly undercut banks; beaver impoundment; beaver impoundment farther US, couldn't sample there, so sample farther DS (here); some clearing on West (left) bank; pond is in backyard and has stone wall perimeter and possible channel diversion.

Location_Description: Adj. to Lovers Lane
Habitat_Comment: trib. To Shaker Mill Bk.; cobble/gravel substrate; good flow; unimpaired watershed; mid-channel gravel bars; undercut banks; sampled US of "invisible fence" markers; walked in on trails from Lover's Lane; may have crossed town line in sample reach.

Location_Description: Adj. to Wendy Rd. (down logging rd. and in  logged area)
Habitat_Comment: Down logging rd.; recent partial clearing of surrounding forest; sampled down from log "bridge"; gravel/sand substrate; undercut banks; good riffle/pool habitat; sedimentation of substrate and bank erosion into channel; stream appears to impacted by logging practices, especially at logging rd. xing  US of sample reach; riparian may be no more than 10-20 m on either bank (not enough to prevent erosion into channel); beaver sam visible US of logging rd xing (~50 m); signs posted for Hull Forest Products-"Danger Shooting Area".

Location_Description: US of Northfield Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Upstream from rd.; cobble/gravel substrate; tannic water; stocked stream; one deep pool held several large fish.

Location_Description: US of North Farm Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Upstream from rd.; rock/cobble substrate; unimpacted upstream section; narrow stream with good flow; small, shallow pools; fish in good condition.

Location_Description: US of Bannis Rd. xing in Savoy State Forest
Habitat_Comment: Worked US of culvert; culvert perched ~4' above water on DS side, blocked w/ debris US; cold clear water, cobble substrate w/ some boulders; some tree falls, one large log jam US blocked w/ debris, sediment deposition and sand in pools; some erosion on both banks causing undercuts; sample reach in Savoy State Forest.

Location_Description: Adj. to N. Warger Rd., DS of last (3rd) house.
Habitat_Comment: Small headwater stream; size range of EBT present, but neighbor (Wes Rowe) mentioned stream was intermittent most years; some pools present that may be refuges during dry years; crossed town line at ~80 m into sample; nice location w/ forested riparian; neighbor (Wes Rowe) logging activity in progress on his property w/ plans for development on other side of N. Warger Rd.; N. Warger Rd. extension to 3rd (Rowe's) and last (currently) house is dirt.

Location_Description: US of Prospect St. (~50 m)-runs adj. to road
Habitat_Comment: Nice stream, clear, flowing water; some channelization along road (historical); runs behind backyard of house US; yard/flower garden goes up to left bank; several large EBT captured under stone bridge in garden.

waterbody: UNT to UNT to Mill Brook
Location_Description: US of Prospect St. xing (~50 m), W. of Summit St. intersection
Habitat_Comment: Nice stream, clear flowing water w/ pools/runs, but sediment film over substrate especially in pools; runs along Prospect St. and crosses (road) ~50 m DS of start of sample

Location_Description: US of Shaw Rd. (~50 m), W. of Bumpus Trail xing
Habitat_Comment: Nice stream, narrow channel, clear flowing water; runs along Shaw Rd. (dirt rd.) for 1st 50 m; old stone wall b/w stream and rd.; just W of Bumpus Trail xing; silty in pools.

Location_Description: US of Baptist Corner Rd., W of N. Warger Rd., behind 2nd house on left
Habitat_Comment: followed trail behind house, past 1st trib (sampled last week); could not find 2nd trib, so sampled Drakes Bk w/ permission of landowner; several dried up "spring" tribs along banks; nice riffle/pool series w/ some undercuts and tree falls; good riparian buffer and cover; owner mentioned some clear-cutting for wildlife conservation farther DS (between sample reach and 1st trib); start of sample actually coincided w/ confluence of trib we were looking for, but was dried up.

Location_Description: Upstream of Bridge St., along baseball field
Habitat_Comment: Medium to high flow; larger RT likely a hatchery fish; heavy siltation in spots.

Location_Description: Hopper Rd., Private Drive, Sky Meadow
Habitat_Comment: Riffle habitat, high gradient; sampled upstream of road crossing; site was accessed from private driveway off Hopper Rd. (driveway leads to place called Sky Meadow)

Location_Description: Downstream of W. Mountain Rd. (or Mountain Rd.?)
Habitat_Comment: Sampled DS of road up to culvert, including culvert pool; wide culvert, bottomless, except for drop of which is fish barrier (1-1/2'), concrete; very few browns, stopped stocking stream in '05; Pond fish are likely from reservoir up above.

Location_Description: Upstream of W. Mountain Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Small, high gradient stream; some bank manipulation; medium flow.

Location_Description: Washington Mt. Rd., where rd. turns to dirt
Habitat_Comment: Very fast moving water!!  One more person to net would be good.  Great habitat, no silt, lots of boulders; missed a nice big BT; may want to sample again for better efficiency.

Location_Description: Upstream of Washington Mt. Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Sampling efficiency better than last sample; conditions good; rocky habitat; stream not nearly as fast as up above (at our last sample location).

Location_Description: Entrance to Beartown State Forest

Location_Description: Along Branch Rd, S of Woodard Hill Rd 0.25mi
US of West Branch Rd xing (Adamsville Rd)
Habitat_Comment: Started above bedrock slide. Stream full of large rocks, mix of runs throuh smaller rocks. Boulder pools, several shallow & deep pools. There was ~2m bedrock falls/slides but sculpins and brook trout were found above both falls. Fields on both sides with 5-7m buffer. CFR

Location_Description: Site #3- US of Crowley Rd, W of Greenland Rd
Habitat_Comment: low water, very few AS (bad year)

Location_Description: Site #2 US of Muddy Pond Rd bridge, just E of I-190
Habitat_Comment: rust collored recipitate over substrate, low water

Location_Description: US of Falls Rd xing S of state line
Habitat_Comment: Water is very dark, tanic, we probably missed 40-50% of the fish. Shocked pool on DS side of bridge, only fish found was 1 CCS (~90mm?). CFR

Location_Description: off E. Leverett Rd, next to garden in a meadow, 1mi E of Leverett Rd
Habitat_Comment: Wide stream. Sandy & pebble substrate, good flow. Some deep pools & occasional riffles. Large EBT & BT found. Old beaver dam 1/2 way thru reach. Slow deep H2O above, dam. Dam also has fallen trees in front. Undercut banks under root structures. Found CM above old dam. Lots of crayfish. Decent canopy cover. Meadow borders NW bank, but trees are boundaries. Wider @ end of reach. Some silt present, mostly clear H2O

Location_Description: DS of Miller St xing, 0.1mi S of Norwich Rd
Habitat_Comment: CFR. Overgrown w/ green & brambles. Good flow, cool water. Nice riffley sections, undercuts underneath growth. Cobbly/sandy substrate, a little sitly but overall clear water. Narrower @ beginning of stretch, flows behind house, stream runs right up to backyard. Yard manicured up to stream edge. Crayfish & stonefly present. Slightly channelized on S side, next to field. Skipped 6m section in middle. Sample length is estimated.

Location_Description: off Turkey Hill Rd, US of xing @ private Rd to houses, 0.33mi W of Sylvester Rd
Habitat_Comment: Small stream, low flow, rocky substrate 25050% exposed. Shocked US of private rd xing, slightly channelized @ rd xing w/ grass on edges. Open arch bridge over stream. Good tree canopy. Rocky-sandy substrate. Slight erosion of banks, root structures present for cover. House #s 105, 119, 133, 147. CFR\

Location_Description: US of Williamsburg Rd xing just W of town line
Habitat_Comment: Stream barely flowing. All fish were in first 25 meters. Portions of the stream below ground. Most of stream full of silt, other sections flowing over bedrock. A couple of pools, evidence of past high flows (over banks). CFR

Location_Description: US of Cross Rd between Lower & Upper Wing Hill Rd, DAR SF. 0.3mi N of Wing Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Conditions very good for overwintering. Moderately deep pools, canopy 90% closed. 12.3C water temp. CFR

Location_Description: US Mountain Rd xing, Across from Dewey St
Habitat_Comment: <1% gradient, slow placid. Sand bottom with some mud. Moderate amount of siltation, mostly in bends, mostly slow and shallow. few pools.

Location_Description: US, along Williamsburg Rd, 0.4mi E of town line
Habitat_Comment: Hard sand bottom with scattered small & large moss covered rocks. Mostly lower gradient & shallow with a few pools & undercut banks. CFR

Location_Description: US of Adams Rd xing, 0.2mi E of Mountain St
Habitat_Comment: Substrate mostly large gravel and small rocks with large rock & boulders. Lots of runs, shallow and deep pools. Some deadfall overhanging branches. CFR

Location_Description: US of Adams Rd xing, 0.1mi W of Mountain Rd
Habitat_Comment: We were only able to shock 32 meters due to brush over stream becoming inpenatratible. Stream shallow, winding, with muddy banks. Stream bottom mostly sand with some muddy, silty areas. Area around stream is swampy. CFR

Location_Description: DS of Northwest Rd xing, @ Parmenter Rd
Habitat_Comment: Several of the EBTs were very pale and blotchy, pics were taken. US of road in new beaver pond. Stream small, very rocky and ledgey. One large pool and several small plunge pools. Entire stream bottom covered ina layer of fine silt with a blueish-green algae growing on it. CFR

Location_Description: US of Moosehorn Rd xing, just W of Rt 202
Habitat_Comment: Good flow, rocky substrate, ~50% exposed. Green moss on rocks. Shady area. Road runs along side, ~50m up from xing. Lots of small plunge pools. Good canopy cover once away from road. Small boulders, clear water. Shallow. CFR

Location_Description: US of Franklin St Ext xing, just N of Michael Sears Rd
Habitat_Comment: Small stream, shocked US of small decorative foot bridge. Low flow, 25% of channel filled, banks consist of shrubs & skunk cabbage. Gravel & sand substrate. Decent canopy w/ shade. Some bends in the stream, a few pools. Water a little dark in some areas. Frogs present. Only 3 fish caught after the 1st 20m.  Mostly shallow runs over rocks. CFR

waterbody: Peppers Mill Brook (UNT to Beaver Br)
Location_Description: US of Monson Turnpike Rd xing, just S of Rt 9
Habitat_Comment: Small foot bridge ~20m into reach. Moss covered rocks, moderate flow, rocky substrate. Muddy further US, silty water. Slightly overgrown @ first, then more overgrowth US. Stream borders backyard of residence. Owner siad used to be beaver activity @ upper section of reach, explains mud & silt. Lots of BND, some dead from shocking. Few undercut banks. Deeper pools further US. 50% exposed substrate. CFR

Location_Description: US of road to Quabbin Gate 8 xing (Packardville Rd Sect 2)
Habitat_Comment: Stream inside Quabbin. Good flow. Rocky & sandy, gravel substrate. Clear water. Moss growing on rocks. Some med sized boulders. Good tree cover-canopy. Lots of frogs. Road xing 3' culvert pipe. Very little undercut banks. Some plunge pools. Wider up top. 2-3 deeper pools, some shallow. Less flow up top-more substrate exposed. CFR

Location_Description: @ end of Holland Dr (cul de sac), N of Allen St
Habitat_Comment: Submerged vegetation, flows behind houses on cul de sac. Lawn manicured up to stream, silty, slighty overgrown on opposite bank. Overgrown US & DS of reach. Lots of TD, BND, large WS, 1 lg BT. Tried other US reaches - swampy. Sandy gravely bottom, some sm woody debris. Deep pools on bank opposite of houses. CFR

Location_Description: US of Batchelor Rd, insde of Mt Holyoke Range Park, US of trail xing
Habitat_Comment: Sampled US of trail xing. Low water conditions, mostly a trickle w/ small pools. Some pools deep. Undercut banks @ pools. Woody debris creating snags for EBT hiding. Overgrown further US. Overgrown & a trickle @ Batchelor Rd xing. Volts varied b/c of H2O levels. Trail off right side of parking lot. CFR

Location_Description: US of Logan Rd/Fryville Rd xing, just W of Rt 32
Habitat_Comment: Very ledgey, has a pool in middle of run that was too deep to shock.

Habitat_Comment: CFR

Location_Description: US of Conway Rd xing, 0.5mi E of Webber Rd

Location_Description: US of Thayer Rd xing, E of Fisk Rd
Habitat_Comment: Rocky mid gradient. Mostly shallow runs with shallow pools. Some moss on rocks, some underut banks and small deeper pools with undercut boulders. Sample area above rements of old mill pond. CFR

Location_Description: US of Root Rd xing, NE of Cutler Rd
Habitat_Comment: Small rock filled stream. Water is mostly flowing around & through moss covered rocks. A couple small shallow pools otherwise all shallow runs. Whole stream very silted in with fine sand and mud. After 70m multiflora rose make stream impassable. CFR

Location_Description: DS of West Rd xing, S of Wine Rd
Habitat_Comment: US of Road xing is old pond. Water color of iced tea. Brook runs down wooded ravie with fields on both sides. Stream a mix of shallow pools & falls/runs with a couple deep pools. Substrate a mix of small rocks/gravel and large rocks/boulders. CFR

Location_Description: DS of South Shelburne Rd xing, E of Albany Rd
Habitat_Comment: Mix of ledge and shale rocks. Very silted in. most rocks in stream have silt on them. Only shallow pools & runs. All flat sections have sand bars & sand mud bottoms. Road runs along stream. CFR

Location_Description: DS of Rt 112 xing, N of intersection w/ Rt 116
Habitat_Comment: Boulder and rock filled under hemlocks. 2 deeper pools US of Rd xing is swamp. CFR

waterbody: UNT to Upper Branch Clesson Brook
Location_Description: US of Hawley Rd xing, just E of Ford Rd
Habitat_Comment: Very small, water trickles over small rocks, with some small pools. Most large rocks have moss. Lots of fine grey sand. CFR

Location_Description: US of Mountain Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Substrate a mix of large small rocks and sand gravel. Lots of shallow pools, plunge pools, riffles, & runs. 2 large deep pools. Well shaded by hemlocks. 1 large northern spring salamander. CFR

Location_Description: US of East Oxbow Rd xing, N of Hawk Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Small and rocky with little flow. Water flows around moss coverec rocks. Mix of small shallow pools and small runs. Lots of fresh dead leaves in brook. A few larger shallow pools and a couple larger deep pools. Pool substrate mix of sand/silt and small rocks. CFR

Location_Description: DS of Dell Rd across from J W Royer Rd
Habitat_Comment: US of road xing is a large beaver pond. Mix of small shallow pools and runs/falls. 1 large deeper and 1 large shallow pool in 100m. Pool substrate mostly sand with scattered rocks, otherwise small to mid-sized rocks. CFR

Location_Description: US Stone Hill Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: <2% gradient, sm cobble, gravel sand. Good cover with several small pool associated with LND & plunge pool. 50% canopy closure, no undercut bank, no deep pools. CFR

Location_Description: off Kingsley Hill Rd, DS (east) of powerline cut
Habitat_Comment: Very steep and rocky. Lots of falls, steep runs and plunge pools. One large deep pool. Several larger shallow pools. Mostly rock, bouldder, cobble bottom with some sand. CFR

Location_Description: US of East Rd xing, N of Bell Rd
Habitat_Comment: Small, low flow. Series of small shallow pools connected by trickles though rocks. Most pools with shale rock bottom with some silt-organic matter mostly. Former thermograph stream. CFR

Location_Description: off Creamery Br Rd, SE of Norton Hill Rd 0.25mi
Habitat_Comment: Bed mostly small rocks, sand, gravel. Scattered large rocks. Mix of rocky runs, small rocky pools and sandy bottom pools. Most of the banks show erosion, few piles of debris but most is out of water. Streambed 80% dry. No photos. CFR

Location_Description: US of East Buckland (Barnes Rd) Rd xing, just N of townline
Habitat_Comment: Very small hemlock shaded. Mostly mud, silt, sand bottom with medium sized rocks. Most larger rocks covered in moss. Lots of dead fall over and in stream. No photos. Former thermograph stream. CFR

Location_Description: US of Charlemont Rd xing, E of townline
Habitat_Comment: Steep, high velocity. Rocky most large mix of cobble to boulders. Some sand in pools. Stream a mix of runs, falls, small and large shallow & deep pools. Plunge pools. Current thermograph site. CFR

Location_Description: off Dodge Rd ~5-600m US of S. River Rd
Habitat_Comment: Very rocky mix of medium and large rocks w/ some boulders. Most of brook is mix of shallow runs, steep runs/ralls and small plunge pools. A few larger shallow pools and a couple small deep pools app.10m of bedrock side in sample site. Former thermograph site. CFR

Location_Description: DS of Briggsville Dam, 0.15mi DS of Cross St
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Vouchered LNS & a few small CS to confirm the ID on small CS. Water is fairly high. We missed a bunch of fish. "CS" vouchered were ID's as Fallfish, all CS have been changed to Fallfish.

Location_Description: US Old County Rd (N. County Rd) xing, just W of Blackstone Rd
Habitat_Comment: Meandering with lots of pools and a few shallow sand/gravel runs. Bottom mostly sand/gravel with a few rocky areas. Lots of sediment depositino in areas. Lot of dead falls in and over stream, debris jams. Signs of very recent (>2weeks) major flood. CFR

Location_Description: River Rd xing US, W of Whitcomb Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Sm boulder, lg cobbles, sand/gravel, shallow pool/riffle sequences. 60% canopy cover w/ fields on both sides, some woody debris/rootwad structures. CFR

Location_Description: US River Rd xing above last house, 0.4 mi NE of Whitcomb Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: High gradient >8%, bedrock boulder, <20% sand gravel, 40-50% canopy cover, plunge pool-glide-riffle associated with boulder containment. Former thermograph site. CFR

Location_Description: US Tannery Rd xing, 0.78mi W of Black Brook Rd, 2nd xing
Habitat_Comment: Stream bottom all cobble. One large deep pool & a couple small shallow pools with some sand. 90+% of stream shallow riffles. CFR

Location_Description: US of Savoy Rd xing, S of S. County Rd 0.25mi
Habitat_Comment: Lg boulder, several small pools, plunge pools. Bedrock containment in middle of reach. Small cobble, sand, gravel. 50-60% canopy cover, not much LWD. CFR

Location_Description: off Rt 2 first pull off  E of S. County Rd
Habitat_Comment: Rocky shale. Small pools, falls. Sand/shale/gravel bottom, lots of trash. Former thermograph stream. CFR

Location_Description: DS of Main Rd xing, just W of North Rd
Habitat_Comment: Shallow with rock and mud/sand bottom. Few shallow pools. Some boulders large rocks. Lots of frogs. US of rd is old beaver pond. CFR

Location_Description: Rt 101 - State park
Habitat_Comment:
1st run 900 sec
2nd run 1321 sec
2-3LMB sighted but not netted. Water very tannic. Lots of YOY 1+ Yellow perch schools.

Location_Description: Below Rocky P - Leominster State Forest
Habitat_Comment: 1 wild EBT (134) & 1 CP (131). Has all makeups of excellent wild EBT stream. Past beaver issues at pond led to stream drying out in summer months. No voucher. CFR

Location_Description: US of blown out culvert up to next culvert
Habitat_Comment: interesting "albino" stonefly, lots of frogs, some crayfish; not a lot of fish in riffles; most EBT in pools & undercuts; sinuosity higher & more developed thalweg here; undercuts nice, deep & treed. Higher conductivity a problem? Upper culvert creating large deep pool DS b/c of restricted flow, has deep, fine sand substrate; M. Brideau said this stream is Not stocked w/ trout. CFR

Location_Description: Cricket Hill Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: CFR

Location_Description: Chestnut Hill Rd, just W of Holtshire Rd
Habitat_Comment: Above culvert. CFR

Location_Description: Water treatment plant off Holtshire Rd
Habitat_Comment: Spottail shiner (?) put in formalin with Lake Mattawa Rd container, voucher found to be a GS not SS

Location_Description: off Kempfield Rd, 0.4mi S of Wendell Depot Rd
Habitat_Comment: Low conductivity. CFR

Location_Description: off Roy's Rd - off Rt 7 0.15mi.
Habitat_Comment: Unnamed road off Roy's Rd. Stream is wide and shallow with very few pools. Forested canopy. Substrate composed cobble, gravel with some boulder and sand. CFR

Location_Description: Downstream of Cross Rd culvert, just W of Mt. View Rd
Habitat_Comment: Cobble, gravel, sand, boulder substrate. Partially forested. Shallow & wide stream channel. Lack of good trout habitat. CFR

Location_Description: Scott Rd xing, downstream of culvert, 0.1mi NW of N. Main St
Habitat_Comment: Heavy silt with sand/ gravel & cobble substrate. Above confluence with Town Brook. Below culvert on Scott Rd. CFR

Location_Description: DCR -off of Hopper Brook Trail
Habitat_Comment: 25' below bridge/ began top edge open field. Off of Hop Brook Trail. CFR

Location_Description: Broughs Rd upstream of top culvert at Log landing pulloff.
Habitat_Comment:
Substrate dominated by boulder, cobble & gravel. Sand also present in acres. Clear stream with hemlock, beech, maple overstory. CFR. Bottom of site 42.52230
73.18423.

Location_Description: Immediately upstream of Briggsville Damn (River right), off Rt 8
Habitat_Comment: Approx 80% barge shocking & 20% backpack (2 packs used). Small gravel & silt dominated substrate. Split channel. Approx. 80% pool & 20% riffle. CFR.

Location_Description: Immediately upstream of Briggsville Dam (River Left)
Habitat_Comment: Approx. 70% barge shocking & 30% backpack (2 packs). Gravel, sand, cobble dominant substrate. Split channel. Approx 70% pool & 30% riffle. CFR

Location_Description: Control site ~ 100m upstream of Cross Rd bridge
Habitat_Comment: 3 backpack shockers used. Boulder, cobble & sand dominant substrate. Step pool habitat - apparent rip rap along stream bank on river left. Control site above Cross Rd bridge. CFR

Location_Description: Downstream of bridge of Cross Rd
Habitat_Comment: Stream contains a good quantity of large woody from hemlock trees. Stream contains dark silt from beaver pond. Substrate dominated by cobble, gravel, sand & some boulders. Forested overhead canopy. CFR

Location_Description: East St upstream behind home
Habitat_Comment: Poor catch per effort for small trout & slimy sculpin. Dominant substrate gravel & sand with some cobble. Site downstream of beaver impoundment. Portion of stream is forested approx 20%. CFR

Location_Description: Harvey Colkin Rd
Habitat_Comment: Gravel, cobble, boulder substrate. Beech hemlock overstory. Nice pools formed by LND. Should check in a few years to see if brown brown trout. CFR

Location_Description: Below 1st bridge at camp
Habitat_Comment: Gravel sand substrate silt overlay on top of gravel/sand. Stream section located in a wetland. Some small woody debris present. Bottom of site 42.47765 73.28762. CFR

Location_Description: off Burt Hill Rd @ end of Covell Rd
Habitat_Comment: upstream of personal bridge. Lower section gravel, cobble, & boulder. CFR. *Home owner wishes to be contacted for all activities on the stream*

Location_Description: off of a dirt road off of Rt 8 (Thorp Rd) 1/3mi W of Rt 8
Habitat_Comment: Great fish habitat, a large number of pools either under undercut boulders, banks with exposed tree roots & a good quantity of LWD. Canopy cover hemlock, yellow birch, beech. Boulder, cobble, gravel & sand substrate. Little silt present. CFR

Location_Description: Russell Rd upstream of culvert
Habitat_Comment: Heavily channelized stream - over 100yrs maybe? Worked upstream of Russell Rd crossing. Substrate grave/boulder. Channelized- very tannic, color root beer float. Not channelized downstream of bridge/culvert. CFR

Location_Description: Johnson Hill Rd US of Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Site located upstream of bridge crossing of old road no longer used. Stream dominated by cobble, gravel, boulder. CFR.

Location_Description: Along Maynard Rd, 500' W of E. River Rd
Habitat_Comment: Cobble, boulder, gravel, sand silt present. LND present. At pulloff off of Maynard Rd at LWD jam. CFR

Location_Description: Strong Rd, upstream of
Habitat_Comment: Tanic stream dominated by boulders and gravel. Survey above old bridge of Strong Rd and above unnamed tributary. Red eft, 2 line salamanders & juv sal of another species. CFR

Location_Description: US of South St xing, North of town line
Habitat_Comment: Culverted road xing - pipe ~8' in diameter. Started 20m above culvert. Many schools of YOY CS. Missed many small fish: CS, YB, BND, LND. Lots of crayfish. Large boulders, slippery, sediment in pools. Large flat deep pools throughout reach. Tannic H2O. Cascades present, flow decent, some small stagnant pools. Good tree cover, shady. Woody debris along banks. Minor bank erosion. Wide stream. Used 2 backpacks, width varies. Humminbird nest above stream.

Location_Description: upstream of Windsor Bush Rd (Windsor Jambs Rd)
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpack shockers were used. Upstream of bridge on Windsor Bush rd above Windsor Jambs. Stream dominated by gravel, sand with cobble & large boulders present. Black spot present on some fish. CFR

Location_Description: Clesson Rd, 0.3mi W of Shepherd Rd
Habitat_Comment: Substrate dominated by cobble followed by boulder & gravel. Site off of Clesson Bk Rd. CFR. Bottom of site 42.58067, 72.82183

Location_Description: Nilman Rd 2/3mi S of E. Buckland Rd
Habitat_Comment: Shocked culvert pool ~ 20 fish w/in pool. Dominated by sand & gravel substrate. Started below & worked up to the Nilman Rd culvert. CFR

Location_Description: South River Rd xing US
Habitat_Comment: At base of stream below shocking site (downstream) a slide occuring on river right & a NRCS & prop project on river left. Bottom of side is above land slide. Boulder, cobble dominated by boulder, some gravel present. Upper section of site is a ledge pool. Hemlock, birch, red maple. CFR

Location_Description: off 8A, past Hallockville Pond, 0.5mi N of Hallockville Rd
Habitat_Comment: Ledge stream with boulders, sand & gravel. Dominant substrate is boulder. Yellow birch, american beech dominate overstory. CFR

Location_Description: off of Zoar Rd, upstream of 4 culverts (together)
Habitat_Comment: Boulder, cobble, gravel stream. Large boulders present with deep pools. Pine, beech, yellow birch canopy. Nice amount of LWD. Upstream of private rd (grassy) with 4 culverts and shed. CFR

Location_Description: Upstream of Davis Mine Rd
Habitat_Comment: Dominant substrate sand, boulder. Outflow of beaver impoundment. Pine, yellow birch, hemlock, balsam fir forest. CFR

Location_Description: Upstream of Monroe Rd culvert & confluence of small pond
Habitat_Comment: Cobble, boulder, gravel substrate. Majority of the site is forested, the bottom portion of the site is in a wetland. CFR

Location_Description: Monroe Rd upstream of culvert
Habitat_Comment: Cobble, gravel, & boulder. Hemlock/birch overstory. Fast flow & low conductivity. Bottom of site 42.68845, 72.99964. CFR

Location_Description: Tilda->Main->North St, US of Main Rd xing, just W of North St
Habitat_Comment:
Downstream of culvert ->beaver damn below culvert recently taken out. Site is located below previously impounded area. Dominant substrate boulder, sand, cobble. Adjacent area has been previously logged. Canopy cover still intact. Heavy silt from beaver. Bottom of site 42.72359
72.97475. CFR

Location_Description: Rt 2 pulloff, S of South County Rd 0.6mi
Habitat_Comment: Stop at pulloff along Rt 2. Tires & barrels along stream bank & in stream. Large quantity of large woody debris in stream. Overstory of hemlock. Step pool riffle system dominated by cobble, gravel & boulders. CFR

Location_Description: Above Cornell Rd
Habitat_Comment: Moss covered boulders. Abundant caddis. Some woody debris. Salamander eggs. Sample ID 2270 done below Cornell Rd, was a selective pick-up for EBT.

Location_Description: below footbridge below Stoney Brook Road, WPS
Habitat_Comment: met with Dana Condit Brewster Herring Warden. Cobble bottom, water willow overgrows stream

Location_Description: Below driveway east of drift road, 0.7mi S of Charlotte White Rd
Habitat_Comment: Large sand deposits on inside of bends, must less water in channel than in 1990. large boulders interspersed with gravel and sand. CFR

Location_Description: Driveway off Drift Rd

Location_Description: DS of dam behind HRD Press on Pelham Rd

Some deep pools present, some scours in bedrock. Boulders & gravel substrate otherwise. Old mill is now HRD Press. Dam is open, ahs been for a while. Dam is 1st one going US on Amethyst Br. Amethyst flows into Fort R, which has no dams.

Location_Description: US of Meetinghouse Rd xing

Several downed trees over brook w/ some sm woody debris present. Boulder, cobble, gravel substrate. Looks like good EBT habitat, but only a few caught. In between 2 dams on pond, pop.s may be isolated. Trout good shape, deep pools present.

Location_Description: US of Meetinghouse Rd
