Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rat tail. Surveyed pools only. Brook filled w/ fine sediment. 5 wild EBTs, no yoy fish or young age groups.

Location_Description: Below Boston Rd crossing, along Buttonwood Ave
Habitat_Comment: Backpack. Covered 100% of area surveyed. Warm & coldwater species found. Wild EBTs 17 & wild BTs 4. crayfish present. Multiple long drop down pools. Excellent canopy. CFR

Location_Description: Buttonwood Ave (along)
Habitat_Comment: Backpack. Wild BT & wild EBTs. Crayfish present. Excellent stream w/ multiple pools, riffles & canopy. CFR

Location_Description: off Mendon Rd (East of Rt 146 crossing) between Johnson Rd & Rt 146
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rat tail. Good canopy w/ multiple pools. 2 wild EBTs 135 & 157, released. CFR

Location_Description: Campground access, US of Lakeshore Dr
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rat tail. Covered 100% of stream sampled. Multiple age classes of EBTs (wild) #120, size 38mm-200. YB & WS caught on pond side of culvert. CFR

Location_Description: Bond Rd xing downstream, just S of N. Main St
Habitat_Comment: BT found at base of culvert to Bond Rd

Location_Description: off Radiker Rd across from Chucklebrook Farm
Habitat_Comment: Approx 10m upstream of culvert of Radiker Rd. Downstream is a cow pasture. Unusual fish community. Very large native reproducing brook trout. Evidence of black spot on minnow species. Huge bite out of the back of a 10 inche brook trout. Top of site reforested - old apple orchard

Location_Description: Access off of Gilead Rd- downstream of dam
Habitat_Comment: Site located immediately below Hall Brook dam. Downstream site. Nice healthy brook trout. Overcast day. Substrate mainly comprised of pebble, boulder, bedrock, cobble, & sand. Numerous trout. Mortality 3 fish.

Location_Description: Upstream of Hall Bk Dam & below Gilead Rd culvert. Above Dam
Habitat_Comment: Approx 3 meters below Gilead St. site immediately upstream of Hall Brook dam. Beaver lodge (small) present within site. Beaver was accidently shocked. Heavier fines than downstream of the dam. Wider BVW. Overcast day.

Location_Description: Reference site for Hall bk dam removal - enter through housing development
Habitat_Comment: Substrate comprised of cobble, pebble, sand, boulder & silt. No presence of bedrock. Brook trout only dominated stream. Some debris such as old cars off in the riparian areas. Brook trout are more cigar like in shape. 2 mortalities.

Location_Description: US of Lenox Rd xing, off Turkey Trott Rd - parked US of Lenox Rd
Habitat_Comment: Stream seems a little unstable in the channel immediately above the Lenox Rd culvert. Bottom of site was upstream of the braided channel section the flows through a skunk cabbage & fern wetland. Substrate contains mainly sand, pebble, gravel, & cobble with the occasional exposed clay & boulders

Location_Description: off of rd headed towards Quarry - off of Rt 189.
Habitat_Comment: Fish kill occurred recently before sample took place. Rockwood Farm. Most fish looked freshly dead. Only species present are brook trout & blacknose dace. Talked with owner of farm currently being investigated by DEP for silver sheen mold growth beggotia. All fish dead but one.

Location_Description: East of (near) Brier Hill Rd, DS of Creamery Rd
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed behind the new location of Ashfield old town hall. Some vegetation along river right has been cleared. Nice LWD pool complex & large boulder pool where the LNS was found. Substrate is comprised of sand, gravel, pebble, cobble, silt, boulder. CFR

Location_Description: S of Emmet Rd & next to Rt 116
Habitat_Comment: Stream is rather silty, Numerous slimy sculpin, difficult to see in silty water and were hard to catch. Overall two nice large pools and some LWD. Substrate comprised of sand, gravel, pebble, silt, cobbl e& boulder. Partly cloudy day. CFR

Location_Description: Off of 41 parked at Tavern, US of Rt 41 xing
Habitat_Comment: Lower portion of stream near Rt 41. Road crossing is dry; however if you walk upstream, water is flowing very well. Excellent brook trout stream, cold water. Nice pools that are deep & some that have LWD. Substrate composed of boulder, cobble, silt & gravel. Warm & sunny. CFR

Location_Description: Bush Cemetary Rd, US of Lower Rd
Habitat_Comment: Near clear cut area of pine plantation. Some siltation in stream. Boulder, cobble, gravel, & sand with some exposed bedrock. Stream is small, surveyed stream before confluence with Windsor Jamb Brook. Overcast day. CFR

Location_Description: US Smith Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Upstream of Smith Rd stream crossing. Substrate is composed mainly of sand, gravel, pebble, and sand. Some scattered boulder. Overcast day and dark substrate and tanic water. Numerous crayfish. CFR

Location_Description: Beartown Mountain Rd, US of confl. w/ UNT to L. Garfield
Habitat_Comment: Stream flow is up from previous days rain. Nice undercut banks with deep pools. Site started upstream of a small bridge behind a house upstream from the confluence with the outflow of Lake Garfield and ended at a natural bank slide. CFR

Location_Description: From 116, take BushRd to Windango.
Habitat_Comment: Rocky, cobble, not real productive. Ledgy bottom, not deep. Clear water. CFR

Location_Description: Along Center Rd, Rt 116 to Center St, 1.67mi N of Rt 116
Habitat_Comment: Very tanic, fast moving riffles (just had storms this past week). Hard to see fish, missed some ~25%. Lots of giant boulders in stream.

Location_Description: off Rt 23
Habitat_Comment: Large old rusty metal dumpsite off of Rt 23 with lots of metal, tires & windshields. Due to the increase of trash, we had to include in the area of evaluation a section of Tannery Bmk that has a small UNT stream that enters in the middle of the site. Substrate is composed of gravel, sand, cobble & boulders. CFR

Location_Description: off North Blandford Rd, DS of small trib. ~0.5mi W of Blair Rd
Habitat_Comment: Stream has really great deep pools, mix of species from outflow of Long Pond & a coldwater UNT enters near the top of the site. The coldwater tri is 17.2C while the stream temperature above the confluence of the trib is 20.6C. Great Habitat! Substrate is composed of sand, cobble, boulder & gravel. CFR

Location_Description: DS of Old Windsor Rd xing, W of town line
Habitat_Comment: Lots of trash in stream. Low catch rate at approx 25% of stream caused by the overhanging alders. Stream is tanic. Substrate composed of gravel, sand, pebble, cobble & boulders. Partly cloudy day. Top of site approx 65 meters below Old Windsor Rd culvert near large boulders.

Location_Description: County Rd upstream of bridge xing
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Stream flow & velocity up from early morning storm. Presence of all ages of brown trout. Substrate is composed of sand, boulder, pebble, gravel, & cobble. Overcast day. Some suspended sediments. CFR

Location_Description: US Woodland Rd - upstream of road crossing
Habitat_Comment: The B was at the bottom of Sample A. Step pool stream for approx. 50m then became cascades. Amazingly the fish were found throughout the sample reach. Substrate is unstable & is composed of boulders & gravel, with some cobble & pebbles. CFR

Location_Description: Roaring Brook Rd upstream of road crossing & stream fork
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks. Worst mosquitos ever. Stream forks part way upstream of Roaring Brook Rd bridge. Beautiful stream. Substrate mainly composed of boulder, cobble, gravel, & some sand. At the top of the site, substrate is composed mainly of bedrock. CFR

Location_Description: Off of Rt 20, SW of housing complex on opposite side of road
Habitat_Comment: Stream is very shallow, avg wet depth is 6 inches. High pH with 8.03. Substrate is mainly composed of gravel, sand, pebble, cobble, & boulders, with some fine. Some garbage present in stream. Site was located at mowed area just downstream of house. Partly cloudy

Location_Description: Upstream of Rt 43 along side of Leab Family Farm
Habitat_Comment: Stream is composed of a number of smaller substrate types; pebble, gravel, sand with cobble & boulder. Very clear stream. It would be interesting to survery stream in the forested portion of the stream. Difficulty catchign slimy sculpin, missed around 5.

Location_Description: Upstream of Rt 41
Habitat_Comment: Stream is flowing approx 4 times the quantity of flow for this time of year. POOR SURVEY DUE TO HIGH FLOWS. Should redo survey to increase catch per unit effort. I would expect in lower flow conditions that the brook trout population would be higher

Location_Description: off Woodcock Rd, DS of Road xing
Habitat_Comment: Flow is up but not enough to prevent shoking. Amazing EBT stream! Good reference reach for EBT. Some older fish are very very fat. One pool in stream was 4ft deep caused by boulders & LWD. Site ended at a ledge pool. Substrate is ledge, gravel, pebble, cobble & some boulders. Finer substrate is very loose. Artesian well bubbling up in stream bed. H2O very cold. Pipe in stream is connected to spring house near start of site. Home owner at top most stream xing doesnt want us to survey on her property.

Location_Description: Upstream of Charlemont Rd culvert
Habitat_Comment: Solid EBT stream. Missed approx 5 fish, mostly juveniles. Upper portion of site, the stream has shifted channels. The bottom of site was approx 30 m upstream of the Charlemont Rd culvert at a large boulder slab pool. Substrate is composed of boulder, cobble, sand & gravel.

Location_Description: ~20m downstream of old logging rd culvert, which is approx 50m downstream of confluence, site accessed off Charlemont Rd
Habitat_Comment: Stream is rather small despite site downstream of confluence. Old logging rd can be used to access site (not on topo map). Culvert pool which is not in the site held approx 8 EBT that were approx 5" in TL. Substrate is composed of boulder, sand, cobble & gravel.

Location_Description: Cheshire Rd, DS of trib road xing. ~1/3 mi E of Cheshire town line
Habitat_Comment: Recent scouring evidence along side the bank sugest the stream has experienced a flash flood in the magnitude of an approx 10 yr event. Substrate is difficult to see, tan brown color. Sustrate is composed of boulder slabs, bedrock, boulder, cobble, gravel, sand. Missed 3 trout. 2 in 5" range & 1 juv. Deep pools. Partly cloudy day. *Original coordinates incorrect. Changed  to Dana's description of location, near snowmobile bridge.*

Location_Description: (Along) off of East Hoosic St, E of East Rd 1/3mi.
Habitat_Comment: Had a great deal of difficulty capturing juvenile EBT. Lost approx 5 or 6. Stream was surveyed along side road. Numerous deep deep pools. Some 3.5 feet deep. Substrate is composed of bedrock, boulder, cobble, sand, gravel. Stream has a cement well in site for approx 15m. Stream would be stunninig if not in a semi-urban setting.

Location_Description: Off Middlefield Rd approx 75m upstream
Habitat_Comment: Had to cut survey short due to too many fish! A few nice pools caused by LWD & undercut banks. Substrate composed of boulder, pebble, cobble, gravel & sand. The appearance of the stream is deceiving as to quantity of fish.

Location_Description: New Lenox Rd
Habitat_Comment: Bottom of site began approx 100m upstream of 1st culvert near log jam & approx 10m below next culvert. Bottom of site had fewer fish than the upper part of the site. Road is very near the stream. Trash dump site near 1st culvert. Substrate is composed of sand, bedrock, boulder, cobble, gravel, & pebble

Location_Description: Rt 23, ~1mi SE of Rt 7 intersection
Habitat_Comment: It is difficult to find access without overhanging shrubs (multi-flora rose) to shock. Ended up surveying stream through an overgrown field w/ golden rod. Stream is shallow with undercut banks. No overhanging trees. Substrate is mostly sand & gravel w/ occasional cobble.

Location_Description: Zoar/Rowe Rd 3m upstream of culvert
Habitat_Comment: Attempted to survey stream near the Tunnel Rd/Brittingham Rd xing; however the flow was minimla. Ended up conducting the survey 3m upstream of Zoar bridge. Substrate is dark & is composed of cobble, gravel, pebble, sand & boulders.

Location_Description: Approx 20m upstream of 1st road crossing of Quarry Rd
Habitat_Comment: Due to time constraints we surveyed near the road. A portion of the stream on river right approx 15m contained rip rap & created a large pool. Some road gravel has washed in the stream. Overall lots of nice pools; however fish are few. Warm temp for water.

Location_Description: Downstream of Farnum Rd crossing
Habitat_Comment: Approx 25m downstream of Farnum Rd crossing culvert. Partly cloudy day. Stream is small with substrate composed of sand, gravel, pebble, cobble & boulders. There is a pasture on river left; however survey area has a forested riparian area. Surprising abudance of EBT.

Location_Description: Phelon Rd - approx 20m upstream of road crossing
Habitat_Comment: Clear day. Pools are not very deep. Stream channel appears to be incised a bit. Possible historical channel alteration from Phelon Rd. Water is clear with very little silt & no turbidity. Substrate is composed of gravel, cobble, pebble, sand & a few boulders.

Location_Description: DS of Benton Hill Rd, below old dam structure
Habitat_Comment: Stream is nice but has some legacy impact issues (eg. Old dam structure); also DS side of culvert perched. Sample requested by Westfield Wild & Scenic to determine coldwater listing status; riparian area forester.

waterbody: May Brook (1; UNT to Windsor Reservoir)
Location_Description: Between culvert & dam - Back Dalton Rd
Habitat_Comment: Site is located between Back Dalton Rd culvert & dam. They are currently working on the culvert but have not replaced it yet with the box culvert. Stream is clear with low turbidity & very little silt. Several nice deep boulder pools. Fat fish! Substrate is composed of boulder, gravel, pebble, sand & cobble. Dam spans entire width of stream. EBT are in full spawning colors.

waterbody: May Brook (1; UNT to Windsor Reservoir)
Location_Description: Downstream culvert off of Back Dalton Rd (Falls Rd)
Habitat_Comment: Approx 57m downstream of culvert. Stream bank full. Seems much much wider than upstream of culvert. Probably would have been better if conducted the survey the previous week. Too many leaves in stream. It looks like a leaf drop occurred within the week between surveys. Stream gradient does not appear as steep. Pools are very shallow. Partly cloudy overhad.

Location_Description: Immediately downstream of Briggsville Dam
Habitat_Comment: Difficult to capture small minnow species, they would sink in between the rocks. Sunny, partly cloudy day. Missed at least 2 trout & 2 longnose suckers. Stream has changed surface substrate in pool below dam. 3 backpacks used

Location_Description: Control Site ~100m upstream of Cross Rd Bridge
Habitat_Comment: Stream is very slippery covered in a silty brown. Very exposed stream. Riprap present & it has been previously channelized from road. Stream is a series of step pools. Substrate is composed of boulder, cobble, sand & gravel. 3 backpacks used. Slippery! ~20% of LND were lost due to overturned bucket.

Location_Description: Above Dam, Immediately upstream of Briggsville Dam (River Left)
Habitat_Comment: Both Barge & Backpack used during survey. LFs were not seperated per method type, therefore are combined under same Sample ID. Approx 80% barge shocking & 20% backpack. 1 backpack used. Substrate dominated by gravel & silt. Some cobble & boulders at top of site. Split channel - only river right channel. Approx 80% pool & 20% riffle

Location_Description: Immediately Upstream of Briggsville Dam (River Right, near Carson Ave)
Habitat_Comment: *Both Barge & Backpack methods used. LFs were NOT seperated per method type, LFs are combine from both methods & are under same Sample ID. Approx. 70% barge shocking & 30% backpack (1 pack). Gravel, sand, & cobble are dominant substrate. River left of split channel. Impounded section is silty. Approx 70% pool & 30% riffle

Location_Description: Parked off of Steven's Glen Rd - upstream of confluence to UNT flowing out of Fairfield Pond
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed in posted area. Stream needs to be surveyed w/ 2 backpack shockers. Surveyed above  the confluence with the UNT flowing out of Fairfield Pond. Stream is very silty with some exposed muck. Substrate is composed of silt, sand, gravel, some cobble & boulder. Nice LWD in system.

Location_Description: Off of Rt 23 downstream of confluence
Habitat_Comment: Not many fish! Vouchered a few. Extraordinary habitat at the downstream end. Stream has changed course & created a new main channel. Probably within the past few years. New channel created from downed trees. Very, very deep pools from overturned trees. However, not inhabited by fish. Substrate is composed of sand, gravel, cobble & boulder

Location_Description: off Rt 63, east of Rt 63
Habitat_Comment: CFR

Location_Description: East Mountain Rd -across from Papermills Rd
Habitat_Comment: Muddy bottom, low water. CFR

Location_Description: Rt 202 Inside gate 15 Quabbin, US of confluence w/ Quabbin
Habitat_Comment: Nice brook - thought more fish. CFR

Location_Description: along Cushman Rd upstream of Atkins Res. 0.1mi W of Cross Rd
Habitat_Comment: CFR

Location_Description: Amherst Rd - US of east side of Hawley Reservoir
Habitat_Comment: CFR

Location_Description: Along Cary Dr off Foundary Acres
Habitat_Comment: Classic Brk trout stream. CFR

Location_Description: Along Heath Rd, West of road xing ~700ft
Habitat_Comment: CFR

waterbody: UNT to Hop Brook (1; Baby Carriage Brook)
Location_Description: US of Bay Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Shocked ~20m US of Bay Rd xing where stream widens. Is ~1ft wide & small just above rd xing. Winding stream along residence's backyard. Lawn mowed to stream edge L bank (facing US). Flow decent w/ bend pools & some sm riffles. Partially shaded. Sm foot bridge over brook in backyard. Some silt in bend pools. Too overgrown to continue further US. CFR

Location_Description: US of Pratt Corner Rd
Habitat_Comment: District stocks brook DS of rd xing but not US. Missed some dace & sm EBT. Cool, clear water w/ good flow. Mix of riffle, run & deep pools. Some pools ~4' deep. Some silt in pools. Boulder, cobble substrate. Woody debris present. Lg boulders & ledge line sections. Robert Frost Trail crosses brook ~2/3 up sample reach. Juv BT found. Shaded canopy, gives good cover. CFR

Location_Description: Warren Wright Rd - pumping station rd, across from bike path
Habitat_Comment: Abundant EBT. Cobble substrate, riffles present w/ bend pools. Good flow, exposed roots along bank, some undercutting. Riparian cover up from culvert xing @ rd to town well. Some woody debris. Cold water. Shocked about 50m US of culvert. CFR

Location_Description: xing on Depot Rd upstream
Habitat_Comment: CFR

Location_Description: between North Main St & Winter St
Habitat_Comment: Shallow, narrow. Right off someone's lawn, but nice fish. CFR

Location_Description: Bay Rd - Muddy Brk Farm
Habitat_Comment: Sandy, clay bottom

Location_Description: Anderson Rd downstream
Habitat_Comment: Crayfish, frogs. Cow across the street on upstsream side

Location_Description: off rd leading from Gate 21 in Quabbin Res, @ Underhill Rd xing where meets w/ Brown Rd
Habitat_Comment: CFR

Location_Description: January Hills Rd - below Atkins Reservoir
Habitat_Comment: Muddy-silty bottom. CFR

Location_Description: along Colrain Brook Rd, DS of road xing
Habitat_Comment: Short stretch - all brookies. CFR

Location_Description: Roger Babii Rd, off South St - pumping station
Habitat_Comment: Open, swampy, muddy but cold water. Only decent water we could find on brk, only could do a short stretch.

Location_Description: Wagner Wood off Southeast St
Habitat_Comment: Brk runs along farm field behind Wagner Wood Co. Sand, soft substrate w/ gravel.. Silty in pools. Deep bend pools. Woody debris present. Missed some fish b/c of debri. Wide diversity. AS found. Runoff from fields. Motor trails cross brook, 2nd crossing is where we sampled.. Cut banks. Winding stretch. Shaded for most part. Sampled US of Heatherstone Br confluence. CFR

Location_Description: Academy Hill Rd - upstream. W of Rt 116
Habitat_Comment: Channelized - upstream of South River below Academy Hill bridge. CFR

Location_Description: Along East Alford Rd, downstream of Bridge
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: Division St upstream of rd.
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Juv BT found!

Location_Description: Royalston Rd, upstream of Millers confluence
Habitat_Comment: First stream encountered. Stream flows under Royalston Rd into Millers. Surveyed @ 100 yards upstream of Millers River. CFR

Location_Description: Directly upstream of Millers R
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed directly upstream of where it pours into Millers R. CFR

Location_Description: Royalston Rd WMA lot across second brook, below falls
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed downstream of falls (snowmobile bridge)

Location_Description: 2nd stretch, end of 100m above Robbins Dam (SID 2269)
Habitat_Comment: Selective pickup survey, only larger fish looking for tag (EBT). One fish had a lower caudal fin clipped. Surveyed at end of the previous sample (SID 2269). No backpack info recorded, sample was at least 100m & 20+min (1200s). See SID 2269 for habitat asses sheet & comments.

Location_Description: Behind Pembroke Woods development (condos)
Habitat_Comment: Hemlock grove. Silt over sand bottom. Ave depth 3". Lot of woody debris. Walked down from parking lot. www.alexanpembrokewoods.com

Location_Description: Clay Street US (N)
Habitat_Comment: Crayfish common. Effort 12m 49 seconds. Lot of silt, beds of starwort. Heavy flow from previous days rainstorm. Mostly sand & muck buttom. Resample of area done in 1990.

Location_Description: end of Miramar Dr
Habitat_Comment: Sand & gravel in sections. Heavy deposits of sediment. Some pools with silt. ATV trails. Jewel weed.

Location_Description: Below Water St (west)
Habitat_Comment: WP 90-91. Trail sign next to stream.

Location_Description: behind Pembroke Hospital, NE of Hemlock Dr
Habitat_Comment: Red maple & white pine. Sand bottom with some gravel. Mud banks with undercuts. More open than Huldah Brook. AE seen but not captures. Pickerel frog observed

Location_Description: Above Berkley St xing
Habitat_Comment: old trout farm with wooden raceways. Tidal. Short section of sand & gravel then deeper muck bottomed upper area, couldnt progress further upstream

Location_Description: Below Wallace Street xing off Elm St
Habitat_Comment: newer subdivision surrounds. CFR

Location_Description: from Rt 1 Executive Suite Parking lot, US of Rt 1A xing
Habitat_Comment: Muck/mud. Overhanging tussocks. Run/glide/pool. Only surveyed 1/2 stream on 9/19. Survey completed over 2 days (9/19 & 9/20).

Location_Description: Shattuck Rd to house #45. DEP station HA01.
Habitat_Comment: Park @ gate across st. walk ~200m to stream/culvert.Sample from 100m below bridge to bridge.

Location_Description: US of Pine St xing
Habitat_Comment: Sand bottom. Most trout taken in one pool about 2' deep. Thermograph station in this reach.

Location_Description: Below Pine St (DS of xing)
Habitat_Comment: Sand & gravel. Well defined banks, 1 meter high. Good woody debris & undercuts

Location_Description: Enter through housing development site-Hoxie Br Rd, off W. Maple St. Reference site for Hall Br Dam Removal.
Habitat_Comment: Start upstream of small rock/dam impounment. Stop of site ends before clearing. Substrate is composed of cobble, boulder, gravel & sand. Majority of pool formation is caused from boulders. Most of site is step poos formation. Partly cloudy day. Overhead canopy is composed of sugar maple, white birch, hemlock, elm.

Location_Description: Access off of Gilead Street (DS of Gilead St xing). Downstream of dam
Habitat_Comment: Site located immediately downstream of Hall Brook dam (downstream site). Partly cloudy day. More rust entering system than observed from last year. Dominant maple overstory. Substrate composed of cobble, bedrock, boulder, gravel, silt. A few nice pieces of LWD. Metal pipes provide plunge pool. Mortality-1

Location_Description: Access off of Gilead St - upstream of dam below culvert
Habitat_Comment: Approx 3 meters below Gilead Street. Site immediately upstream of Hall Brook dam. Majority of site is gravel & sand. Riparian area is more flood plain wetland. Substrate is unstable. Maple & willow canopy cover. Mortality- 10.

Location_Description: Off of Washington Mtn Rd, above Hathaway Res.
Habitat_Comment: Started site in channelized area upstream of dam. There was stacked stone on either side of the channel. Substrate composition changed from that of the other 2 sites. Site is dominated by more cobble & sand than boulders. Boulders still comprise the factor for creating pools.

Location_Description: Off of Washington Mtn Rd, below Hathaway Res. between dams
Habitat_Comment: Sampled between the 2 dams. Lots of channel alterations due to the dams. Lots of stack boulders on the sides of the channel. The dam also erected 2 sections of split channel, split channel was about 50m. Hemlock overstory. Deeper pools.

Location_Description: Off of Washington Mtn Rd, below lower dam
Habitat_Comment: Site was located 100m below the lower dam & worked upstream to the large pipe of the lower dam. Overstory dominated by hemlock. Some down trees present. Water level is up but not unshockable.

Location_Description: Dalton Div Rd to Pleasantview Dr. Parked at end of rd.
Habitat_Comment: Bottom of site not the best, an ATV trail runs through it. Wanted to sample the stream below the confluence. Not much understory veg. Canopy dominated by hemlocks. Cobble, boulder, gravel, sand substrate. Sunny, partly cloudy.

Location_Description: Use rd that runs through Hancock Shaker Village
Habitat_Comment: Much of the mainstem of Shaker Brook has historical landuse impacts from dams that were utilized by the Shaker Village. The survey was conducted above the top most dam, but channel impacts were still present. Stream mainly a step-pool/riffle system. Habitat is very homogenius. Cobble, gravel, boulder. Water lever is up from passing storm. Good candidate for LWD installation.

Location_Description: culvert w/ property for sale off of Austerlitz Rd, ~1/3mi W of Bailey Ln
Habitat_Comment: Stream has nice pool habitat created by undercut banks, boulders & trees. Substrate is dominated by gravel, pebble, cobble, sand & boulder. Outcropping of bedrock are present at end of site. The downstream or start of site is located upstream approx. 10-15m of twin culvert. Riparian area has hemlock, pine & maple

Location_Description: Upstream of Seace Brook Rd crossing
Habitat_Comment: Started survey approx 25m upstream of Seace Rd xing. Substrate dominated by cobble, gravel, pebble, sand & lg boulders. Deepest pools are side channel pools created by undercut roots or boulder. There is an old 10m bank slide on river left that may have contributed some sand.

Location_Description: Off of Rt 20 near a cluster of homes. ~1/4mi W of Richmond Rd
Habitat_Comment: Started downstream end of site at an old dam ruins. Top of site ended at a bedrock riffle. Excellent riparian area composed of oak, maple, hemlock, yellow birch. Substrate composed of ? dominated by cobble, pebble, gravel, lg boulders in poos & some exposed bedrock. H2O clarity is good.

Location_Description: Off of Anthony Rd through 4WD road above culvert
Habitat_Comment: Step pool system. Substrate composed of gravel, pebble, cobble, & boulder. Boulders form the majority of pools with LWD scattered throughout the stream. Water is slightly tanic. Riparian area is composed of hemlock, beech, & yellow birch. Started stream above 4WD rd culvert. Spring salamander found.

Location_Description: Off of Tyringham Rd upstream of small dam
Habitat_Comment: Started upstream approx 7m upstream of small old concrete dam. Above dam, stream is much is much less channelized & impacted. Stream has very clear H2O & little silt. Really nice boulder pools w/ some LWD. Step pool system w/ cobble, gravel, pebble, boulder & sand as substrate. Riparian area composed of sugar maple, pine, oak, hemlock, beech. *Potential dam removal site.

Location_Description: Approx 30m upstream of Fernside Rd
Habitat_Comment: Steep gradient stream. Cascade step pool system. Tanic water. Substrate mainly composed of sand, boulder, gravel, & some cobble. Riparian area composed of hemlock, sugar maple, beech, ash. Sunny with mixed clouds

Location_Description: Off of Monterey Rd downstream of old impoundment
Habitat_Comment: Upstream of location os site is located downstream of impoundment & trib. Substrate is very dark w/ tanic water. Substrate is composed of cobble, gravel, boulder, boulder slab & ledge. Riparian area is composed of hemlock, yellow birch, beech & sugar maple. Some LWD present. Outflow of dam is over top. *Good candidate for dam removal.

Location_Description: US of E. Washington Rd
Habitat_Comment: Shocked US of E. Wash. Rd ~20m, shocked up thru old beaver swamp. Stream had defined channel thru swamp. Got narrower further US, stopped just before old beaver dam. Riffles w/ some pools present. Fallen trees over brk. Variety of substrate w/ sand, fine sediments & mud. Good cover for 1st 40m. Meanders thru swamp.

Location_Description: US of Michaels Rd xing ~20m
Habitat_Comment: DO meter not working. Started shocking US of culvert xing ~20m. Riffles & cascades main habitat w/ pools, very few runs. High gradient. Moss covered rocks. Water tannic at first, cleared up further US. Good riparian cover. ~50% exposed substrate, boulder cobble & sand substrate. EBT vouchered - not measures (~40mm). Couple of year classes of EBT found

Location_Description: US of confluence w/ Bennet Br, off Middlefield Rd
Habitat_Comment: DO meter not working. Shocked US of Bennett Br confluence ~15-20m. Stream runs along fence to Beefalo pastures, meandering. Substrate gravel & sand w/ fine sediments. Deep bend pools, slightly overgrown banks. Wide open, little to no cover. Good flow, not much structure. ~50-75% banks exposed in spots (bends). Schooll of BND & CS observed

Location_Description: US of E. New Lenox Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: No DO meter. EBT & sculpins found. Substrate ledge, boulder & cobble. Slight siltation. Strm grown in w/ multiflora rose from road to start poing (up ~30m from rd). Started shocking ~15-20m up from rd. Nice canopy after briars. Good flow, clear water. Some plunge pools, nice riffles & cascades. Crayfish & salamanders present.

Location_Description: US of Secum Br confluence
Habitat_Comment: No DO. Lost some fish (both SC & trout) due to high flow. Clear, cold water. Riffles, cascades, plunge pools & bend pools. Some pools deep (~3ft), exposed root structures create undercuts. ~50% channel filled in spots. Woody debris present. Good canopoy that buffers from cow pastures, ~15m ea. Side. Substrate cobble, ledge, & clay w/ sand & gravel. Overal, a beautiful stream.

Location_Description: Off of Rt 41. Started site immediately upstream of Race Brook confluence
Habitat_Comment: High water year. Stream is low gradient & has a split channel. Spoke w/ home owner. Channel right is dominant w/ flow. Split channel occurs ~52m of site. Substrate composed of gravel, pebble, sand, cobble. Some nice pools caused by the scouring of tree roots. Lots of japanese barberry. Maple & elm overstory. Could be a threaded system during high flow events.

Location_Description: Access off of East Rd downstream of private bridge
Habitat_Comment: Excellent undercut banks that form pools w/ LWD. Substrate composed of sand, gravel, pebble, cobble, & a few boulders. Pools are nice & deep. Overstory composed of hemlock, maple, birch. Great low gradient stream. Site below 2 private bridges end below a confluence

Location_Description: Access through field off of Stony Brook Rd, ~0.2mi N of Blue Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Unique stream nice input of LWD. Majority of pools created by LWD. Substrate composed of gravel, sand, cobble & boulder evenly mixed in quantity. Canopy cover dominated by hemlock. Little to no understry. Site started upstrem approx 60m from pond. Upstream of site incredible input of LWD! Step pool system. *Excellent reference stream.

Location_Description: Access off of Monument Valley Rd headwaters
Habitat_Comment: Difficult to find survey spot that is not brushed in. Majority of stream system is either impounded or flowing through a wetland. Surveyed area in the headwaters. Substrate is compsed of sand, gravel, cobble, & boulder. Thick understory. Past land use has degraded the riparian area & stream channel. Skipped a 100m section in middle. 1 EBT (93mm) found outside sample site, not included in LF/database.

Location_Description: off Chestnut St (upper section) US of UNT
Habitat_Comment: Low conductivity. Not a lot of fish. Did miss some fish. Wide at first then narrowed a bit. Few sections where stream created 2 channels. Good flow, clear & cool. Little sediment in pools. Wood debris present. Boulder, cobble, gravel present w/ some sand & mud. Good canopy. Slightly high gradient. Started shockign ~15m up from confluence with UNT that crosses Chestnut St. Worked just US of lg blown-out wood debris jam. Good mix of riffles & pools w/ plunge pools present & cascades.

Location_Description: US of Cooper Creek Rd xing ~20m
Habitat_Comment: High gradient. Shocked US of rd xing ~20m. Good flow. Water slightly tinted. Habitat mostly plunge pools, cascades & moderate runs w/ riffle in between. Missed some fish. Caught 1 TT (403mm). Woody debris present. Good canopy. Boulder, ledge, gravel substrate w/ sand & mud. Moss covered rocks. Some deep pools present.

Location_Description: US of Codding Br confluence, off Reservoir Rd
Habitat_Comment: Very low conductivity. Efficiency low, missed several fish. High fast flow. May need to survey again to get a better, more efficient sample (3ppl crew too small). Clear cool water. Lots of riffles, step pools, cascade & plunge pools. High gradient. Stream narrows further US. Some pools deep. Lg boulders, cobble, gravel w/ some sand. Moss covered rocks. Great canopy. Fairly issolated. Started shocking ~20m US of confluence. All EBT w/ YOY. Very little silt if any.

Location_Description: Us of Reservoir Rd xing (upper section near reservoir)
Habitat_Comment: Only 1 fish! EBT - 156mm (no LF sheet). Started ~15m up from culvert. Clear, cold water. Silt in pools (probably from res.). Habitat mostly cascades & plunge pools. Low flow. Water runs underground in some places. Boulders, cobble, gravel & sand substrate. Lots of woody debris & leaf litter. Salamanders present. Moss-covered rocks. Good shaded canopy. High gradient

Location_Description: US of Wrenwood Res, US of Belmont Res. Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Shocked US of Res ~30m up from rd xing (Belmont Reservoir Rd). Got key for gate @ Emerson Camp. Great habitat but few fish. Cool, clear water. Cobble, gravel, sand substrate w/ a few boulders. Lots of undercut banks & sm. Woody debris. Variety of habitats: shallow runs, riffles & pools present. Root structures present. Good canopy US of rd. ~50-75% channel full. Camp manager (Merv) would like copy of data sheets & would like prior notice next time.

Location_Description: DS of Belmont Res & Reservoir Rd
Habitat_Comment: Shocked DS of Reservoir, below higher gradient habitat. Missed a few fish. Lots of plunge pools & cascades. Lower section was lower gradient than upper part of sample reach. Boulder, gravel, sand substrat w/ some mud. Woody debris present w/ some fallen trees over stream. Good canopy & riparian zone. Water clear w/ good flow. Some undercut banks present. Exposed ledge on banks.

Location_Description: just DS of confluence w/ UNT from Belmont Res
Habitat_Comment: Accessed from Fernwood Campground & moved down to confluence. Shocked from sm. Footbridge (in Camp Romaca) up to confl. Lots of EBT! Missed a few. Meanders thru old beaver swamp. Low gradient. Woody debris, undercut banks present. Mostly cobble, sand & mud substrate. Wide open - little cover. Water clear w/ good flow w/ some silt.

Location_Description: DS of Grange Hill Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Had to cut sample short (72m) due to T-storm & rain! Good flow, clear water. Plunge pools, cascades & riffles common habitat. Some downed trees. Good canopy, runs along rd. Boulder, gravel, cobble, some sand. Ledge/bedrock present. High gradient. Some plunge pools deep. Started quite a ways down from rd xing - GPS coords taken from car.

Location_Description: start @ confluence w/ Whiting R, off Campbell Falls Rd
Habitat_Comment: High flow, white water runs/ plungers made sampling difficult. Started at confluence just DS of Campbell Falls & US to CT border. Start of large log jam. Forested riparian. Mostly rock/boulder substrate w/ sand, gravel in slow flow pools (edges only)

Location_Description: Upstream of Flintstone Rd & dam
Habitat_Comment: Started site upstream from influence of 4ft dam. Stream very clear w/ little silt. Substrate is composed of cobble, gravel, sand, boulder. Step pool system. Pools mostly formed from boulders. Overstory canopy cover dominated by hemlock. Some beech & maple. Dam location 42.49629, 73.11174. *Good dam removal candidate & LWD additions

Location_Description: US of New Marlboro Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Started 10-15m US of culvert. Tried to start further US but major natural barrier. End of transect @ baseof barrier. Mixed substrate cobble/rock/boulder w/ sand/gravel in pools. Hemlock-hardwood forest canopy. Due to barrieer channel splits into 2 main channels. Surveyed one w/ most flow through. In main channel had 1 mid channel island-surveyed both sides. LWD contribution significant. Hand-drawn map attached to back of data sheets

Location_Description: US of Campbell Hill Rd xing, DS of falls
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks. Shocked US of rd xing below Campbell Falls. High flow conditions made for difficult shocking. Missed several fish. Had trouble seeing w/ flow. Water clear otherwise. Boulder, cobble, gravel, sand substrates. Boulders slippery. Decent canopy. Section runs along rd. mostly riffles & runs w/ some pools. Deep b/c of flow. Some woody debris present (lg tree). Started to pour while measuring fish! Good hab. though. Missed 1 lg Bt (~300mm)

Location_Description: Launched off of public boat launch on Rt 116
Habitat_Comment: Nice cover for fish. Cover consists of down trees in water & aquatic vegetation. Nice diversity of fish. Killifish may be present at the boat launch. Edges are not shallow with trees. Clear day with some clouds in 70's.

Location_Description: along Rt 112, 1/2mi S of Thompson Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks. Heat wave!

Location_Description: Along Rt 112 between Fowler Rd & Smith Rd, DS of Hager Br confluence
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used

Location_Description: Along Branch Brook Rd, 0.3mi N of Rt 112
Along Rt 8A, US of 1st rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Flow decent, due to rains/Tstorm night before. Lost (~10) some fish due to bucket spillage/falling accident. Shocked a little longer than 300' to compensate for lost fish. Lots of EBT. Started shocking US of junkyard resident

Location_Description: Along Middle Rd US of bridge
Habitat_Comment: High flows! From rain & t-storm night before. Some deep holes in between rocks. A few lg EBT caught, LNS caught. Lots of EBT. 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: Along Savoy Rd @ pulloff 1/4mi W of Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Fast flow, from rains/T-storm from the night before. Water clera but moving good. Missed several fish due to flows. Worked up from riffles @ pulloff up to top of lg deep pool. Seconds on one of backpacks doesnt work

Location_Description: Lower site (garden), along Adamsville Rd opposite Wilson Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: missed some 0's & 1+'s. Fat salmon. 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: Adamsville Rd fry stocking staging area. W of Steston Bros Rd
DS of bridge on Rt 8A, W of Sumner Stetson Rd
Habitat_Comment: Wood turtle found

Location_Description: Old Rt 9 xing, US past UNT conlfuence
Habitat_Comment: Sand buildup under bridge due to damming by lg pines. Brook wram but flowing well. Good lg cobble/boulder habitat.

Location_Description: Along River Rd, ~0.6mi S of Rt 9
Habitat_Comment: Lost some small dace, <30 thru holes in live well.

Location_Description: River Rd xing, South of High St
Stage Rd xing
Lower site, Southampton Rd xing
Easthampton Rd xing, S of North Rd
Town Hill Rd, US of xing, Index site
Habitat_Comment: Water high, missed a number of fish.

Location_Description: Along Route 8, below cemetary across the street
Habitat_Comment: Water a little high, due to thunderstorms last night. Missed a few zero salmon

Location_Description: below culvert, along Cummington Rd, N of Mount Rd
Behind Worthington Rod & Gun Club off Rt 112
Habitat_Comment: Fattest EBT ever!

Location_Description: upper site DS of bridge on "Main Poland Rd", E of North Poland Rd
Below new bridge xing on Dingle Rd
Just above falls off Rt 143, just W of Thayer Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Looks like rain. Water low & clear.

Location_Description: off Rt 57, 1/2mi N of Sodom Rd
Habitat_Comment: Lost fish in bucket mishap (not many). 2 backpacks used. Smaller eel (approx 650mm) estimated due to slippery escapement.

Location_Description: US of N. Loomis Rd xing, pullout @ Baxter Sand & Gravel
Habitat_Comment: 2 Backpacks. Visibility limited due to tannins. Missed many SC & dace. Had 1 eel ~120mm, got away. Missed 1 lg trout ~300mm BT. Some lg trout in pool @ rd xing. Trib entering @ base of site, just above rd xing. Trib was dry last year, does not appear to be side channel to Munn Br but a separate trib.

Location_Description: along Maxwell Rd 1/4 mi N of Rt 8A
below dam site along Keets Brook Rd, across from Paige Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks. Water a little high for Aug but clear.

Location_Description: Keets Brook Rd @ farm Rd xing (lower site)
Along Brook Rd 1/4 mi W of Greenfield town line
Habitat_Comment: Good conditions

Location_Description: Along Skyline Trail 3/4mi N of Old State Highway
Habitat_Comment: High water, between beaver dam & falls. Good boulder cover & undercuts

Location_Description: Along Rt 66 1/3 mi E of Bean Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Higher water, plenty of tannins in water. Tree branches from ice storm. Garbage along riprap section close to rd. >5 AS 1+ missed.

Location_Description: Nye Brook Rd/2nd Division Rd
Blandford Stage Rd xing, 0.2mi E of townline
US of 1st bridge on Hull Rd off of East St
@ Loomis Rd bridge along Rt 9
Habitat_Comment: Water a little high, but clear. Hot & sunny. Efficiency low, water higher than it looked.

Location_Description: US of Carrington Rd xing
Pfersick Rd xing, below bridge
Habitat_Comment: Overgrown at riparian. Great LWD habitat.

Location_Description: S. Shirkshire Rd xing (powerlines)
Habitat_Comment: Overcast. No backpack data recorded.

Location_Description: Rt 9, across from vet office
Habitat_Comment: Missed fish due to lack of netters & fast moving water. Caught Huge RT ~400mm. No measured, escapee. Did section US of pulloff just E of ice cream/food stand/greenhouse. 2 backpacks

Location_Description: Along Ashfield Rd, just N of Village Hill Ave ~0.15mi.
Habitat_Comment: Started US of lg deep pool. Ended in run. Missed a few fish, flow good. Backpack seconds counter did not work.

Location_Description: US of Village Hill Rd xing, just E of Rt 9
Habitat_Comment: Worked up from below bridge up to rock dam. Missed a few fish. Good flow, clear water. Could've used 2 backpacks. Stocked RT found beneath bridge, bigger than board (~330mm).

Location_Description: Along Valley Rd, US of rd xing, S of northern-most RR xing on Valley Rd
Habitat_Comment: Smells like raw sewage by bridge. No coversheet filled out during survey, was filled out in office.

Location_Description: US of Harris Mtn Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Started sample ~50m US of road xing. Clear, cool water. Rocky, sandy substrate. Mossy rocks. Some undercut roots along banks. Mild sedimentation in pools. Few small cascades w/ plunge pools, one deep plunge pool ~3' deep. YOY EBT & RT. Missed some SC. Shady canopy. Occasional woody debris along banks.

Location_Description: Rt 32 crossing (Barre Plains), downstream
Habitat_Comment: Slow flowing, cloudy water w/ 80% gravel bottom. Frogs present. 1 BT - 280 (stocked). Backwater due to beaver dam.

Location_Description: Hardwick Rd crossing South
Habitat_Comment: Rocky w/ vegetation. Free flow. Barge. Covered 100% of river sampled. Low water flow. 1 BT (211, stocked)

Location_Description: Below off Billington Street, along Billington St
Habitat_Comment: Rapid flow below dam over cobbles. Triple pass. Dam slated for removal. Seconds not recorded.

Location_Description: old ped. Bridge off E. River Rd 1/2 mi S of Cone Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 Backpacks used.

Location_Description: Turnout on E. River Rd, 1.2mi N of Kinnebrook Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: Along River Rd, N of 1st rd xing N of covered bridge
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Missed some sculpin & dace. Not a lot of salmon. Good riffle habitat. Water cold & clear.

Location_Description: Reeds bridge & USGS gauge, Elmer Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks. We do not stock here, well DS of stocking site.

Location_Description: Turnout on Rt 116, 1/4mi E of Bullitt Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks

Location_Description: US of bridge on Rt 116 @ Riley Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks

Location_Description: Bascom Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks. Water clear but a little high

Location_Description: Sugar shack. DS of Burke Flat Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Left behind several sculpin. 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: Hayfield off of Rt 9, ~1/2 mi W of Shaw Rd
Habitat_Comment: Water clear, a little high.

Location_Description: Lower MA site (River Rd), ~1/2mi N of Nelson Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: DS of Russell Wiley Dam off Deerfield St
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Water low but cloudy. Urban stream. Flood walls on both banks

Location_Description: Powerlines on River Rd 0.6mi S of Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: DS of Windsor Jambs SP on River Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used

Location_Description: Right pulloff on Rt 20, across from Quarry Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: Zoar Rd, 0.2mi N of County Rd
Habitat_Comment: Cool morning, low water, clear.

Location_Description: Mohawk SF picnic area off Rt 2
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: Large turnout along Rt 112
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: start upstream of bridge off Rt 20 & Hampden St (western intersection)
Habitat_Comment: Missed some fish due to high water. 2 backpacks used

Location_Description: Bridge by Mass Pike off Rt 23
Habitat_Comment: water still a little high.

Location_Description: Along Warwick Rd @ School St intersection
Habitat_Comment: Electofishing demonstation for Northfield Mtn Recreation. Flow moderate

Location_Description: DS of DPW barn on Rt 8A
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used

Location_Description: above second dam off River St
Habitat_Comment: All suckers & trout in one hole created by rock gabion.

Location_Description: Along Warwick Rd, DS of rd xing, just W of townline @ pulloff
Habitat_Comment: Shocked US from turnout to below road xing, adjacent to house. Caught 1 big AS (190mm). Flow moderate- good for shocking.

Location_Description: off Swift R Rd, N of Rt 9 xing
US of confluence, below natural boulder barrier
Habitat_Comment: Started shocking US of Hamant Br confluence a ways, stream runs along backside of gravel pit. Worked up to natural barrier of lg boulders & downed tree. Lots of microdace, found EBT & WS! Stream meanders, few deep pools, some undercut banks. Flow low. Boulder, cobble, gravel, sand substrate. Good canopy, hemlock, hardwood. Woody debris present in spots. Most trout were small. Missed some sm dace & large EBT in heavy undercut/deep pool.

Location_Description: Culvert reach, downstream of culvert on dirt rd, along W. Mt. Rd 0.2mi W of Outlook Ave
Habitat_Comment: Survey done by professor & student of Mass. College of Lib. Arts. Cover sheet filled out by MDFW. Attached are copies of data in Excel format. Zero mortality. Tail tips not compressed together when TL was measured.

Location_Description: Upstream reach, upstream of dam impoundment. Along W. Mt Rd, 0.2mi E of Lanesborough Mt Rd
Habitat_Comment: Survey done by professor & students of Mass. College of Lib. Arts. Cover sheet filled out by MDFW. Attached are copies of data in Excel format. Zero mortality. Tail tips not compressed together when TL was measured.

Location_Description: Reference reach. Above culvert @ West Mt Rd/Lanesborough Mt Rd
Habitat_Comment: Survey done by professor & students from Mass College of Lib. Arts ENVI class. Cover sheet filled out by MDFW. Attached are copies of data in Excel format. Zero mortality. Tail tips not compressed together when TL was measured.

Location_Description: Downstream reach, immed. DS of dam. Along W. Mt Rd. 1/4mi E of Lanesborough Mt Rd
Habitat_Comment: Surveys done by Mass College of Lib Arts ENVI professor & class. Cover sheet filled out by MDFW. Attached are copies of data in Excel format. Zero mortality. Tail tips not compressed together when TL was measured.

Location_Description: Rt 56 xing @ Rt 12 intersection, downstream
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks w/ rattails. High gradient w/ rocky bottom. Sampled below Texas Pond. 1 RT @ 315mm (stocked). Frogs & crayfish present.

Location_Description: Turner Rd crossing (downstream)
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Stocked BTs. Rocky w/ step down pools. Crayfish present.

Location_Description: Along Granite St @ Leominster Town Forest, 0.6mi W of Old Farm Rd
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Wild EBTs only 30 total (ranging 53-150mm). Frogs present. Excellent sm brook. In steep valley w/ drop down pools.

Location_Description: Mendon Rd crossing, downstream of xing
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 25 wild EBTs (66-265). Trout only. Frogs & crayfish present. Started downstream of Mendon Rd & worked US.

Location_Description: Rt 16 crossing at powerlines
Habitat_Comment: backpack w/ rattail. Tannic water & channelized stone walls on each side up to culvert pipe. 2 EBTs 123 & 170. Frogs & crayfish present.

Location_Description: Sandersdale Rd (Dresser Hill Rd) @ gravel pit
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ 2 probes. High gradient w/ drop down pools. 3 BT stocked, 1 at 372 (beauty). Excellent canopy - nice brook.

Location_Description: Old Turnpike Rd crossing, S (US)
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ 2 probes. Silty & sandy bottom. Good canopy. 2 EBTs (150 & 184), no YOY.

Location_Description: Old Turnpike Rd crossing N, 0.4mi W of Scott Rd
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ 2 probes. Excellent stream w/ drop down pools & canopy. 22 EBTs (44-198)

Location_Description: Rt 2A @ powerline crossing
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 2 wilde EBTs (175 & 200), no YOY EBTs. Good mixture of drop down pools. Down tree (cover) & cobble. Excellent canopy. Sampled below pond @ Old Mill Rest (powerlines)

Location_Description: Upstream from Depot Rd crossing, along Rt 2A
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. High gradient stream w/ drop down pools. 9 EBTs (70-272). Stream not stocked.

Location_Description: US of Rt 12 xing & RR tracks, behind Zion Church
Habitat_Comment: Accessed stream behind Zion church. Started ~50m up from Rt 12 xing. Trout found! Survey requested by G. Krevowsky. Channel narrow (~1m). Undercut banks w/ root structures. Substrate gravel & sand, mud. Flow decent. Some woody debris. Deep bend pools holding the larger trout. Banks are part of flood plane in high flow events (sand/debris on banks). Canopy decent. Habitat mostly shallow runs, some bend pools & few true riffles (most riffles shallow).

Location_Description: US of Worcester St xing, behind Water Dept.
Habitat_Comment: Shocked up to driveway crossing to Worc. St xing. Water cool, clear, some riparian cover but sparse. Lawn manicured to stream edge. Frogs present. Boulder, cobble, gravel, sand substrate. Missed a few fish. Brook edge lined w/ stones. Mostly run habitat w/ some pools & very few riffles. Purple loosestrife present on stream edge. Deep holes in pools. Adult EBT, BT. Well withdrawl pipe in stream.

Location_Description: Behind Mt. Vernon cemetary, US of stone archway
Habitat_Comment: Accessed stream thru back of cemetary. Started above stone archway. Riffle, pools, run habitats. Some pools & runs deep. Some undercut banks. Good riparian. Some root structures exposed on banks. Some woody debris present. LLS found! Shocked 2 lg deep pools above end point (not included in seconds), found several lg BT. Could've used 2 probes for this section.

Location_Description: Above Gates Cove, above DCR access rd
Habitat_Comment: Nice series of pools, riffles & rapids. Not as many fish caught as was expected. No BT present in sample location.

Location_Description: Upstream from Wachusett Reservoir, below DCR acess rd
Habitat_Comment: Sampled up from edge of reservoir to culvert on DCR access rd. conditions (stream make-up) similar to above section ("above access rd"). Warmwater species gave way to coldwater species as we worked upstream.

Location_Description: Along Worcester St below dam, just N of Pierce St
Habitat_Comment: Below dam EBT & BND. Above dam, just BND no salmonids. 12 foot stone dam. Above lots of silt.

Location_Description: Above Browning Pond (Treasure Valley)
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Excellent section of stream. Pools w/ drop downs. Excellent canopy (hemlock). 1 TT (378) traveled upstream from Browning Pond (stocked)

Location_Description: Pleasantdale Rd crossing E, <1/2mi S of E. HillRd
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Gravel bottom w/ drop down pools. Only EBTs found, 22 (54-188mm). Storm damage limited length surveyed (trees in brook)

Location_Description: US of Laurel St xing
Habitat_Comment: Started shocking US of stone wall (US of Rd xing). Stream got narrower further upstream. Shocked up to boulder bridge, just DS of sm farm pond. Mostly dace & lg EBT. Small trib empties into stream just DS of starting point, COLD 7 clear! Boulder substrate @ first then gets smaller US. Lots of poison ivy! Frogs & crayfish present. Sm trib has pipe w/ outflow, streambed is dry.

Location_Description: Rail trail access, US of xing & sm pond
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ 2 probes. Trib above rail trail breech. 85 wild EBTs, ranging (34-197). Multiple age classes found

Location_Description: at Rail Trail crossing, below to above crossing
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ 2 probes. Sampled breech impact area. Found 9 EBTs in area

Location_Description: Cutler Rd xing downstream
Habitat_Comment: Below culvert coming from large impoundment. Heavy canopy. Flowing through rocky canyon. Some EBT present in older age classes. EBT x 6, 144-174mm.

Location_Description: xing @ railroad grade below steep grade. N of Gilbert Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Steep series of falls upstream of sampling location. Good canopy. Excellent mix of drop pools, riffles of varying depths. Healthy trout.

Location_Description: Railroad grade above steep grade, N of Gilbert Rd
Habitat_Comment: Sampled above railroad grade & steep gradient. Brook trout do not seem to be able to pass culvert/gradient. Brook habitat (pools & riffles) are identical.

Location_Description: Templeton Rd crossing N
Habitat_Comment: Only wild EBTs found. Surveyed below old beaver impoundment (replenished- new growth). 41 EBTs (52-166)

Location_Description: downstream of East Street xing
Habitat_Comment: Sampled downstream of road. Beaver dam blocks stream directly upstream of road crossing.

Location_Description: Malden St crossing (downstream)
Habitat_Comment: Water flowing from a breached beaver dam. Both warm & coldwater species found. EBT x 2, 208 & 194. "Industrial" smell w/ grayish tint to water. Similar to odor/color of Blackstone River.

Location_Description: Upstream of confluence w/ Asnebumskit, W of Heather Circle
Habitat_Comment: Abundant woody debris in stream. Water cold for coming out of impoundment. Multiple year class EBT. EBT x 48, range 180mm-52mm.

Location_Description: Quinapoxet St crossing (downstream)
Habitat_Comment: Small section done due to swamp/storm damage trees blocking access. Multiple year classes of EBT. EBT x 30, range 39-182mm. Sampled pool above culvert, no fish found. Water here much warmer than downstream.

Location_Description: Access @ Sisters of Notre Dame Property, off Plantation St.
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ 2 probes. Gravel bottom w/ drop down pools. 6 BT (75-94), 1 vouchered. Trib to Coal Mine Br temp 17.2

Location_Description: Lake Ave upstream
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ 2 probes. Samples 50 yds up from confluence of Lk Quinsigamond. 17 BT (64-223mm). Vouchered 1 BT, 2 B-Hybrids?

Location_Description: Calamint Hill Rd crossing, North
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ 2 probes. Excellent stream w/ long deep pools. EBTs. 7 SC netted & vouchered (1).

Location_Description: Off Terrace Rd heading west, off Rt 117
Habitat_Comment: Entire stretch fast, riffles. Missed some EBTs

Location_Description: Middle Rd downstream
Habitat_Comment: Shallow, heavy silt. Plunge pool at road

Location_Description: Middle Rd, upstream
Habitat_Comment: Heavy silt.

Location_Description: Blacksmith Rd xing upstream, N of Cranberry Rd
Immediately downstream of Briggsville Dam
Habitat_Comment: 3 backpack shockers used & 3 netters. Accidentally added 46m to site. Sunny & clear & low 70's. Water levels for the summer have been higher than the previous 2 summers.

Location_Description: Immediately upstream of Briggsville Dam (River right near Carson Ave)

Too many fish w/ 2 nets, so went to sets of 1 net each. 19 morts in problem net set #2, didn't tag already stressed fish. Cold! Lower 30's upper 20's w/ slight wind. Weights incl. bucket (900g). 61 fish caught: 23 tagged, 20 morts, 11 released, 16 recaps.

Location_Description: off Rt 62 behind tennis court, US

Lots of Ice Storm '08 damage. Appros 50% capture due to conditions. Approx. 100' culvert crossing Stanjoy Rd, concrete 24" coming apart, put in over 30 yrs ago homeowner stated.

Location_Description: Rindge Rd crossing US, 0.3mi N of Bennett Rd

Location_Description: Along Rindge Rd (West of) 0.6mi W of Ashby West Rd

Location_Description: Mendon Rd crossing, just E of W. River St
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. EBTs found (9). Sampled 3 long pools

Location_Description: Hartford Ave crossing
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. EBTs=4 (wild). 3 BL? Specimens not vouchered. Surveyed pools

Location_Description: New Braintree Rd crossing DS, ~0.7mi N of Church St

Location_Description: Rt 32 crossing DS of River Run

Location_Description: Loring Rd crossing, just S of Stetson Rd

Location_Description: US of confluence of Ware R off of Rt 122

Location_Description: Lyman Barnes Rd crossing (DS), 1/4mi SE of Mill Brook Rd
Habitat_Comment: This section of brook originates from an impoundment. Flows through a boulder field. Good flow present. 2 EBT caught (215, 210)

Location_Description: Kingman Dr crossing US, along Exchange St
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Sampled above & below road crossing (Kingman Dr). 1520 seconds combined Run 1 & 2. 4+ age classes of wild EBTs. 31 total EBTs identified & released.

Location_Description: Lancaster St crossing
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 2 sections of survey, LFs separate for each section but effort & length were combined. Survey #1- confluence of Nashua R to road crossing, #2- above road crossing to initial impact area (Lowe's store site). At site #1 @ confl. Of Nashua R sighted large school of WS fry.

Location_Description: Upstream of confluence of Wheeler, Gates Ave
Habitat_Comment: Upstream of confluence w/ Wheeler Br (=8.3m). 1/2 of the site is in a hemlock dominated area, other half is oak & beech. Stream has some silt but less silty than Wheeler. Substrate composed of gravel, sand, boulder, cobble & silt. End of site near a natural check dam. Partly cloudy.

Location_Description: Off of Gates Ave, upstream of Hunterfield Br confluence
Habitat_Comment: Upstream of Hunterfield Br confluence ~10.4m. Stream is very dry & low. Riparian area is composed oak, beech, & sparse hemlock. Stream is rather silty on top more so than you would think on appearance. Substrate is sand, boulder, silt, gravel & cobble.

Location_Description: behind St Joseph's cemetary Rt 8A, upstream of impoundment
Habitat_Comment: Stream site was located approx 100m US of impoundment. Stream appears to be altered. High overgrown boulder berms on either side of stream. 90% BND erre found below confl. Once gradient changes, great step pool formation, very few BND. Substrate composed of sand, gravel, boulders, cobble & pebble. Riparian area-sugar maple, beech & oak. Spring salamander present.

Location_Description: Upstream of Rt 8xing, S of Fred Mason Rd
Habitat_Comment: Excellent superb stream! Great habitat w/ deep pools, large wood, some natural bank distabilization. Below site ledge. Substrate sand, gravel, cobble & silt, occasional boulder. Nice habitat. Riparian composed of hemlock, yellow birch, sugar maple. Exposed undercut banks w/ roots. Terraced flood plan. Stop 50m below large huge boulder.

Location_Description: Below dam off of Gilead Rd
Habitat_Comment: First year following dam removal. Fines & silt appear to have increased in some areas. Substrate composed of sand, silt, muck, bedrock, cobble. Lots of trash still prominent. Some disturbance evident near pipes.

Location_Description: Reference site-Hoxie Brook Rd, off of W. MapleSt
Habitat_Comment: stream has not changed all that much from last year. Great riparian area mix of beech, oak, cherry, maple, hemlock. Substrate composed of sand, gravel, cobble & boulder. A few trees down. Flow seems about average.

Location_Description: Lanesboro Mtn Rd xing US, just W of Curran Rd
Habitat_Comment: Stream is ery dry. Fish are stacked up in culvert pool. Stream dry below culvert except for culvert pool. Dry for ~300m US from culvert then we found water. Section surveyed was very shallow but phenominal quantity of fish for hardly any water! During a wetter summer, it could really produce EBT. Riparian is 2nd growth sugar maple. Substrate-cobble, gravel, sand & boulders. Lots of downed trees. Site 25m below small 3ft dam.

Location_Description: US of West Rd xing @ VT state line
Habitat_Comment: Picturesque cold water stream. However not very productive. Site started ~75m US from West Rd culvert. System is mainly a step pool system w/ 1/2 car size boulders strewn throughout. Substrate mainly cobble, gravl, sand, boulders, bedrock. Riparian mainly hemlock w/ some sugar maple & yellow birch, beech. Perched culvert @ rd xing. Lots of dumping DS of rd.

Location_Description: US of confluence w/ Bear Swamp Br off West Rd @ VT state line.
Habitat_Comment: Boulders the size of Volkswagens! Very high gradient! Step pool system. Impressive habitat w/ some very deep pools & very well oxygenated. Substate composed of boulders, gravel, cobble & silt. Little to no silt present, only in backwater pools. Substrate hardly embedded. Slightly tannic, more yellow  water in color. Riparian is hemlock w/ some birch & maple. Start at site approx 40m US of confluence. Start when channel comes together

Location_Description: Off of Spring Rd behind small corn field, DS of last rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Stream can grow very large sized EBT despite some smaller shallower pools. Substrate composed of sand, gravel, cobble, boulders & some exposed bedrock. 1st attempt above last rd xing-no fish. Site ended @ waterfall cascade natural stream barrier. Lot of streambank erosion occuring. Riparian composed of hemlock, sugar maple, beech & red/black oak

Location_Description: Upstream of Red house off of Walling Rd
Habitat_Comment: Stream at first doesn't appear to be great, however tons of brookies! Nice plunge pool in middle of site, not a fish barrier. Site ended @ vertical cascade just DS of a cow pasture. Plunge pool in middle of site brookies were "boiling" out of. Stream would benefit great from restoration techniques. Riparian area- sugar maple, beech. Substrate-loose sand, cobble, boulder, gravel & ledge toward end of site. Would be nice to survey US of pasture.

Location_Description: US of MADFW Cheshire Barn
Habitat_Comment: Site ended approx 6m DS from old blown out wood dam. Substrate composed of gravel, sand, cobble & boulder. Boulders are forming the dominant pools w/ some pools have exposed tree roots. Riparian area dominated by hemlock w/ yellow birch & Amer. Beech.

Location_Description: US of East Rd (Daniels Rd) access off of private driveway
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed US of last home & above spring well head & hose. High gradient step pool stream w/ lots of shist as substrate. Boulders the dominating force driving the pools. Boulders about the size of very small car. Substrate dominated by boulders, cobble, gravel, w/ some sand. Riparian area- hemlock, maple, beech, cherry & some yellow birch. "rugged country"

Location_Description: US of Cross St bridge, control site
Habitat_Comment: Stream site has changed some over the prev 4 yrs. Tree at bottom of site is gone while an oak has fallen just US of the site. In addition, someone has made a small dam at the top of the site.

Location_Description: US of Dam, left channel
Habitat_Comment: 1 barge crew & 2 backpack shockers. Left channel is shallower than prev sample years.

Location_Description: DS of Briggsville Dam
Habitat_Comment: 3 backpacks used to up to pool below dam. 2 backpacks in pool (killed battery on the 3rd). 1 large RT jumped bucket. 700V to start, down to 300V in pool

Location_Description: Off of Washington Mtn Rd, US of Upper Dam
Habitat_Comment: Despite water being low, there's still really good flow in upper site. Stream gravel & substrate is very clean. Comprised of gravel, boulder, sand, cobble. Some downed trees & boulders are the forming locations for the few pools. Nice cold clear stream

Location_Description: Washington Mtn Rd between dam site
Habitat_Comment: Water is very low. Majority of fish found at base of the upper dam in a 2.5ft deep pool. Hemlock overstory. This section has a larger portion of silt than the below dam section. SC & BND not found.

Location_Description: Off of Washington Mtn Rd, DS of lower dam
Habitat_Comment: Water levels extremely low. Currently working on acces rd to upper dam. EBT looking rather cigar shaped & thin. Hemlock dominated riparian area. Boulder dominated stream w/ cobble, sand, silt, pebble & gravel. Not a great deal of flow over the dam. Majority of flow coming from 2nd pipe

Location_Description: Off of Flintstone Rd, US of dam
Habitat_Comment: Site is located immediately upstream of dam. Majority of water was found in 2 pools. Substrate composed of cobble, gravel & boulders. Hemlock dominated overstory w/ some beech. Lots of sediment collected above dam.

Location_Description: Off of Flintstone Rd, between culvert & dam
Habitat_Comment: site is located between dam & culvert. 95% of fish caught at pool DS of dam. Substrate was composed of cobble, gravel, sand, silt & boulders. Orange goo coming out of one of the dam pipes

Location_Description: Off of Flintstone Rd DS
Habitat_Comment: Downstream of culvert site. 1st 25 m of stream- no fish. DS of site completely dry for ~100m, looks like its due to disturbance event. Substrate composed of boulder, cobble, sand, gravel & some silt. Riparian is hemlock, beech, sugar maple & birch. Stream flow is down in Housatonic

waterbody: May Brook (1; UNT to Windsor Reservoir)
Location_Description: US of removed dam, US of Back Dalton Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Upstream of dam that was removed in 2009. Prev samples yielded no fish, however w/ the dam removal a fish pop has been established. Hemlock- dominant overstory w/ some beech, yellow birch at start of site. Site has a higher gradient than the other 2 sites. Substrate- boulder, cobble, gravel & sand. Little to no silt. Large quantities of ledge, boulder. Meter needs calibration; measurements are off.

waterbody: May Brook (1; UNT to Windsor Reservoir)
Location_Description: US of road crossing (Back Dalton Rd)
Habitat_Comment: 1st sample post dam removal. Stream is cold clear & free of silt. Flow is good for this time of year. Substrate composed of cobble, boulder, gravel & sand. Some nice pools formed by ledge boulders. Riparian area dominated by hemlock w/ some yellow birch, beech & maple.

waterbody: May Brook (1; UNT to Windsor Reservoir)
Location_Description: DS of Back Dalton Rd (57m)
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed stream after leaf fall. Stream cold, clear & at a decent level. Not sure how hot summer & no rain affected fish pop.Substrate- cobble, boulder, gravel & some sand. Hardly any silt. Some nice input of LWD. Riparian area composed of maple, beech, birch & ash. Banks are eroding. Wide stream at start of site. Riparian trees, fairly young 10-50yrs. Water chem meter not functioning.

Location_Description: Upstream of Kinne Brook Rd 1/2mi N of Dayville
Habitat_Comment: Substrate composed of sand, boulder, cobble, silt, ledge, is very black. Riparian area dominated by hemlock w/ some sugar maple & beech. 1/2 site very high gradient, other 1/2 low to med gradient. High gradient half has ledge outcroppings & large 1/2 car size boulders. Very steep step pools in 1st half. Site ended ~5-10m before wetland

Location_Description: Kinney Brook Rd upstream of rd xing, 1mi S of town line
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed stream adjacent to road. Substrate - sand, gravel, cobble, boulder & very small amount of ledge. Great habitat w/ exposed root wads, undercut banks & some boulder pools. Riparian area- hemlock, yellow birch, sugar maple & Amer. Beech. Stream rather small & low water flow

Location_Description: Access through Knightville Basin
Habitat_Comment: Accessed stream thru confl w/ Westfield R EB. Numerous inputs of down trees majority are in the process of decay. Appears to have changed the stream course in few spots. Riparian area- hemlock, beech, oak, ash, maple. Substrate- sand, silt, gravel, boulders, cobble. Pools collect great deal of detritus. Lost of sm. step pools. Riffle/run habitat present. Water leven expected for time of year

Location_Description: Goss Hill Rd w/in or near DFW property, off road side
Habitat_Comment: Substrate very dark. Rather difficult to capture small EBT. Most fish in same size class. Substrate- sand, gravel, silt, cobble, boulder. Riffle, run, pool comples. Not very many fish. Riparian area- hemlock, birch, mple. Decent flow for time of year

Location_Description: Along Wildcat Rd/Lane No 1. US of Old Westfield Rd
Habitat_Comment: Start of site just US from trail off Wildcat Rd. Stream composed of pools & riffles. Substrate- mainly sand & good size boulders w/ some cobble & bedrock. Not sure how much road is contributing sand in stream. Some nice deep pools caused by boulders w/ some LWD. Stream very clear w/ only detritus breaking down for silt. Flow rather low but continuous. Riparian- hemlock, white pine, yellow birch, beech. BND found below site

Location_Description: Indian Hollow Rd upstream of bridge crossing
Habitat_Comment: Surprising little stream, tons of fish! Stream flow definitely low. Lots of LWD, 10 or more trees w/ over 1ft dbh were in stream. Lots of nice interstitial spaces & boulder pools, some undercut banks. Probably missed some fish due to exceptional habitat. Substrate- boulders, sand, gravel, cobble, silt. Riparian- hemlock, yellow birch, sugar maple, sycamore.

Location_Description: Along Powell Rd, 1/2m W of Honey Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: End of site ~7m DS of log dam. Couple of really nice deep & wide pools. Some riprap along stream bank (minimal). Stream very very clear, hardly any silt, lots of broken down detritus & soil particles from moss. Substrate- ledge, gravel, sand, boulder & cobbles. Riparian- hemlock, beech, yellow birch, cottonwood.

Location_Description: Upstream of Dingle Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Stream is great cold water stream. Has a nice balance of pools, riffle habitat & some LWD. Excellent stream interstitial spaces. Riparian area dominated by hemlocks w/ some cherry & yellow birch. Dominant long deep pools caused by ledge. Substrate- ledge, cobbles, boulders, gravel, sand & some detritus. End of site is ledge pool US of LWD pool. Good "showcase" coldwater stream.

Location_Description: Upstream Hamilton Rd & US of old dam
Habitat_Comment: Surprising stream! Lots of rather large (~6in) EBT. Stream low gradient & substrate is black. Substrate- sand, cobble, boulders & some detritus, muck. Riparian- hemlocks, beech, yellow birch, maple. Old dam US of road xing lots of muck build up definitely a fish barrier. Initially looks like a dace stream but only EBT were found.

Location_Description: US of Rt 8 xing, Adj to Fred Snow Rd
Habitat_Comment: Stream has great deal of beach sand in it, not sure but assuming a result of beach at Camp Becket. Substrate - sand, cobble, boulders, silt. Riparian area- sugar maple, ash, birch, hemlock. Nice large pool at the start of site w/ some LWD. Lots & lots of CRC

Location_Description: US of Curtis Rd xing, 0.2mi S of Rt 143
Habitat_Comment: Low flow. Water clear, silt present. Water flows beneath exposed rocks & boulders. Very rocky substrate w/ some sand. Moss covered rocks. Pools mostly present, w/ higher flows riffles would be possible. Good deciduous canopy, nice & shaded. Some small WD & detritus present. Small salamanders & frogs found. Missed some fish due to deep holes beneath rocks. Old stone wall on banks @ end of reach, looks like it crossed the stream @ some point.

Location_Description: US of residence off Northwest Rd
Habitat_Comment: Gorgeous stream! High gradient @ beginning of reach, then leveled out some. Decent flow for what we've been seeing lately. Clear water w/ some silt. Good mix of pools, riffles & runs. Some woody debris present, undercut banks & pockets beneath boulders. Rocky, sandy substrate w/ boulders. Good mixed canopy. Frogs present. Culvert to logging/carriage road US of reach's end point. What looked like a natural barrier of high cascades @ start of reach much not be a barrier after all.

Location_Description: DS of Schulze Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Weird stream. Very low flow! Lots of exposed substrate, cobble, boulder & sand w/ some silt. Pools deep, "riffles" very shallow due to flow. Tons of CRC! Very few EBT. Water clear. Deciduous canopy. Flat stones toward end of reach (from possible dam?). Couple of rock barriers. End ponit below rock dam that's lined w/ plastic & sand/silt filled. Fish US of that to culvert are starving (would eat apple pieces tossed in!). US of rd- old rock dam, stream channel exists US of dam. Dead CRC found in shallow pools- related to lack of water?

Location_Description: Upstream of Worthington Rd xing by cabin/house
Habitat_Comment: Stream is an interesting mix of deep pools (4+ft), ledge, long runs & large complexes of LWD. Stream has extensive flood plain. Substrate- sand, cobble, gravel, boulder, ledge, detritus. Riparian- maple, hemlock, yellow birch, baslm, white birch, cherry. Flow very good comparied to a number of ther streams.

Location_Description: Access upstream of confluence & River Rd brige
Habitat_Comment: Stream has incredible habitat for its size. Nice deep pools created by LWD. Great flow compared to a number of streams smapled this year. Substrate- sand, cobble, gravel & boulder. Not a great deal of silt. Most fines contributed to detritus. All BND & SC found w/in first 3m of side DS of log jam. Riparian dominated by hemlock & occasional yellow birch.

Location_Description: US of Old Chesterfield Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Substrate is very black & water is slightly tanic. Water flow is good despite the really low flows this year. One rather deep pool w/in the site. Riparian area is composed of hemlock, pine, yellow birch. Substrate composed of cobble, gravel, sand, boulders.

Location_Description: Off of Reservoir Rd to Austin Bk Reservoir
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed stream downstream of reservoir. Old reservoir component/piece & old metal pipes scattered throughout site. Some portions of stream have old riprap on top of bank near rd. very silty stream may be result of being DS of dam. Very productive for coldwater stream. Step pool system. Substrate- cobble, gravel, ledge, boulder, sand, silt. Riparian- yellow birch. Stream very close to rd. Austin Bk Res is an active reservoir.

Location_Description: Off of Round Hill Rd, 0.3mi W of Rt 20
Habitat_Comment: Conducted sample in middle of ledge section. Neat looking stream, low fish productivity. Lots of very deep ledge pools but no fish in them. Substrate- ledge, cobble, gravel, boulder, sand. Some LWD. Riparian- hemlock, ash, yellow birch

Location_Description: Upstream of New State Rd, adj to Main Rd
Habitat_Comment: Very fat fish! Fish look engorged after a rain event. Rain brought back flow up to about average. Nice clear stream. Riparian- hemlock (dominant), yellow birch, maple. Substrate- sand, cobble, bouders & gravel. Started ~20m US from rd xing

Location_Description: DS of South St xing & US of Cobble Mtn Reservoir
Habitat_Comment: Surprisingly we got EBT. One BT too. Nice low gradient stream w/ great riparian area. Riparian- oak, hemlock, sugar maple, yellow birch. Substrate- cobble, sand, gravel, mud & boulder. Decent flow despite the lack of rain. Cold water. ~40-50m at top of site to culvert. Culvert very undersized for stream.

Location_Description: Accessed upstream of Stage Br off Stage Rd @ town line
Habitat_Comment: Stream has flow but is very low. Lots of lg boulders. Substrate composed of boulders, cobble, gravel, sand & silt. Riparian dominated by hemlock w/ some yellow birch, beech. Lg riparian area. Site ~150m US from confluence. Started site where gradient is not so steep.

Location_Description: Approx 150-200m DS of reservoir off Martin Phelps Rd
Habitat_Comment: Stream contains both low & high gradient sections. Sample taken in low gradient area ~150-200m DS of reservoir. Very silty w/ muck on top of cobbles. Result of being DS of dam. Riparian- hemlock, oak, maple, beech, some birch. Substrate- sand, cobble, silt & boulders. Some nice down trees in system. May have less silt deposit further DS. Good flow.

Location_Description: Outflow of Huntington Res, US of Rt 20 @ townline
Habitat_Comment: Step pool stream system. Cascade like section in middle of site. Reservoir may no longer be in use. Not much use on road, wonder if dam should be removed. Substrate- boulders, sand, occasional cobble, gravel. Riparian- beech, hemlock, maple, pine, birch. Dark substrate. Started where road meets stream

Location_Description: DS of General Knox Rd, DS of Russell Pond
Habitat_Comment: Stream is silty probably result of outflow from pond. Flow decent for time of year. Occasional trash found in stream. Substrate- gravel, sand, cobble & boulder. Riparian- hemlock, beech, ash, male & oak. Lots of crayfish. Surveyed DS of pond. Appears to be an impacted coldwater stream. *LMF spoke w/ DO on 1/27/11. EBT are wild, brook&pond Not stocked w/ trout.*

Location_Description: DS of Water St xing, just S of Trumble Ln
