Habitat_Comment: Impressive stream. 2 large trout & 1 lg eel. Lots of ledge/boulder formed pools w/ lg wood habitat. Substrate- ledge, boulder, cobble, gravel, silt. Nice lg pools. Great inerstital space in small & large pools. Riparian- hemlock, grey & yellow birch, beech, maple. Low flow

Location_Description: oof of Peru Rd upstream of culvert
Habitat_Comment: Substrate dominated by cobble & gravel followed by sand & boulder. Stream forested.

Location_Description: Along Rt 143, E of Goshen townline ~1/4mi
Habitat_Comment: Sampled US of barrier- old trail xing. Old barrier further US in mid-sample, water flowing beneath rocks. Boulder, cobble w/ sand, little silt in pools. Not as many EBTs as expected, but habitat is present. Shaded canopy. Good flow- rain the past 2 days. Water clear. Moss on rocks, made spotting fish difficult along w/ glare. Missed a few. Sticks & branches present. Stream channel narrows further US

Location_Description: US of Old Goshen Rd xing, 0.9mi W of Hemenway Rd
Habitat_Comment: Low flow, ~50% channel exposed, few fish & beginning of sample, more numberous further up. Found EBT. Riffles & pools. Cobble, sand w/ some boulders. Silt in pools. Woody debris present. Fairly good canopy. Talked to nearby land owner- stream was dry before rains (past 2 days), explains low #s of fish. Water clear, cool. Stopped @ electric fence spanning over the stream

Location_Description: Sylvester Rd crossing
Habitat_Comment: Nice stream, loaded w/ native brook trout.

Location_Description: DS of Audubon Rd, just E of Kennedy Rd
Habitat_Comment: Small stream, very low flows. EBT found. Stream almost dried up @ start of reach. 2 natural barriers (started @ 1) in stream. Most of substrate (boulder, cobble, sand, mud) exposed. Silt present. Sheen on water, possibly due to stagnation. Swamp US of rd. fallen trees over brook. US section of reach has more pools that are almost isolated, w/ only a trickle flowing into them. Stream would be decent w/ more water. *low gradient hab sheet used but a high gradient would be more appropriate if more water present*

Location_Description: Chesterfield Rd -> Dirt Rd along Marble Brook
Habitat_Comment: Low flow, substrate exposed- mostly boulder, cobble & sand. Silt present. Woody debris. Riffles, pools & runs present. Canopy ok. Lots of BND, missed some fish. A few morts. Frogs, crayfish present. Had some trouble w/ fish swimming out of field, diving down under rocks b/c of low flow. Muddy in some areas. Stream was mix of low/high gradient. Low grad right now due to flows.

Location_Description: Upstream of Audubaun Rd crossing, just W of River Rd
Habitat_Comment: Low water. Muddy, low gradient run @ beginning of reach, then turned into high gradient further up. Boulder, cobble, sand & mud. Nice & shaded. Missed some fish but got a lot of EBT. 1 SC caught, was already dead. Nice deep pools & riffle present (even though water was low). Fallen trees in brook. Moss covered boulders.

Location_Description: US of New Boston Rd, inside Quabbin gate
Habitat_Comment: Low flow, lots of substrate exposed, moss covered boulders & cobble. Good shaded canopy. Missed several fish due to exposed rocks & fish diving underneath rocks. Woody debris present. Water clear. Low water made it difficult to net fish. 2 morts as a result of netting accident. Lots of pools fed by water flowing underneath rocks.

Location_Description: Sta 2, SW end of lake, Beach
Habitat_Comment: Sandy gravel, no sav. Survey conducted by Berkshire Environmental Research Center as part of annual sampling done on Onota Lake.

Location_Description: Sta 5, Burbank Park beach, along Lakeway Dr
Habitat_Comment: Warm, sunny, calm. Sandy beach. urvey conducted by Berkshire Environmental Research Center as part of annual sampling done on Onota Lake.

Location_Description: Above & below Drift Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Rocky, high gradient stream. Evidence of high flows, disturbed gravel, unusual rocks for area. Pond above sample area. Craig CR purchased in 1999 by TTOR & WLCT below road.

Location_Description: Below Drift Rd xing, N of Great Island View Rd
Habitat_Comment: Next to metal storage bldg, most of stretch unable to shock due to brush. YOY & AE caught downstream, rest of trout caught in pool below road. Stirred up silt but generally cobble & gravel substrate.

Location_Description: Lovell's Rd (River Ridge Rd) xing upstream
Habitat_Comment: Missed large eel. Well vegetated, silty. Spharganium, sweet pepperbush, alder, maple.

Location_Description: Adjacent to Boot Pond Rd
Habitat_Comment: 3 runs conducted. Heavy vegetation cover, burreed. Deep ~1m. Numerous connected backwaers. Silt bottom. Seconds not exact, are estimated.

Location_Description: US of Long Pond Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Sand & gravel bottom. Lot of woody cover, logs & rootwads. Ave depth 0.3m. 3 runs conducted. Seconds are not exact, are approximated.

Location_Description: Above & below Rt 88, just S of rest area
Habitat_Comment: Above Rt 88 to chain link fence 70ft, mossy cobbles. Bridge culvert, very shallow & flat, 26m, shocked but no fish. Large pool below bridge, silty cobbles. No crayfish.

Location_Description: @ end of Hickory Ridge Rd
Habitat_Comment: Water a little fast but clear. 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: Pulloff Rt 116, 1/4mi E of Bullitt Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used

Location_Description: N. Poland Rd xing, 0.7mi S of Rt 116
Habitat_Comment: Water good level & clear. 2 backpacks used

Location_Description: 800ft US of town line, along Rt 8A
Habitat_Comment: a bit high but clear.

Location_Description: Turnout US of gorge on Rt 57
Habitat_Comment: A bit high but clear. AE TL's are estimates

Location_Description: Turnoff above falls on Maxwell Rd
Habitat_Comment: a bit high (rain last night) but clear

Location_Description: Bridge on Loomis Rd, next to gravel company
Habitat_Comment: a bit high, but clear

Location_Description: Farm xing on Rt 8A, 0.4mi N of covered bridge
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Water much lower than on Monday. 140 salmon!

Location_Description: 2nd bridge on Middle Rd, 1/2mi from Pudding Hollow Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Water still a bit high

Location_Description: Upper site, on dirt rd off Zoar Rd
Habitat_Comment:
2 Backpacks used. Attempted survey on 8/22 but cancelled due to high water from 
rain event.

Location_Description: DS of bridge on Zoar Rd @ Steele Brook Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Water high & fast. Missed fish.

Location_Description: Searsville Dam, US of Village Hill Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Water low & clear, cold.

Location_Description: Runout on (North St) Ashfield Rd, 3/4 mi N of Village Hill Ave
River Rd bridge off Rt 9
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: Lower site, along Blandford Stage Rd
Habitat_Comment: Water Low!

Location_Description: Rt 123 xing E of Mass Pike overpass
upper site, Old Schoolhouse Rd xing
2nd Carrington Rd xing, S of Main Rd
1/2 way bridge off Rt 66, Lyman Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: No conductivity (very low)

Location_Description: Turnout on Rt 112, 0.9mi S of South Worthington
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Water a bi high from rain on Monday, but clear. Missed a few salmon & trout due to fast current & high water

Location_Description: DFW land, DS of Rt 112 xing
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Light rain cleared up.

Location_Description: Turnout on hill along Skyline Trl, 3/4mi N of Old State Highway
Habitat_Comment: Low water

Location_Description: Powerlines off River Rd, N of town line
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Water low & clear. Sunny & hot. Salmon stressed, many died in bucket or livewell

Location_Description: Windsor Jambs State Park, along Rvier Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpack used. Water water, little rain last night, but clear.

Location_Description: Along Cummington Rd, 1/3 mi N of Mount Rd
Habitat_Comment: Very low flow

Location_Description: Worthington Rod & Gun Club, US of Rt 112 xing
Habitat_Comment: Water low & cold

Location_Description: Lower site, along Rt 143 just W of townline
Habitat_Comment: Water low & clear

Location_Description: Hayfield @ Rt 9, W of townline & Shaw Rd
Habitat_Comment: Low water

Location_Description: Off dirt rd behind barn, off Spruce Corner Rd
Habitat_Comment: Low water

Location_Description: Loomis Rd xing along Rt 9
Habitat_Comment: Low & clear

Location_Description: Cemetary site off Rt 9
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used

Location_Description: Upper site, River Rd xing, S of Rt 116
Habitat_Comment: Water low & clear

Location_Description: DS of Stage Rd culvert (Lower site)
Habitat_Comment: Low water. 2 backpacks used

Location_Description: Old Rt 9 (River Rd), 1/2mi S of Rt 9
Habitat_Comment: Water low & clear. Sunny & hot. 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: DS of driveway bridge on Old Hwy 9, just E of Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Water low & clear, Cold!

Location_Description: US of bridge on Town Hill Rd (Bancroft)
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpack used. Overcast

Location_Description: Turnout on Rt 8, 1/2mi N of County Rd
Habitat_Comment: Overcast w/ rain on the way.

Location_Description: DS of Pipeline, within Sudbury Valley Trustees land
Habitat_Comment: Stream channel open forested riparian. Solid bottom, mostly sandy, gravel & cobble substrate. Nice mix of bend pools, undercut banks, some shallow riffles. Some pools present due to past LWD contribution

Location_Description: Started just DS of Desert Trail xing, within Sudbury Valley Trustees land
Habitat_Comment: Started sample 10m DS of trail xing where flow stops. DS of this point water "pools" in swampy section. Similar habitat as Cranbery Br, but stream substrate is primarily sandy w/ fine detrital covering. Caught small % of EBT present, but difficult to catch (diving into detritus). ATVs crossing thru stream rather than on bridge, are widening the channel & causing sedimentation. Not connected to Cranberry Br thru surfave water due to low flow. Was completely dry @ trail xing in June 2011.

waterbody: UNT to Hop Brook (2, 1; Trout Brook)
Location_Description: Upstream of pipeline, within Sudbury Valley Trustees land
Habitat_Comment: US of pipeline ~10m. Started at stone 'weirs' noted by SVT. Meandering stream, good stable banks, undercut w/ good bend pools- good trout hiding spots. Not a lot of fish, some EBT. Some woody structure present in bend pools. Riffles present, some runs & deep pools. Water dark. A little more silty than DS site. Water flows thru 'weirs', not a lot of backwater behind them, don't seem to pose much threat to flows. Frogs & crayfish present. Beaver dam US of end pt. Ended survey too short by accident, but could've done 100m.

waterbody: UNT to Hop Brook (2, 1; Trout Brook)
Location_Description: DS of pipeline, within Sudbury Valley Trustees land
Habitat_Comment: Survey done @ request of Sudbury Valley Trustees. Surveyed DS of pipeline, ended ~20m down. Stream meanders along trail. Good stable banks. Flow ~50% w/ some exposed substrate (cobble & gravel), some silt. Dark water. Good mix of bend pools, rifles & sm runs. Undercut banks present. Good habitat present, just not too many fish. Flow good for this time of year. Crayfish & frogs present.

Location_Description: DS of Hudson Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Lots of fish, but only 2 EBT. Forested stream habitat on right bank, but left bank lawn to stream bank. Nice combo of riffles & pools, but no really deep pools. Very different from US of culvert. Culvert small for size of stream. *confirmed w/ J. Sheedy that no stocking occurs in Sudbury- EBT are wild.*

Location_Description: US of Old Lancaster Rd xing, across from DPW
Habitat_Comment: Suvey requested by T. of Sudbury. Lot of sediment in stream appreas to be in stream channel. No obvious source noted. Clear water. Sandy & muddy substrate. Organic debris layer, some vegetation growing in stream. D. Dineen (ConCom) said stream was fish in 70's & 80's for trout. Spoke w/ abutting neighbor- aware of EBT in 90's but not recently. Yards nearby stream edge. Limited forest, mostly brushy canopy. Frogs, stoneflies present. Lower section runs next to DPW bldg. EBTs were fat & healthy

Location_Description: S. Shirkshire Rd powerlines
Habitat_Comment: High water, missed some fish. Clear. New stream

Location_Description: Briar Hill Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: On Briar Hill Rd right after fields on both sides of road, right before road turns. Above box culvert (perched culvert).

Location_Description: N. Poland Rd, left directly after bridge, <0.2mi S of Rt 116
Habitat_Comment: UNT is located on left directly after bridge. About 50 yds past driveway on left, just past turn in road.

Location_Description: Shelburne Falls Rd xing, 1/3 mi S of Bardwell Ferry Rd
Habitat_Comment: Tributary parallels driveway #755 & 753. located on Shelburne Falls Rd, after decaying red barn & next to pumpkin orange house. Slight pull out located at st crossing.

Location_Description: Intersection of Williamsburg Rd & Bird Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Directly at intersection of Bird Hill Rd & Williamsburg Rd

Location_Description: Savoy Rd @ Fuller Br confluence (before entering woods), 1/2mi W of Rt 8A
Habitat_Comment: Went above flood plaing of Chickley. Lots of blowdowns

Location_Description: Sears Rd & Rt 8A
Habitat_Comment: At intersection of Sears Rd & Rt 8A. It follows Sears Rd right before farm.

Location_Description: At junction with West Branch Br
US of Carpenter Rd xing, just w of Fiske Mill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Some scour from flood event. Big EBT, fat!

Location_Description: US of Colrain Shelburne Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Stream looks very good, very little storm damage (post Irene).

Location_Description: DS of Radiker Rd xing, 1/2mi E of Rt 112
Habitat_Comment: Stream is deep. Culvert perched ~1ft. EBT were caught in culvert pool only.

Location_Description: Bissel Rd (US), W of Pond Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Road rutted by high water. Culvert perched. Beaver wetland upstream, old & drained. Lots of salamanders. Crayfish. Also shocked pool DS of culvert (zero fish).

Location_Description: US of Sam Hill Rd xing, 1/2 mi W of Rt 112
Habitat_Comment: Lots of loose sediment. Looked better upstream

Location_Description: US of West St xing, 1/4mi S of Sam Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Culvert perched 3ft! Very fat trout. Salamanders. Sediment from road xing

Location_Description: Scott Rd xing (US), 2/3 mi S of West St
Habitat_Comment: Not much flood damage. Culvert passable

Location_Description: Wilder Hill Rd xing (US), 1/4 mi W of S. Shirkshire Rd
US of Bardwells Ferry Rd & swimming hole.
Habitat_Comment: Stream channel hammered by flood (Irene), everything moved; logs, sand, gravel. Several small dams in stream

Location_Description: DS of Zera Fiske Rd xing, ~1/2mi S of S. Shelburne Rd
Habitat_Comment: Looks very nice. No storm damage. DS of large wetland (US of rd) (old beaver pond?). Some muck in pools & on margins

Location_Description: End of Reservoir Rd (US of culvert)
Habitat_Comment: EBT DS of culvert. US-300', DS- just pool (30'). Culvert box w/ no depth, 10' wide. Seconds not recorded

Location_Description: US of Foster Rd xing, ~0.1mi S of Matthews Rd
Habitat_Comment: Lower than last sample. Very closed to another UNT to Great Brook. Still lots of sand & some gravel

Location_Description: W. Oxbow Rd xing US, 1.5 mi N of Burnt Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Small, clear, clay subtrate exposed. Flat, plate-sized goshen stone. Good cover, good shade. Gradient increases rapidly after initial 100'. Road experienced damage affecting tributaries. Some scour at stream bank edge.

Location_Description: W. Oxbow Rd xing, 0.8mi N of Burnt Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Upstream of 36' CMP that crosses rd extends beneath adjacent property #336. *Barrier* Makes immediate 3' jump to cobble bottom stream 2' wide, entire channel <10' W. Well formed banks, enters mixed forest 150' above rd. good shade. All fish in pool immediately above CMP at Rd xing.

Location_Description: Avery Brk Rd xing US, ~3/4mi N of townline/Burrington Rd
Habitat_Comment: Lg goshen stone & cobble substrate just above lg box culvert xing rd. Lots of small wood (trees) in channel. Good pool structure. Gradient rises quickly 5%+ after 150ft.

Location_Description: Old Goshen Rd, ~1.2mi W of Hemenway Rd
Habitat_Comment: Stream formed from 3 tribs coming together. Decent habitat

Location_Description: Conway Rd off Webber Rd ~1/2mi. E
Habitat_Comment: Good pools, cobble & gravel substrate. Low gradient. Dr Letcher has survey posts at top & bottom of reach. Both EBT & BT found.

Location_Description: Rt 9 US rd xing, 1/2mi S of Old Goshen Rd
Habitat_Comment: Hemlock/birch dominant overstory, good shading. Previously logged. Blue flagging on stream. Good banks & lg cobble cover. Undercut. Some small wood jambs. Boulder enhanced pools. Cement culvert, outlet perched.

Location_Description: Nash Hill Rd upstream Rd xing @ Depot Rd
Habitat_Comment: Sandy bottom w/ small cobble. Well forested. CMP in good condition. Some road erosion problems. Public drinking water supply (WSHD) above stream, Noho.

Location_Description: Culvert reach; DS of culvert on dirt road, Along West Mt Rd @ powerline xing
Habitat_Comment: Survey performed by E. Traister & students from Mass College of Liberal Arts. Part of their annual surveys. High water following Hurricane Irene.

Location_Description: Reference Reach; above culvert at West Mt Rd
Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by E. Traister & students from Mass College of Liberal Arts. Part of their annual surveys. High water following Hurricane Irene

Location_Description: Upstream Reach; upstream of dam impoundment, off West Mt Rd
Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by E. Traister & students from Mass College of Liberal Arts. Part of their annual surveys. High water following Hurricane Irene

Location_Description: Downstream Reach; immediately DS of dam, along West Mt Rd
Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by E. Traister & students from Mass College of Liberal Arts. Part of their annual Thunder Brook surveys. High water following Hurricane Irene

Location_Description: US of Silver St xing (Dickenson Rd)
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed lower xing due to pond @ upper xing. Quite the species diversity. Water somewhat clear 2/ lots of detritus in water. Sandy substrate. Smll wood debris present. Mostly shallow w/ small pools & runs. 1 deep pool (~2.5ft deep) below big boulder. Undercut banks w/ some submerged roots. Moss covered banks. Good canopy cover -70% conifers, 30% deciduous. Moderate flow, ~40-50% substrate exposed.

Location_Description: Along Fowler Rd, 3/4mi S of City View Rd
Habitat_Comment: Nice looking section! Good available habitat, mix of pools & riffles. Boulder, cobble, gravel, sand. Moss covered rocks & banks. Great canopy, 70% deciduous 30% evergreen. Good flow, ~25% exposed substrate. Ended @ deep pool below road drainage (logging road). Culvert ~10m above that, 3 pipes. Missed 1 AE ~1ft long. End of section not as pristine, impacted by logging road?

Location_Description: US of driveway culvert, US of Hillside Ave xing
Habitat_Comment: Sampled US of 2nd driveway culvert, US of Hillside Ave. Low flow, >50% exposed substrate. Sand & mud w/ cobble. Small rock dam (man-made) 1/2 way up reach, water flowing through. Woody debris present. Mostly shaded canopy, exposed ~20m in behind houses. Ended @ deep pool next to manicured yard. Resident appears to pump out of this pool. Stormwater drainage flows directly into stream, pipes exposed next to stream bank. Production of both EBT & BT! Lots of silt & sediment, substrate movement apparent.

Location_Description: US of farm road xing off Birch Bluffs Dr
Habitat_Comment: A surprising stream! Tons of EBT! Stream overgrown, muddy, silty, runs along tobacco fields. No good EBT habitat apparent except woody debris but it's chock-full of them! Lots of overgrowth, thorns, trees. Deep runs & pools, no riffles. Very few shallow reaches. Shaded. Cold water. Lively, fat fish. Difficult shocking due to overgrowth. High conductivity. Missed some fish. Some beaver sign present.

Location_Description: US of Glendale Rd xing, <1mi S of Crane Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: A deceiving stream at first! Started out muddy, mucky, low gradient, turned more high gradient ~20m in. Habitat turned out to be nice. Low flow. Water flowed under moss-covered boulders. Boulder, gravel, sand, mud substrates. Moderate shaded canopy. Lots of invasive plants (barberry, multiflora). woody debris. Started at old breached dam face. Lots of EBT! Filled out low grad. Hab sheet. Some sediment.

Location_Description: US of small pond south of Bennett Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed US of small resident's pond. Good habitat where sampled. Boulder, cobble, sand substrate. Lower flow, ~50% exposed substrate. Variety of habitat- lots of riffles mixed w/ pools. Moss covered rocks & banks. Deciduous canopy. Woody debris & root wads present. Some undercut banks present. Frogs present.

Location_Description: Along Granville Rd, US of Gorge Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Stream crosses Gorge Rd, property of Springfield Water. Sampled US of box culvert. Very high gradient @ first then levels out. End point just before large natural barrier w/ downed trees. Boulder, cobble, sand substrate. Water clear. Shaded canopy. Stream narrow, in spots due to low flow (~50-75% exposed sustrate). Not many fish but stream is small & narrow. Lively EBTs!

Location_Description: Border Rd xing, Eastern-most xing (DS one)
Habitat_Comment: Nice stream! CFR. Substrate is cobble w/ sand & woody debris throughout. Mixture of habitat types & good flow (after rain though). Runs through residential area, but still mostly wooded. One yard in transect comes up to stream. One bend collecting sediment about 50-75ft DS of culvert (3 pipe culvert). EBT are healthy & fat. Females producing eggs & males producing milt (no kypes though), 100+mm fish.

Location_Description: DS of Hunter's Ridge Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Very nice. High gradient (for E. Mass), high flow (just after rain). Cobble, rock, sm boulder substrate. Dark substrate & tannic water. Difficult to see fish turn. Stream appears to be 'flashy' for a small stream, several large trees down in transect. CFR, low #s but healthy, fat & ready to spawn. Runs through residential area but wooded. 2 yards come close to stream but are wooded. Good mix of habitat types.

Location_Description: Off Greenville Rd/Turnpike Rd (Rt 124), 1/4mi N of Water Treatment Plant
Habitat_Comment: Wide, fast moving. Parked at log landing @ 42.98601 71.76545.

Location_Description: Pleasant St, behind VFW, upstream from Flagg Brook
Habitat_Comment: Brush too think to continue upstream. Saw several fish, possible trout, in pool at confluence w/ Flagg Brook

Location_Description: Downstream side of Cross St
Upstream of Gifford Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: 19 EBT found, all <140mm. Note: stream not shown on topo map

waterbody: Hemlock Gutter (UNT to Bread & Cheese Br)
Location_Description: Gifford Rd upstream, towards Mouse Mill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Sample also includes pool at waypoint 017

waterbody: UNT to East Branch Westport River
Location_Description: End of Primrose Lane
Habitat_Comment: 10 EBT found, all <140mm

Location_Description: Murphy South Rd (25m DS - 75m US)
Habitat_Comment: 1 BL found

Location_Description: Windy Gates Rd xing
Below Bread & Cheese Brook
Habitat_Comment: Dark stained.

Location_Description: DS of North Rd (driveway crossing at end)
Cutler Rd South of Muschopague Rd (DS)
Habitat_Comment: Even mix of pools & riffles. Log jams with pools behind yielded most of the EBT. Cutler Rd is a private road. Stream overflows most springs according to homeowner. 11 EBT collected, 144-43mm.

Location_Description: Millbrook St DS, @ Muschopague Rd intersection
Habitat_Comment: Banks extremely steep, heavy brush & trees covering stream. Some bedrock present. Many rocks & brush in stream. Lost many EBT under rocks & logs, caught about 50% that were seen.

Location_Description: Reservoir St crossing (US), N of Bailey Rd
Habitat_Comment: City of Worcester DPW maintains edges of brook. Open w/ ferns & poison ivy 3'-5' tall almost covering brook. Brook is 4-8" deep. Missed 2 EBT (approx 150mm & 90mm). Bank is armored in some spots with field stone. Could not see edges of brook due to fers. Flows out of a large swamp off Bailey Rd in Holden

Location_Description: Hardwick Rd xing, 1/4mi N of townline
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Rocky w/ drop down pools. Good canopy. 7 EBTs found only at plunge pool

Location_Description: Off Keyes Rd, ~1/2mi E of Bemis Rd
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Very rocky w/ drop down pools. Large deposits of silt at pools. Frogs present. Excellent canopy. 22 wild EBTs found, no yoy found.

Location_Description: Thomas St crossing US, 1/4mi S of River St
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Sampled between old beaver dams. 22 EBTs (wild). Temp surprisingly cold. Slow-moving water w/ sediment bottom. Past old smelt spawning stream from Wachusett Res.

Location_Description: Goodale St crossing DS
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 12 EBTs found (wild) & 27 SC found. Excellent stream w/ drop down pools, riffles & canopy

Location_Description: Kendall Rd (below Kendall Reservoir)
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 54 EBTs found (wild). Started above beaver impoundment. 4-5 EBT age classes found.

Location_Description: Elmwood Ave crossing DS, 0.4mi E of Princeton Rd
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Sampled plunge pool only, stream unable to sample (trickle). 16 EBTs found (wild). Missing multiple age classes, yoy to 2 yrs.

Location_Description: Along Lancaster Rd (near RR tracks), S of road crossing
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 7 EBTs (wild). Hard bottom w/ 3 long pools, nice riffles between pools. Banks of stream w/ sediment build up. Excellent canopy

Location_Description: Rt 12 (along), just S of McIntyre Rd
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 4 EBTs (wild) found. 1 long pool, trout found. Excellent stretch w/ rocks & gravel bottom.

Location_Description: Emerald Rd off Rt 56 (dirt road), 0.5mi E of Rt 56
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 10 EBTs (wild), 3-4 age classes. Excellent small stream. Gravel bottom w/ rocks & drop down pools.

Location_Description: Off Rt 56 (dirt road), 1/3mi W of Hillside Rd
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 13 EBTs (wild), no yoy up to 3 yr age classes. Excellent stream w/ drop down pools & excellent canopy. Also lots of ice storm tree tops in stream.

Location_Description: Dana Rd crossing DS, adj to powerlines
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 41 EBTs found (wild), 4-5yr age classes. Excellent stream w/ drop down pools, riffles & canopy. Recent culvert replacement & road repair.

Location_Description: Old Keene Rd crossing US
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 59 wild EBTs. Sampled 1 long pool up to narrow pinch point. 5+yrs of age classes found. Excellent canopy

Location_Description: US of confluence w/ Chaffee Br, off Packardville Rd @ Gate 8
Habitat_Comment: Sampled US of old dam & Chaffee Br confluence. Good mix of riffles & pools. Caught 15 EBT, missed a few. Good flow. Shaded canopy. Water clear & cool. Boulder, cobble substrate w/ some sand. Very little silt if any at all.

Location_Description: Packardville Rd (Gate 8), US of Cadwell Br confluence
Habitat_Comment: Narrow, high gradient step pools. Cascades. Shady. Woody debris. Hemlock canopy. Surveyed upstream from conluence Cadwell Br, ended at bottom of cascade, all high gradient after that.

Location_Description: Amherst Rd bridge xing
Habitat_Comment: High gradient, upstream of bridge crossing. Stoped @ upper cascade falls (~6' high). Acidic water, tannic. Only 2 fish (EBT <140mm). Found 1st EBT in pool half way thru survey, 2nd in end pool below falls. All cascades above, flow good. Old stone lined culvert 4' wide x 6' high. High gradient cascades DS of xing. 1 frog found. No water in 2010.

Location_Description: DS of Swamp Rd xing, US from Sawmill R confluence
Habitat_Comment: No GPS coverage, coordinates added later. Stream meanders thru lo area. Hemlocks, pines & ash. Undercut banks, woody debris. Deep bend pools. Soft substrate, mostly sand, mud w/ some gravel & silt. Good flow, water clear. Shallow riffles, undercutting w/ pools & debris make catching fish difficult. Quite the variety of species. Missed 1 lrg AE ~14". Missed several fish. Streamside residence has large screened cage partially submerged in stream, either a pumphead or some kind of tall minnow cage.

Location_Description: US of Perry Farm Rd xing, in Wendell State Forest
Habitat_Comment: Reach DS of Wickett Pond several hundred meters. Slower flow, clear. Sandy, muddy substrate w/ boulders. Missed a large fish (sp?). Frogs present. Good canopy. Mossy banks. Didnt start getting fish until half way up sample reach. Woody debris present. Some riffles present, good mix of pools, runs,  riffles. Some undercut banks present.

Location_Description: US of Belden Hill Rd xing, inside Quabbin gate
Habitat_Comment: Beautiful little EBT stream! Small but good flow. Lots of variety w/ habitat (riffles, runs, pools), w/ undercut banks & bend pools. Shaded canopy, primarily ash & maple w/ fern & shrub-lined banks. Aquatic snails present. Sandy, gravel, cobble substrate w/ woody debris present in spots.

Location_Description: Below Colonial Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Access at end of Brewster Rd. gravel & cobble bottom. Some moss on rocks. Some jewelweed & larger trees in riparian zone. Old footbridge in mid-reach. Max water depth about 6 inches. Some green-bodied damselflies flying. Some encroachment on riparian zone by house.

Location_Description: Meadowbrook Rd downstream of xing
Habitat_Comment: Note: Brook not shown on topo map

Location_Description: Below Smelt Pond Rd
Upstream of Rt 80
End of path off Dale Dr
Habitat_Comment: Saltmarsh below bridle path crossing. 1ft clay culvert. Sand over marsh below, gravel & cobble above. 3ft cobble dam & wood underneath silt. Some trout below bridle path & above dam. ~190ft sampled (150ft below, +40ft above). Salinity below bridle path. 200volts bumped up to 500volts.

Location_Description: Upstream of Money Brook Trail crossing
Habitat_Comment: Future biomap stream. Lots of nice large fat brook trout! Some great habitat w/ plunge pools & pools w/ large wood. Stream is one of the best in terms of habitat & fish #s. Substrate composed of slab boulders, sand, gravel, cobble, boulders. Nice step pool system w/ small riffle areas. Canopy composed of hemlock, oak, beech.

Location_Description: Upstream of dam, off Gilead Rd
Habitat_Comment: Two years following dam removal. Riparian vegetation much more grown in w/ tall plants. No trees present in disturbed area. Few trees that are present are sugar maple, ash & cherry. Substrate composed of boulder, cobble, gravel & sand. Most of post construction is a series of step pools. Avg stream flow.

Location_Description: Downstream of dam, off Gilead Rd
Habitat_Comment: Stream is laden w/ trash & open sewer semll is apparent. Substrate composed of sand, gravel, cobble, pebble w/ occasional boulder. Forested on either (side of) stream despite urban area. Canopy composed of sugar maple, red maple. High productivity despite small pools & urban degradation. Avg stream flow.

Location_Description: Reference site- Hoxie Bk Rd, enter through development
Habitat_Comment: Appears to have a new dead fall in stream which has created a nice scour pool. Flow appears to be average this time of year. Partly cloudy. Nice diverse habitat. Substrate is sand, gravel, boulder, cobble. More silt than one would expect in this type of stream. Some construction trash in stream. Canopy is maple, oak, birch, ash.

Location_Description: DS of dam site. Off Rt 8 adjacent to Cascade School Supplies.
Habitat_Comment: Sunny, partly cloudy. 1st survey post dam removal. Boulder, cobble, sand, gravel substrate. Flow is average for this time of year. Canopy cover consistent w/ previous survey. Top of site on river left bar is degraded.

Location_Description: Above dam site. Off of Rt 8
Habitat_Comment: 1st survey post dam removal. Stream channel wide at bottom of dam site. It then narrows up as you reach the top of site. Some nice scour pools scattered throughout site. Little to no silt. Very little canopy cover. Substrate composed of boulder, cobble, gravel.

Location_Description: Site #3 Control Site, US of Cross St
Habitat_Comment: Bright sunny day. Stream is slightly up from yesterday due to overnight stream flow. No stocked trout caught this year. Stream site appears very similar to previous years. Flows very strong & fish difficult to catch.

Location_Description: Access off of road leading up to Apple Tree Hill
Habitat_Comment: Decent coldwater stream. Not much stream flow compared to exposed substrate. Stream flow is less than 1/2 of exposed substrate. Pools not very deep. Nice blue green shist substrate, very flat. Substrate composed of gravel, pebble, sand, some exposed ledge. Not much cobble, might be due to substrate type. Canopy composed of yellow & white birch, & maple.

Location_Description: Access off private drive off of Main Rd, parallel to Rathburn Rd
Habitat_Comment: Water is low but had at least some nice pools. Surveyed the stream lower than expected b/c of access issues & stretches of ledge. Substrate composed of pebble, gravel, sand, silt & cobble. Some nice boulder pools. Canopy cover is hemlock, yellow birch, paper birch, maple.

Location_Description: Downstream of Flintstone Rd
Habitat_Comment: Stream appears to be slightly below average stream flow for time of year. Substrate composed of boulder, cobble, gravel, sand & detritus. Majority of substrate is loose. Lower half of site channel has been disturbed yielding very few fish. Some nice downed trees in stream. Canopy is comprised of hemlock, maple, yellow birch, beech.

Location_Description: Upstream of Flintstoe Rd, between culvert & dam
Habitat_Comment: Appears to be slightly lower flow than average flow. Substrate is cobble, gavel, pebble, boulder & silt. Majority of fish were caught at pools at the dam face. Canopy composed of hemlock, beech & birch.

Location_Description: Upstream of Flintstone Rd, Upstream of dam
Habitat_Comment: Only one size class of fish present. It appears as if only one of the juvenile fish survived last year's drought. Substrate composed of boulder, cobble, gravel, sand & silt. Pools are only present w/ large boulders. Canopy cover composed of hemlock, maple, beech. Flow appears slightly lower than average.

waterbody: May Brook (1; UNT to Windsor Reservoir)
Location_Description: Upstream of dam, US of Back Dalton Rd
Habitat_Comment: Lots of great habitat. Pools are nice & deep. Higher flow than previous sample. Sample is after 2 high flow events; Trop. Storm Irene & Bob. Lower section of site has lots of scour. Appears as if lots of boulders have moved. Hemlock overstory. Substrate composed of boulder, bedrock, cobble, gravel & sand.

waterbody: May Brook (1; UNT to Windsor Reservoir)
Location_Description: Between road crossing & dam, US of Back Dalton Rd
Habitat_Comment: Higher stream flow than previous samples. Sample taken after 2 high flow events; Trop. Storm Irene & Bob. Fish appear to be a little beat up. Step pool system w/ some pretty high gradient. Possible fish may have washed down to lower site from high locations. Substrate composed of cobble, ledge, boulders, gravel, sand. Maple, birch, hemlock canopy cover.

waterbody: May Brook (1; UNT to Windsor Reservoir)
Location_Description: Control site- DS of Rd xing (same as 2010)
Habitat_Comment: Higher stream flows than previous years. Survey sample following 2 very high rain events post Trop. Storm Irene & Bob. Survey occurred after leaf drop. Numerous leaves in stream channel. Water is very clear & silt free. Some deeper pools present than previous years. Large EBT present, may be a result of following high flow. Substrate composed of cobble, boulder, gravel, sand. Canopy cover composed of maple, cherry, birch, ash.

Location_Description: off of Washing Mountain Rd, above top dam
Habitat_Comment: Evidence of higher than previous 2 years for flow event. However instability in stream channel not evident like lower 2 sections. Some nice large boulder pools present w/in section. Average stream flow for time of year. Boulder pool forming stream. Canopy composed of hemlock, paper birch, sugar maple, cherry. Substrate dominated by boulder, sand, gravel, cobble, pebble.

Location_Description: Off of Washington Mountain Rd, Between dam sites
Habitat_Comment: Lots of instream channel distrubance. Lower end of site was a split channel & stream distrubance crreated a single channel. Mid-size debris jam was found in the middle of the site. Very few juvenile EBT, could be a combination of construction, short term impact., drought conditions last year & high spring runoff this year. Inatream flow average. Canopy composed of hemlock, yellow birch, sugar maple, beech. Heavy on the hemlock side. Substrate composed of boulder, cobble, gravel, pebble, sand, silt.

Location_Description: Washington Mountain Rd, below dam site
Habitat_Comment: Stream is moving a great deal of small cobble, pebble, gravel & sand through the system. Beginning side channel bar has increased as well as increased instability of stream channel throughout the thalweg. Stream flow is about average for the time of year. Well developed canopy w/ hemlock, yellow birch, beech. Substrate comprised of cobble, gravel, boulder, sand, pebble.

Location_Description: Off Rt 23 between Gibbs & Blair Roads
Habitat_Comment: Unusual species composition. Definite influence from Blair Pond w/ chain pickerel & pumpkinseed mixed w/ brook trout. Boulder stream w/ a high scour mark along banks. Lots of pools but not very deep gradual slow step pool system. Substrate composed of boulder, sand, cobble, gravel & ledge. Canopy cover is hemlock, birch, maple.

Location_Description: Access through cemetary off of Blair Rd
Habitat_Comment: Nice low gradient brook trout stream. Deep long pools w/ some undercut banks. Not much flowing water in general may be an underground seep contributing to cooler temps. Substrate composed of silt, cobble, boulder & ledge. Canopy composed of beech, hemlock, cherry, maple. Mix between a hight & low gradient system.

Location_Description: Off of end of Mica Mill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Very very very high gradient where we surveyed the stream. All of fish we found in the pools present. Pools were formed by boulders & ledge. Substrate composed of boulder, ledge, cobble, gravel. Very limited sand. Canopy cover composed of beech, hemlock, maple, birch, white pine & oak. Surprised to see trout in such a high gradient stream.

Location_Description: Upstream of River Rd, SE of townline
Habitat_Comment: Beautiful stream! Step pool system. Nice deep pools w/ rather cold water. Presence of LND were only found at lower end of site. Dace are suspected to be influenced by the close proximity of MB Westfield R. Old dam relic. Substrate composed of boulders, cobble, sand & gravel. Canopy cover hemlock, birch, maple.

Location_Description: Downstream of Rt 116 xing, 1/2mi W of Stonewall Dr
Habitat_Comment: Low gradient coldwater stream. Found a thermograph in stream. Stream channel is not very stable in parts. Substrate is soft & stream channel is shifting. Substrate composed of sand, gravel, muck, cobble & boulder. Most of pools are formed by downed trees in streams. Canopy composed of hemlock, beech, maple & ash

Location_Description: Upstream of Prospect St xing
Habitat_Comment: Small stream w/ slightly dark substrate. Started site at top most ledge pool. Ledge only present first 25% of site. Substrate composed of cobble, boulder, gravel, sand & ledge. Nice undercut stream banks. Canopy cover composed of hemlock, yellow birch & sugar maple. Appears to be average flow.

Location_Description: Downstream of dam-Powell Rd
Habitat_Comment: Lots of fish for such a small stream. Avg stream flow for time of year. Nice interstitial spaces for brook trout to hide in. a few down trees as well. Substrate is dominated by cobble w/ gravel, bedrock outcropping, sand & detritus. Stream right next to road. Canopy cover is hemlock, yellow birch, sugar maple, beech.

Location_Description: Upstream of dam-Powell Rd
Habitat_Comment: Stream is much shallower uptream of dam. Not very many pools. Interesting nick points as you move upstream w/ sudden grade changes. A large debris dam appears to have been recently washed out in the middle of the site. Lots of pebble & gravel as well as detritus are present just upstream of dam. Avg stream flow for this time of year. Canopy of hemlock, birch, beech, maple. Stream site is in close prox to road. Subtrate is cobble, pebble, gravel, boulder, detritus & some boulder slab.

Location_Description: US of Powell Rd xing - control site
Habitat_Comment: Control site has a great deal less flow than the downstream site. This portion of stream is not even present on topo map. Flow is present w/in channel, albeit less than others. Lots of nice pools w/ LWD. Low pH, not sure why. Forested on both sides of stream. Mainly hemlock in overstory. Substrate is sand, gravel, boulder, cobble, pebble

Location_Description: Off of Rt 116, between Bullitt Rd & Bird Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Bottom of site started upstream of cascade flow consistent thoughout survey site. Fish present throughout duration of site. Still quite a bit of disturbance throughout stream channel. Stream is in a ravine. Substrate composed of sand, cobble, gravel, silt & boulders. Pools formed by downed log. Average stream flow. Canopy is hemlock, ash, oak.

Location_Description: Downstream of Bullitt Rd xing, along Rt 116
Habitat_Comment: Stream site surveyd prior to MA DOT fixing retaining wall. Substrate a mix of cobble, sand, gravel & boulders. Not much silt but fines are present in form of detritus. Not much stream shading along river left (looking downstream). Canopy cover present along river right. Canopy composed of sugar maple, oak, ash. Some nice pools created by boulders. Top of site is 45m DS of Bullitt Rd

Location_Description: Upstream of Bullitt Rd, along Rt 116
Habitat_Comment: Average stream flow for time of year. Substrate composed of sand, cobble, gravel & some boulders. Not much silt. Survey is prio to MA DOT construction. Majority of pools in this site are along side the road. Canopy cover only present on river right (looking downstream). Canopy composed of hemlock, ash, oak, maple. Top of site located at top most thermograph.

Location_Description: DS of confluence of Creamery Bk-Reference site, along Rt 116
Habitat_Comment: Site is located immediately downstream from Creamery Brook & South R confluence. Interesting mix of habitat types: long pools, great riffles, scour pools & side channel pools. Bottom of site is at 2 large boulders, just upstream of another wall. Average stream flow. Canopy is ash, maple, birch, beech, hemlock. Substrate is gravel, cobble, sand, silt, boulders & bedrock outcropping.

Location_Description: Upstream of confluence w/ West Branch Br
Habitat_Comment: Not a very productive stream probably due to low conductive waters. Stream has great habitat characteristics such as undercut banks & a few nice pools. Occasional large wood. Not a great deal of stream disturbance. A logging cut that has occurred w/in the last five yrs on river left. Well developed habitat for stream. Substrate composed of cobble, sand, boulder, gravel & ledge. Canopy cover is hemlock, beech, balsom fir.

Location_Description: Upstream of Number Nine Rd xing, 1/2mi S of Underwood Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Eventful sample. It appears as though the sampe originates in the wetlands. Stream is incised from past agricultural use. Mucky substrate w/ some sand & gravel. Loose at spots under footing. Some undercut banks. Balsam fir, poplar & hemlock trees for overstory.

Location_Description: Downstream of Ledge Lane crossing & UNT confluence
Habitat_Comment: Rather small stream. Lots of very steep ledge upstream from site. Stream bank somewhat unstable. There is a nick piont that is marching upstream. Top of site ended  at nick point. Substrate composed of cobble, sand, silt, boulder. Not much depth to stream. Canopy cover is hemlock, ash, balsam.

Location_Description: Downstream of Stetson Rd xing, Along Stetson Rd
Habitat_Comment: Nice stream all in forested land. Surprisingly more silt than expected. May be a result of ice storm from 3 years ago. Lots of branches upstream of site. Substrate is composed of slab boulders, gravel, cobble, boulder, ledge & silt. Canopy composed of hemlock, yellow birch, beech, ash & maple

Location_Description: Downstream of Chapel Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Neat stream! Lots of great hiding places for fish; undercut banks, wood debris, boulder pools & interstitial spaces under rocks for hiding. Tons of juvenile brookies. Solid brook trout stream. Top of site located ~75m DS from road. Substrate composed of sand, gravel, little silt, cobble, boulders. Lots of moss cover. Canopy is white & yellow birch, hemlock, cherry, maple & beech.

Location_Description: Upstream of Central Shaft Rd & powelines
Habitat_Comment: Rather small stream w/ not a great deal of water depth. However, surprised to get 70 EBT. Substrate composed of cobble, gravel, sand, boulders w/ some silt & detritus. Occasional nice underbank. Canopy cover is yellow birch, hemlock & maple. Stream flow is about 1/4 of the exposed substrate.

Location_Description: Downstream of North County Rd
Habitat_Comment: Not much flow in the upper section. Surprised at the # of EBT. Nice undercut banks & pools created by large wood. Substrate composed of sand, gravel, cobble, & some boulders. Canopy cover is hemlock, birch & white pine. Low flow

Location_Description: Downstream of Raycroft Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Upstream of road appeared rather small. There is a road siltation issue. Hardly any young of the year & lots of trash dumped off side of road. Lots of small diameter downed trees. Most pool formation is from the trees. Substrate composed of sand, silt, gravel, pebble, boulder, cobble. Avg stream flow. Canopy is beech, birch, maple, some hemlock. Nice cover in pools

Location_Description: Upstream of River Rd & powerlines
Habitat_Comment: Wow! This stream produces a ton of brookies, not only in quantity, they're also some of the fatest brookies I've seen. The girths are impressive. Nice step pool habitat. Has stretches of riffles, scour pools, & center channel pools. Substrate composed of sand, boulder, gravel & boulders. Pools generally formed by boulders. Nice stream flow. Canopy is ash, maple, beech, yellow birch & some small hemlock

Location_Description: Downstream of Main Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Dark tannic stream. Flow is up from previous day's rain. Surveyed downstream of Browns Pond & Main Rd. Substrate composed of boulder, cobble, gravel, silt, sand & ledge. Difficult to see fish b/c of glare & dark tannic water. Canopy cover is hemlock, birch, ash & sugar maple

Location_Description: Upstream of Maynard Hill Rd crossing
Habitat_Comment: Nice stream w/ riffles, step pools caused by boulders & large wood. Lots of nice large wood. Appears to be average stream flow. Canopy dominated by hemlock w/ occasional yellow birch. Substrate is boulder (1/2 car size0, boulders, cobble, sand, gravel & pebble.

Location_Description: Upstream & downstream of Rt 112 xing
Habitat_Comment: Start of site is 55m downstream of Rt 112 bridge. Disturbed habitat under bridge caused by placement of large rectangular blocks. Substrate is composed of boulder, cobble, gravel & sand. Canopy cover maple, cottonwood, pine

Location_Description: 100m below new footbridge at site of old dam
Habitat_Comment: Battery #1 died. Misses many YOY trout. Below site of 2010 sawmill dam removal. Nice mix of gravel, sand & large boulders. Some large dead trees in river. ATV damage in woods.

Location_Description: Eel 1, Along Long Pond Rd
Habitat_Comment: Triple Pass (3 runs). Sand & silt bottom. Most brookies at end & near S trib.

Location_Description: Eel 2, Below Long Pond Rd
Habitat_Comment: Triple Pass. A lot of frogs. Runs: 811s, 663s, 641s.

Location_Description: upstream from Leonard Washburn Brook confluence @ Rt 44 xing
Habitat_Comment: Wild EBT above mouth in fast moving brush. Muck bottom 2-3 feet deep

Location_Description: Union Bridge Rd DS, adj to Franklin St
Old bridge @ Houghton Rd xing, Site 6
Downstream of Bullitt Rd
Habitat_Comment: River has changed dramtically as result of Hurricane Irene flooding. Midway through sampling reach, channel runs deep along wall (2+ft deep). Substrate movement evident, composed of lg boulders, gravel, cobble, sand w/ some fine sediment in deeper sections. Flow good but low. Water clear. Downfall trees at start of reach. Erosion of bank & wall next to road at start point. Was riprapped as repair. Thermographs in reach are all missing, were washed out by Irene.

Location_Description: Upstream of Bullitt Rd 0.2mi
Habitat_Comment: Habitat changed as result of H. Irene flooding. River more narrow at end point. Fair amount of sediment movement, including boulders & downed trees. Erosion on R bank (facing DS) caused fallen trees. Start of site still a deep run w/ lots of silt, sand & sediment. Middle is still a series of shallow riffles. Flow good but level is low. Some bank erosion @ upper end of wall. Thermographs w/in reach are missing or buried, except 1 @ upper end of wall (later to be found missing).

Location_Description: Downstream of confluence of Creamery Brook & South R
Habitat_Comment: Lots of woody debris along banks & into river. Substrate bedrock (@ start point), boulder, cobble, gravel, sand w/ fines in runs. Flow decent, water clear but levels are low. Fills ~50% of streambed. Few openings in canopy, otherwise mostly shaded. Larger woody debris just above start point.

Location_Description: Launched at Populatic Pond, downstream of confl w/ pond
Habitat_Comment: Part of Populatic Pond survey. Launched at Populatic Pond. Selective pickup of LMB only. Motored DS then surveyed from there to confl. w/ Populatic Pond

Location_Description: Pine Grove Ave xing downstream, just US of Peters River confluence
Habitat_Comment: Upstream side flows through culvert underground

Location_Description: Wrentham Rd upstream, towards Arnold Brook confluence
Off Patterson Rd, 1/2mi N of Ayer Rd
Habitat_Comment: Low water. Conductivity meter not working

Location_Description: Walker Rd upstream ~380m up from road crossing
Habitat_Comment: Missed quite a few EBTs

Location_Description: Off Pleasant St at junction w/ Ash St
Habitat_Comment: Russell St (42.35358, 71.56045) buried. Site done US of culvert w/ heavy snag. Low water but good flow. Silt, mud.

Location_Description: Off Pleasant St at junction w/ West Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Site shocked DS of culvert snag. Higher gradient than US site. Rocks, boulders. Misses a few EBTs

waterbody: Bennetts Brook (UNT to SB Souhegan R)
Location_Description: US of Watatic Mtn Rd xing, parallel to Bennett Rd
Habitat_Comment: Conductivity very low, readings were unstable.

Location_Description: #476 Pillsbury Rd, behind house at back of property
Habitat_Comment: Lower 2/3 of brook surveyed, wide & 2-3 feet deep. Upper 1/3 of survey shallow, narrow thru grassy field. Many large trout unaffected by probe in lower section.

Location_Description: End of Commerford Rd off Rt 2A/Rt 119
End of Surrey Lane, off trail on SVT land
Habitat_Comment: Very shallow, difficult for probe to even work.One pool muddy where most trout were caught. Survey done at request of Town of Sudbury & Sudbury Valley Trustees for CFR status.

Location_Description: End of Cranberry Circle, W of Border Rd
Sycamore Dr upstream
Sycamore Dr downstream
Stage Rd xing, just E of Shawbrook Rd
Habitat_Comment: Little water

Location_Description: Along Rt 9, 300' DS of Rt 9 bridge @ turn off
Habitat_Comment: Low flow. Dark, lots of silt. Stream veg & lg cobble boulders, look about the same a prev. years. Max depth ~2' in riprap pool

Location_Description: US of Rt 112 at Worthington Rod & Gun club
Habitat_Comment: Shaded, good flow, cond & temp. not seeing flood damage. Boulder cover high. Amazing # of EBT

Location_Description: Off of Rt 143, 1/4mi W of townline
Habitat_Comment: Shallow throughout w/ good holes in riprap on W bank. Good boulder pockets producing large #s of fish. Seconds not recorded

Location_Description: Along Cummington Rd @ Hull Forest Land gated bridge
Habitat_Comment: Dark, mossy rocks. Very low flow. 1/3 riffle step, 1/3 pool, 1/3 runs. Terrible efficiency. Lots of fish lost in rocks. Difficult to shock effectively.

Location_Description: Skyline Trl, Chester Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Low water. Pools, sm riffles.

Location_Description: DS of Stage Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Lg boulders, shaded hemlock. Pool, riffle, runs. Not much apparent post flood damage. Banks stable. Poor efficiency, lost a lot of fish in the rocks.

Location_Description: Kinne Brook Rd, ~3/4mi N of Dayville
Habitat_Comment: Low water. Lots of fine sediment. Good shade. Little instream cover.

Location_Description: Old State Highway xing, 1/4mi E of Rt 20
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. From new bridge upstream. Good cobble habitat. Lg boulders, pool, run, riffle. 1 AE caught was estimated at 3ft long (measurement not added to LF records in database)

Location_Description: Off Middlefield Rd @ RR bridge
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Good sample. Lots of 1+ salmon. Missed a bunch of sculpin & dace. Good cobble & boulder spaces in rifles

Location_Description: Off of Rt 9, 0.3mi W of townline
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Lg boulder substrate. Good visability & accessability from prev. years due to low flows. Dont think we stocked this section. The one 0+ salmong must have come from Stones Br. One battery cut out early

Location_Description: Windsor State Forest, along River Rd 0.6mi NW of Windigo Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Boulder/ cobble, riffle/run pool. Low flow. Decent efficiency. Lost a few fish but overall good representative sample.

Location_Description: US of Village Hill Rd xing, adjacent to Rt 9
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used

Location_Description: Along E River Rd 3/4mi SE of Cone Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. 3ft undercut root wad

Location_Description: Carrington Rd xing DS, 0.6mi S of Montgomery Rd
Habitat_Comment: Volume way down. Lots of changes esp. in pool vol. good undercuts, wood, root wads, etc. Sm cobble/gravel substrate, considerable fine sediment silt/sand. Banks stable, good veg.

Location_Description: Rt 23 xing just E of I-90 overpass
Habitat_Comment: Little murky following rain. Banks stable. Lg boulders. Undercuts. Pool step, riffles. Highly conductive (super high shorting out battery at 400). Good undercuts for boulders, pockets

Location_Description: Blandford Stage Rd xing just E of townline
Habitat_Comment: Boulder, cobble, low fine sediment. Good shade. Nice riffle step habitat. Back passes probably 4 1+ & 8-10 0+ AS

Location_Description: At crossing of Valley Rd, 1/3mi S of RR bridge
Habitat_Comment: Fine silt & cobble bottom. Dark. Undercut. Cobble habitat. Low water, max depth 1ft. Pushed the culvert to pickup some 1+ salmon, EBT. Pumpkinseeds came out of this reach. Good shade. Banks looks stable.

Location_Description: Lovers Lane Rd xing upstream.
Habitat_Comment: Stable banks. Bedrock & boulder, cobble. Good undercuts & wood at banks. Clear & cold. Great AS & eBT hab. Max pool depth 1.5-2'

Location_Description: Along Rt 8 (index site), cujo corner pullout 1/2mi N of County Rd
Habitat_Comment: Boulder, bedrock pools, runs. Sm. Gravel riffles. Incredibly difficult to sample, but a ton of salmon

Location_Description: Town Hill Rd xing, 1/2mi N of RR xing
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Sampled 200' DS of bridge & 100' above to avoid pool habitat. Good boulder, undercuts, bubble curtains & rock ledges. Banks stable. Lots of aq insects. Good sample

Location_Description: Rt 20 rd xing US of campground, US of Blandford Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Boulder, cobble substrate. Lots of algae in stream margins. Some bank scouring above rip rap at bridge. Step pools, short riffles, well confined channel. Knotweed encroaching on riparian area. Huge staging area for bridge & roadwork upstream at stocking pullout across from Wade Inn Rd. Back pass produced 6-10 AS.

Location_Description: Along Rt 112 S of Thrasher Hill Rd ~900ft
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Think were are just DS of index site. Good riffle run, & pool habitat. Complex boulder/cobble undercuts. Mod. Siltation in pools. Salmon abundant, brook rout not to abundant. Good shad. Stable banks.

Location_Description: Rt 66 @ Lyman Rd xing DS
Habitat_Comment: Shallow, small, silty. Streambed shifted & lost some of channel toward the road (Rt66). Dark, difficult to see. Lots of cracks . Tiny brook trout

Location_Description: Rt 112 pullout, ~1/2mi S of townline
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Wider section, more sun. Large boulder & bedrock substrate. Some deep pockets & pools. One long side channel 100' produced many EBT & AS. Lots of EBT & large EBT. Several hundred dace got away.

Location_Description: Rt 57 (Granville Rd) pullout past hairpin turn on right
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Bedrock & boulder dominate substrate. Deep pools >3' depth. Bubble curtains. Small riffles produced many 0+ fish & many eels all sizes. Volume low by 1/2, side channel that is usually full drying out. Is not regular index site.

Location_Description: N. Loomis Rd xing, adjacent to gravel pit driveway
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Very tough to grab all fish from riffles, lost a ton. Nice eels & lg trout. Root wad (massive) shifts to block stream literally. Nice pools in upper section, where majority of AS were found. Local fisherman (neighbor) said many of EBT he caught had bellies full of AS fry.

Location_Description: Southampton Rd xing US
Habitat_Comment: Well shaded. Boulder, cobble, gravel substrate. Pool, riffle seq habitat. Banks stable, root wad & bank LWD udercuts. Sedimentation in many riffles @ or above 50%. Lots of BT & one apparent TT, no formalin to pickle it though.

Location_Description: Rt 9 xing @ River Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Bridge being worked on. Shallow & seeing some sedimentation

Location_Description: Along Ashfield Rd, 3/4mi N of Village Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Shallow. Some sedimentation from prev years. Large boulder. Runs, riffles, pools. Max depth 1.5-2ft. Bank looks stable. Sediment coming from instream sources. Gravel pretty clear, <25% embedded. Good shade. Little wood

Location_Description: Rt 116 pulloff, 0.2mi E of Bullitt Rd
Habitat_Comment: Dropped bucket, lost several 1+ salmon & other species. Very low water. Working on bridge upstream.

Location_Description: Along S. Shirkshire Rd @ powerlines xing, US of rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Very low water. Lots of green algae. Site under high tension wires

Location_Description: Along Easthampton Rd, across from Stage Rd
Habitat_Comment: Very low water. Stream canopy low & overgrown. Tom turkey in stream.

Location_Description: Along Loudville Rd, 1/4mi E of Mineral St
Habitat_Comment: Missed a few 1+ salmon

Location_Description: Green River Rd (pullout), DS of orig site, 3/4mi N of Nelson Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Moved 300'DS of site to avoid split channel. Left many BND, LND, CS behind.

Location_Description: upper Green River Rd xing @ Hinesburg Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Shallow, sedimented 50% +. Cobble, gravel substrate. Lots of woody debris but mostly on banks. Signs of flood damage but banks fairly stable.

Location_Description: Along Branch Rd, 1/4mi N of Rt 112
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Boulder, cobble substrate. Tons of fish. Shaded hemlock. No apparent flood damage in the site. Pool at head of site deep. Lots of trout.

Location_Description: Rt 112 @ Branch Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Low water. Bedrock/bouder. Channel obviously impacted by flood waters. Bare channel. Banks look good, little erosion due to bedrock & rip rap. Shallow though.

Location_Description: Colrain/Greenfield Rd US road crossing
Habitat_Comment: Shallow. Highly sedimented. Small rocks & undercuts. BT looks like AS, light colored. No 0+ salmon though double check see if we stocked it.

Location_Description: Off Zoar Rd 1/3mi N of Brittingham Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Pool at base of site deepened  scoured at beach. Rest of habitat looks shallow, w/ good interstitial spaces. Rock overhangs & bubble curtains. Stable banks. Littered w/ bottles on road adj to creek.

Location_Description: Along Rt 8A ~1/2mi N of covered bridge
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Shallow, cobble, gravel. Banks raw, covered in boulders.

Location_Description: Maxwell Rd, 0.2mi N of Rt 8A
Habitat_Comment: Large pool in middle of index site is totally gone. Irene cleaned blow-downs out

Location_Description: US of Adamsville Rd xing @ townline
Habitat_Comment: Dark. Boulder, cobble substrate. Banks scoured but stable. Good root protection. Some downed wood. Very few salmon. Good efficiency.

Location_Description: Along Adamsville Rd @ garden site, opposite of Wilson Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Sandy, wide. Lots of trees down. Complex in the wod. Missed a lot of fish . Got 2 1+ AS & 4 0+ on quick back pass. Not the best sample

Location_Description: Rt 8A rd xing DS, next to Sumner Stetson Rd
Habitat_Comment: Lost a lot of riffle habitat through section. Many pools & runs. Good root wads & LWD where EBT found abundantly

Location_Description: Leverett Rd, E of RR tressel, <0.5mi E of Rt 63
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. USFWS may have been through to get their disease sample. Not a lot of 0+ salmon, eels (2). Stream wide, bubble curtains. Easy hiding places. Missed some salmon; 2 1+ & 4-5 0+ at least.

Location_Description: Along N. Leverett Rd, 3/4mi E of Moores Corner
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Dark, tannic water. Mossy cobble bottom. Very difficult to see, sure we missed fish. Bank stable. Good shade. Seemed to weather the Irene flood well in this location.

Location_Description: Keets Bk Rd/Shattuck Bk Rd (upper site), just W of townline
Habitat_Comment: Shallow. Bedrock, boulder dominate substrate. Small patches of gravel. <50% inundated by fine sed. Abundant small wood, debris in channel. Run, riffles, pools. Max depth ~1.5ft. Low conductivity. Decent sample. Missed a few sculpin.

Location_Description: School Rd/Warwick Rd xing, 3/4mi W of townline
Habitat_Comment: Dark. Mossy cobble, gravel, boulder substrate. Hemlock dominated overstory. Low water, half the lower channel exposed.

Location_Description: 2nd Middle Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Looks channelized in lower section above bridge xing. Cobble, gravel. Banks in good shape. Last 75ft of channel looks more normal after road between the 2 fields. Sedimentation in pool, shallower, lots of fine sediments. Good sample though, lots of fish.

Location_Description: Off of DCR access rd, DS of Muddy Pond Rd
Habitat_Comment: Low gradient. Pools, runs, riffles. Undercut banks & wood. Riffles produced astounding amounts of salmon & shiners. Fallfish in pools mostly, in lg #s. algae throughout gravel, cobble, sand substrate.

Location_Description: US of Dana Hill Rd/Muddy Pond Rd, old dam
Habitat_Comment: Algae covered boulder/cobble, sand. Started where water was flowing, through 2 riffles & runs. Tons of salmon

Location_Description: Above Rt 140 bridge, upstream
Miller St xing US, 1/4 mi S of Rt 21
Habitat_Comment: Upstream of rd xing between Miller Rd & house #590. Shallow, 8" deep avg. Mostly riffle/run w/ corner pool. After 60' thick rose bushes, had to bounce up 30'. Wooded area, pretty thick underbrush. Bridle shiner voucher (?)- later confirmed to be CCS not BM.

Location_Description: Heath Rd across Taylor Brk under powerlines
Habitat_Comment: Exposed though regrowing fast. Open rocky chnnel beneath powerlines. Partially functioning cement culvert. Run pool step though. Lg boulders up to gorgeous pools at head of site. Lost considerable pool volume from last year & produced less adult fish than recalled. However extremely impressive quantity & health of EBTs. Taylor Br scoured to clay.

Location_Description: Thibideau Rd xing US of culvert
Habitat_Comment: Cobble substrate above CMP culvert set at grade. Bank stability & vegetation look good. Good pools near top of reach w/ fabulous root undercuts produced big EBT

waterbody: UNT to East Branch North River (4)
Location_Description: Off Franklin Hill Rd 300ft upstream from GPS coordinates
Habitat_Comment: Low gradient, high levels of silt. Small pools. Fern & moss covered banks. Hemlock, alder, oak overstory. Went subsurface at starting point, disconnected from that point to EB North R. very shallow, most fish found in pools. Above top of reach, stream heavily incised, steeper gradient >5%.

waterbody: UNT to East Branch North River (2)
Location_Description: Calvin Cooms Rd xing @ Fairbanks Rd junction (US of culvert)
Habitat_Comment: Shallow, highly sedimented. Riffle habitat, 3.5" in depth. Small pools, 1ft in depth. Best pool immediately above culvert.

waterbody: UNT to East Branch North River (2)
Location_Description: Along Calvin Coombs Rd 0.3mi W of Rt 112
Habitat_Comment: Bedrock controlled step pools. Little gravel. Banks in good shape, no apparent blowouts. Small woody debris, shaded. This is upstream of the exact site sampled last year.

Location_Description: Little Mohawk Rd xing, 1/2mi S of townline
Habitat_Comment: 0 fish upstream of rd xing (200'). Perched CMP ~24" above grade of DS outlet. Bedrock falls DS of culvert. Sm step pools, little gravel. Unconsolidated rubble. Some sm wood. Fish caught in lower gradient pools & riffles 200' DS of rd xing. All fish obtained DS 200' of xing.

waterbody: UNT to West Branch North River (2)
Location_Description: between 389 & 381 Adamsville Rd, upstream of stone wall & cement pipe, 1/4mi E of Hillman Rd
Habitat_Comment: Ellie Rigosa (landowner, growseed.org) stopped to talk to us. Interested in restoration, tree planting, helping the trout. (she also has 2 other streams on her property). Pools & tiny riffles, very low flow. Cobble, boulder substrate. Incised channel. Good tree cover & bank stability.

Location_Description: Williamsburg Rd to Bird Hill Rd US of road crossing
Habitat_Comment: US of CMP xing (30") at Williamsburg Rd, sampled 150ft. Shallow, cobble gravel substrate. Tons of gravel & sand adj to culvert, must be backed up during Irene. Then upstream of next culvert at 42.49034, 72.76604, 150ft on Bird Hill Rd. US site more contained, mossy banks, boulder controlled, 4' avg width, larger deeper pools. S

Location_Description: North Poland Rd US of stream crossing, <0.2mi S of Rt 116
Habitat_Comment: Stream going subsurface between pools in first 100ft US of iron culvert (40'). Gravel substrate. Trib to east at top of reach dry. US of our sample site continued disconnected pools. Highly braided channel

Location_Description: #753-755 private drive off Shelburne Falls Rd, 1/3mi S of Bardwell Ferry Rd
Habitat_Comment: Small, brush filled pool & small riffles. Bedrock/gravel substrate, mostly well confined. Lots of woody debris. Well shaded w/ mix of overstory & shrubs. Switchign to hemlock forest above site. Darker, more bedrock. Begin of site has blue flag on RB ree, end of site at flagging & point of prop bndry.

Location_Description: Foundry Village Rd to Cary Dr in Foundry Acres
Habitat_Comment: Campsites. Nice shelter, start at wooden bridge. Cobble, gravel. 1+ salmon (only 1)! Nice pools, stable banks, good tree cover in sections. Some sedimentation issues at riffles. Nice spot to work up fish in the rain.

waterbody: UNT to East Branch North River (1)
Location_Description: Off York Rd, 1.2mi N of Foundry Village Rd, DS of homestead
Habitat_Comment: Small pools, short riffles. Lots of trees down in channel. Some bank sloughing & scour but doesnt appear much different from last year. Cobble, bedrock substrate.

Location_Description: Rt 2 @ Black Brook Rd across Cold River
Habitat_Comment: Brook fully isolated from Cold R due to bedload deposits in mainstem. Fish in lower section may have come from Cold R during flooding. However found fish (EBT) midway up impassable waterfall & when gradient reached 0-2.7 at top of reach found mult age classes in pools. Bedrock, boulder substrate, cascades, steep, some lrg wood, sparse gravels. Amazing & interesting brook.

Location_Description: Rt 143 to Geer Hill Rd xing upstream to confluence w/ Town Lot Brook
Habitat_Comment: Low gradient forested stream. Well est. fern covered banks. White pine, alder overstory. Gravel bed. Lots of downed wood, good structure. Pool, riffle sequences. Undercut banks, meander bends. EBT mostly in pools & undercuts. Lots of tanins, water reddish colored. Colorful fish.

Location_Description: Ashfield Rd to county line, follow Bradford Bk DS to confluence w/ Cold Br
Habitat_Comment: Low gradient forested stream. Hemlock overstory. Gravel, cobble bottom. Well confined banks w/ occassional side channels. Sampled into slight gradient change. Large boulders. Dark, high levels of tannins.

Location_Description: off Stage Rd, walked downhill to brook
Habitat_Comment: Shallow, low gradient. Hemlock, alder forested stream. Silt, gravel bottomed stream. Stable banks. Found 0 fish upstream of coord point to 300'. Turned around went downstream 380'. WS & EBT came mostly out of pools, riffle segments barren.

Location_Description: Plainfield Rd crossing at town line, US of xing
Habitat_Comment: Cobble, gravel substrate. Shallow, low gradient, raising slightly through upper section of site. Downed wood, pools. Small road crossing directly US of north road crossing. Tried South Hawley Rd in the State Forest; very swampy & disconnected, very little water so came downstream to this location.

Location_Description: Fuller Bk Rd xing DS, 0.4mi W of Chesterfield Rd
Habitat_Comment:
Tried above Rd xing but found no fish in first 150'. Culvert DS of Fuller Rd perched ~1ft from stream on DS side. Boulder/cobble substrate. Downed wood. Nice pool formation, scour pools. Banks stable DS, Erosion coming from road at crossing, could be stabilized.
*Stream line not on topo map or GIS, UNT was mistaken as Fuller Br*

Location_Description: S. Quarter Rd xing DS, 3/4mi W of General Knox Rd
Habitat_Comment: Upstream practically dry-unshockable. Spot-shocked below perched rd xing, no fish for 200'. Found 1st EBT in logging road where brook crosses. Slash/debris, tire ruts, etc. measured 300' DS to start survey. Sm pools & riffles. Gravel & cobble, boulder substrate. Forested stream. Stable banks. Fine sediment from apparent recent logging activity crossing stream & riparian zone at US end of survey. Observed fish DS of Soum Br xing, also perched. US is shockable though.

Location_Description: off of Herrick Rd @ end, last house thru field to stream
Habitat_Comment: Elane Gates, landowner at end of Herrick Rd gave us permission to cross her field. Said land surrounding area is conservation land. Wanted a copy of data sheet.

Location_Description: E. River Rd down to boat ramp & US from confl w/ res
Habitat_Comment: Start at rubble-filled cement culvert on other side of reservoir. EBT found between 100' & 200' US to base of a 3' vert drop, followed shortly by a 15-20' step falls. Surveyed 100' past these falls.

Location_Description: South Rd to end US of stream crossing @ CT state line
Habitat_Comment: DS of road crossing on South St. deep pool after broken cement culvert. Wetland above culvert. Shallow, meandering forested stream. Gravel, sand, silt bottom, lots of woody debris.

Location_Description: End of South Rd just into CT
Habitat_Comment: DS of rd xing, shallow forested stream. Sand, silt, gravel substrate. Lots of wood in channel, 8' wide. 2nd reach upstream past swampy wetland. Creek channel meanders & works its way back into the forest. Need 2 age classes,

Location_Description: Reservoir Rd DS towards cul de sac (Pine Glen Dr)
Habitat_Comment: Low gradient. Heavily sedimented. Forested. Swampy brook upstream into development cul de sac. Started there & spot shocked until finding fish in upper loc. Then proceeded DS until locating EBT at start point coord. Measured out 200' DS fromt hat point & proceeded w/ lower survey.

Location_Description: Lyon St xing US
Habitat_Comment: Urbanized lawns going right up to channel above sampled sections, going through back yards. Substrates gravel & muck, less than 1ft in depth. Tiny pools, tinier riffles.

Location_Description: US of Depot Rd xing (road going to gravel pit)
Habitat_Comment: 37 wild EBTs found. Excellent canopy. Multiple age classes. Survey as part of review for proposed MBTA layover facility.

Location_Description: RR crossing to Depot Rd culvert (road going to gravel pit)
Habitat_Comment: Survey as part of review for proposed MBTA layover facility

Location_Description: DCR access road to Wachusett Res, off Rt 140/12
Habitat_Comment: Strong odor. High gradient. All fish from below 1st culvert. Surveyed from reservoir plunge pool to railroad crossing. Many small pools amongst channel.

Location_Description: Rt 117 corssing DS, DS of Bartlett Pond
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ 2 probes, crew of 3. 3 EBTs found w/ multiple age classes. Crayfish & frogs present. Good canopy w/ downed trees & cobble. *boards removed at Bartlett Pond, free flowing through pond up to confluence of Nashua R.

Location_Description: Rt 117 crossing DS
Habitat_Comment: 1 EBT found. 1 8-10" BT seen (stocked trout from pond). Black spec found on cyprinids

Location_Description: Rt 117 crossing US to dam
Habitat_Comment: 1 EBT found. Surveyed from Rt 117 crossing to dam (Bartlett Pond). Frogs & crayfish present.

Location_Description: Above Bartlett Pond US
Habitat_Comment: Multiple age classes- EBTs (57). Backpack w/ 2 probes, 3 person crew. Sand on top w/ 1 ft+ of silt underneath. No canopy. Past beaver activities w/ multiple staged old beaver dams. Crayfish present.

Location_Description: Lake Rd crossing N
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Survey plunge pool only (brook dry). 1 EBT - 280mm. Frogs present.

Location_Description: Mill Rd crossing DS, ~1/2mi N of King Rd
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Low flow w/ good canopy. Frogs present. 22 EBTs found.

Location_Description: off Colony Rd US of confluence
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 25 EBTs found. Sampled pools. Excellent canopy. Frogs & crayfish

Location_Description: Gulf Rd DS crossing
Habitat_Comment: Many small pools w/ mixed substrate. No crawfish, many frogs. Fish spread throughout stream. Many rocks causing small gradual step pools. Little sediment. Brookies ranging from 130-44 with a total of 33. vegetation growth to stream, w/ hemlock & hardwood canopy. Little impact from road crossing from erosion.

Location_Description: Cons property DS of Newton Res
Habitat_Comment: 20 EBTs. Backpack w/ rattail. Sampled pools mainly, thin water between pools. Excellent canopy

Location_Description: Andrea Ln crossing US
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. EBTs only. Channelized w/ rock walls. Cloudy water w/ stagnant pools surveyed. Surprising to find EBTs

Location_Description: Above Trout Brook Park
Habitat_Comment: Isolated pools w/ minimum flow between. Sampling conducted above & below natural boulder 4' wall amongst stream bed. EBTs found in pools above & below barrier. Hemlock canopy with moss covered stony bottom. No fine sediments. 30 EBTs, 60-146m.

Location_Description: Forbush Mill Rd DS, 1/3mi W of Main St
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 83 EBTs found. Cold clean water w/ excellent canopy. Plenty of EBTs left behind along sample zone. Excellent stream

Location_Description: Cronin Rd crossing DS, just N of powerlines xing
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 8 EBTs (52-1433mm). Rocks w/ stone base. Silt build up at pools. Good canopy. Frogs present

Location_Description: Southbridge Rd crossing DS, 1/4mi N of Brookfield Rd
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 27 EBTs (46-170mm). Loose rocks w/ hard bottom. Good canopy, frogs present.

Location_Description: Off of Rt 8 adjacent to Cascade School Supplies. Upstream of dam site
Habitat_Comment: 3 backpacks used. Split channel post-Irene. Deeper channel is on river right. Tons & tons of little fish. Rained in early morning but stream flow still appears low w/ no turbidity. A portion of bank on both sides are slumping. Substrate composed of boulder, sand, cobble, gravel & silt. Very large percentage of wetted rocks are algae-covered. Canopy cover of maple, willow & oak.

Location_Description: Off of Clesson Brook Rd, 1/2mi W of Shepherd Rd
Habitat_Comment: First sample post Irene. Site starts upstream of streamford & placed stream boulders. Site ends at red house. Habitat was not that great in site. Mostly small step pools & riffles w/ some slack water. Lots of down cutting from storm w/ sand. Banks are very scoured. Riparian area composed of yellow birch, white pine, beech, poplar, maple

Location_Description: off Apple Valley Rd, 800ft W of Smith Rd
Habitat_Comment: Surprisingly very few fish! Not sure what is going on. Sample located in more of ledge sectin. Has deep pools but not much cover in the pools. Pools have a ton of post-Irene sand in it. Some cover is still available. Hemlock, birch & maple riparian area. Substrate composed of sand, ledge, cobble & boulder. Site locaed ~20m upstream from first bridge.

Location_Description: DS of Summer St
Upstream of Cross Rd, parallel to Rt 8
Habitat_Comment: 1st year after TS Irene. Upstream of site on river right major bank failure w/ entire loss of riparian trees. W/in control site riprap was redone & sligthly extended in length. Stream is slightly turbid compared to the other 2 samples & lot less algae growth. Substrate mainly boulder, gravel, sand & cobble w/ some silt. Riparian area composed of maple, white pine, oak, cotton wood. 3 backpacks used.

Location_Description: Off Rt 8 adjacent to Cascade School Supplies. Downstream of dam site.
Habitat_Comment: Very low water year. First sample post-Irene. 3 backpacks used. Lots of algae in strem. Riprap now present on river left for 2/3 of the site. Riprap side now devoid of trees. Riprap does not match native rock composition in stream. Riparian composed of Willow, maple, oak & ash. Substrate of boulders, cobble, sand & gravel

Location_Description: off Rt 112 downstream @ Athertons Farm, 1/2mi N of Upper st
Habitat_Comment: Repeat of 2004 survey after Irene. Tons of fish! Stream channel has shifted to river right. One large root wad in site. Site located between Athertons Farm stand & next bridge heading north. Grassy pulloff. Substrate of sand, cobble, & boulder. Very large cobble/boulder bar in site. Not much riparian shading.

Location_Description: Upstream reach, US of where dam was removed, off West Mt Rd
Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by E. Traister of Mass College of Liberal Arts, as part of their annual Thunder Br surveys. Zero mortality. Reach reflagged-downstream end is where dam was removed

Location_Description: Culvert reach, downstream of culvert on dirt road, off West Mt Rd
Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by E. Traister of Mass College of Lib Arts, part of their annual Thunder Br surveys. Zero mortality

Location_Description: Reference reach, above culvert at West Mt Rd
