Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by E. Traister of Mass College of Lib Arts, part of their annual Thunder Br surveys. Zero mortality.

Location_Description: Downstream reach, immediately DS of dam's prior location, off West Mt Rd
Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by E. Traister of Mass College of Lib Arts, part of their annual Thunder Brook surveys. Zero mortality

Location_Description: Downstream of dam on Powell Rd
Habitat_Comment: Started survey at flagged start point & worked up to dam face. Flow low for July due to lack of rainfall. Clear & cool water though. ~50-75% substrate exposed. Substrate boulders, bedrock, cobble, gravel w/ some sand. Woody debris in some spots, probably due to high flows during H. Irene. Shaded canopy. Moss-covered rocks. Lots of EBT, different age classes (n=140!)

Location_Description: Upstream of dam on Powell Rd
Habitat_Comment: Started at dam & worked up to flagged end point. Low flows for July due to lack of rain. 50-75% substrate exposed in areas. Some silt in pools. Pools above dam very silty. Substrate boulder, bedrock, gravel, cobble, some sand. Shaded canopy. Some small woody debris piles present on banks. More yoy at this site.

Location_Description: Upstream of Powell Rd xing, Reference site
Habitat_Comment: Low to no flow! Stream goes to isolated pools at 40m (just US of large woody debris pile across stream), then dries up at 75m w/ 1 isolated pool near end point holding 1 small EBT. Isolated pools loaded w/ EBT (all yr classes) that have survived. Lack of rain is most likely cause. Fish stressed as a result. Mostly shaded canopy. Substrate boulder, cobble, gravel, mud & silt in pools at woody debris jam. Moss covered rocks. Flow moves subterrainean @ 40m. A few more isolated pools US of end point w/ fish. One dead EBT in 2nd to last pool shocked.

Location_Description: Washington Mountain Rd, above top dam
Habitat_Comment: Down fall trees just downstream of start point along rock wall on right bank. Erosion & bank stability to blame (from high flows?). Some dead trees suspended over brook w/ little woody debris in stream. Flow low, fills ~50% of channel. Habitat levels out half way thru reach, then turns to high gradient w/ steep pools & cascades. Substrate boulder, cobble, gravel & sand, very little silt. Note:seconds on backpack reset itself before they were recorded

Location_Description: Washington Mountain Rd, between dam site
Habitat_Comment: Started at end pont of downstream site. Ended at clearing of the former pond. Flow somewhat low for July, water clear & cool. Boulders, gravel, cobble, & sand. Shaded for most of reach. Woody debris/log jams present at start of reach (likely from Irene flows). Channel is split at start of reach then joins again after ~10m. Habitat is a series of cascades & drop pools. Not as many fish as downstream site. EBT only.

Location_Description: Below dam site, Washington Mountain Rd
Habitat_Comment: Flow decent but low for July, considering we've had no real rain for weeks. Water clear & cool. Good shaded canopy. Substrate is boulders, gravel, cobble w/ sand in pools & slight siltation in pools closer to dam site.~50% of substrate exposed. Flow is good compared to other streams seen lately. The only woody debris present is on banks, probably from high flow events. More fish found than last year's survey at same site.

Location_Description: Reference site, Hoxie Brook Rd, enter through yard at end of cul de sac
Habitat_Comment: Shaded canopy. Good flow for July, though we did have rain this morning. Water clear & cool. Good mix of habitat, pool riffle run. Substrate is boulder, bedrock, gravel, cobble, sand w/ very little if any sediment. Small trees suspended voer brook

Location_Description: Upstream of dam site, downstream of Gilead Rd
Habitat_Comment: Narrower & more high gradient than downstream site. Flow good for July, but we did have rain this AM. Water clear & cool. Mild sediment. Habitat mostly riffles, plunge pools & cascades. Boulder, cobble, gravel & sand substrate. Only last 10m of reach was shaded. Nearby resident said a "posted-private' sign was put up at road xing ~2months ago, asked if it was done by the town. May need to look into that further. *Timer not working properly on shocker

Location_Description: Downstream of dam site, downstream of Gilead Rd
Habitat_Comment: Downed trees at start point. Substrate muddy & rocky, smells like sewage. Substrate more boulder, cobble, gravel & sand further up in reach. Most of reach shaded. Flow is good for July, but it did rain this AM. Clarity is good. Some woody debris for structure throughout the first 2/3 of reach.

Location_Description: Upstream of Flintstone Rd, upstream of dam
Habitat_Comment: Low flow for just but flow is better in this section than downstream. Lack of rain is to blame. Substrates-boulders, gravel, cobble, sand. Variety of habitat including small plunge pools. Would be more riffles if there were more water. Gets higher in gradient toward end of reach. At least 50+% substrate exposed. Low conductivity. Fish were thin & snakey again at this site.

Location_Description: Downstream of Flintstone Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: No water at original start point, had to start upstream a little further. Low flows must have caused brook to run subterrainean. Low flows for July due to lack of rain. Lots of exposed substrate. Small standing pools at start. Water clear. Loose substrate, composed of boulders, gravel, cobble & sand. Very, very few fish! Due to lack of water? Conductivity is very low. No SC caught this year.

Location_Description: Upstream of Flintstone Rd, downstream of dam to culvert
Habitat_Comment: Worked upstream from culvert to dam face. Flow is low for July, lack of rain. Flow better in this section than downstream of Flintstone Rd. Majority of fish caught in pool at foot of dam. Water level in pool is lower than last year's survey. EBT looked very thin & snakey, probably from holding over in dam pool. No SC caught this year.

Location_Description: Upstream of 3rd bridge crossing Savoy Rd
Habitat_Comment: 89m downstream of 4th bridge. Downstream of UNT to Chickley & Brown Brook. Post-Irene. Partly cloudy. Boulder stream mixed w/ cobbles as dominent. Stream is wider than you would have imagined. Canopy is dominated hemlock, yellow birch, w/ some beech & maple. Substrate cobble, boulders, sand, silt. Cool & clear water. No bank sides in survey area. Very limited Irene impact. Tons of brookies!

Location_Description: Upstream of Chapel Rd in K. Debuque State Forest
Habitat_Comment: Repeat following Irene. Looks like some had a lot of time on their hands, made 2 swimming holes in the site. Remnents of a definite high flow event w/ high debris line. Stream dominated by boulders & sand, some silte & cobbles. Site located in a hemlock ravine w/ a foot path on river left. More silt than one would expect. Site located 52m upstream of road.

Location_Description: Downstream of Forge Hill Rd off Rt 8A
Habitat_Comment: Downstream of Forge Hill Rd. least altered section due to outcropping of ledge. Rip-rapped side ~30ft on river right. Some nice deep pools in site caused by ledge outcroppings. One swimming hole in site ~10ft or so. Substrate composed of ledge, cobble & boulder. Canopy cover of yellow birch, ash, hemlock, maple

Location_Description: Along Rt 8A, .5mi North of Pudding Hollow Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpack used. Through channelized section, riffle & run, highly exposed channel. Iron oxidized throughout. Banks, cobble & boulders. Solitary pockets of very small cover. Dominant species are dace

Location_Description: Rt 8A by Hawley DPW
Habitat_Comment: Trenched almost entire reach. One small pool at end of reach knee deep. Low water. Quite a bit of silt. Missed some dace.

Location_Description: Along Rt 8A by Charlemont town line
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. 1st 100' not channelized. Older riprap from previous bridge work. Last 230' obviously channelized by lg equipment. Cobble bottome, one med sized tree down in channel. Algae covering substrate. Some pocket water for hiding spots but overall very little in the way of instream cover or hiding spots. Mostly riffle/run.

waterbody: May Brook (1; UNT to Windsor Reservoir)
Location_Description: 57m downstream of culvert, Control site.
Habitat_Comment: Survey was conducted past leaf drop. More large wood habitat in site than in prev years. Substrate composed of cobble, boulder, sand & leaves. Not too many fish. 2 female EBT were post-spawn! Lots of bank scour on both sides of channel. Canopy cover of beech, maple, ash, yellow birch, poplar, cherry

waterbody: May Brook (1; UNT to Windsor Reservoir)
Location_Description: Downstream of old dam US of Wahconah Falls Rd
Habitat_Comment: Spawning central! Tons of post spawned females & large males. Lots of clean spawning gravel present. Some nice pools w/ hiding spaces

waterbody: May Brook (1; UNT to Windsor Reservoir)
Location_Description: Above dam site, US of Wahconah Falls Rd
Habitat_Comment: Post spawning female brook trout! Some spawning gravel in site. Not as much leave. Some nice pools. Substrate composed of cobble, sand, boulder, gravel & bedrock. Canopy cover comprised of hemlock, beech, maple, ash. Nice woody covered pools.

Location_Description: Off Rt 20, 3 locations for net sets
Habitat_Comment:
Gillnet repeat of efforts from 6/22/12. Secchi disc reading 752cm. Set 1, 42.32866, 73.27225, set at 4:50pm pulled at 8:45pm. Set 2, 42.32448,
73.26557, set at 5:05pm pulled at 9pm. Set 3, 42.32607, 73.27662, set at 5:25pm pulled at 9:20pm.

Location_Description: Upstream of West Mountain Rd, started just US from culvert
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: Upstream from Fred Mason Rd
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. No human influence noticable other than snowmobiel trail. Well vegetated, no evidence of 4 wheelers. There is a dam at downstream/beginning of run sampled.

Location_Description: From confluence with Green River upstream to first bridge
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: At East Hoosac Rd & East Rd downstream corner
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: Upstream from Lincoln St. DEP Station SM03
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Not sure if the killifish was a mummichog. Sampling efficiency poor due to turbidity & stagnantion.

Location_Description: Behind Mobile station, at Sibley St off Rt 20. Upstream of Stony Brook Reservoir between res & RR bridge just upstream
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Riparian vegetation. Both upstream & downstream of railroad crossing was optimal. High flow & leaf litter. Good habtiat given location. Efficiency high. No fish observed that weren't collected.

Location_Description: River St at water quality sampling site, N off River rd ~2200ft E of I-190
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Sampling efficiency poor due to deep fast moving water, 50% or less. Road on right bank entire reach. Boulders for stabilization (old)

Location_Description: Downstream of Boardman Rd
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Tessellated darter also observed, at least 2 seen. Efficiency poor due to high flows, dark water, deep wider section, wide shallow sections. Although some large trout, all appeared to be wild.

Location_Description: Above & below Coney St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: Upstream of Westover Parkway, nearest Leyton Rd
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Great fish habitat. Erosion channel on right bank is definitely a problem

Location_Description: At Hortonvill Rd, upstream
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Fairly low gradient reach. Heavy mosses & color made fish collection difficult. ~50% pickup. High color, moss, leaves affected pH. Darter caught yesterday by bug crew, sp. Not ID'd

Location_Description: Downstream of Rt 118 (south of Rt 44), DS of Moulton St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Very diverse fish habitat from moss to boulders to mixed banks. AE lengths are approx. 1 AE up to 36in observed. Numerous observed, not collected. Darters, numerous observed not collected. Very tough sampling conditions., ~50% pickup.

Location_Description: Downstream of Sharp St, just E of Weymouth townline
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Very good fish habitat in form of old tree snags & undercut banks. Good pools as snags. Overhanging brush.

Location_Description: @ most northernly Cushing St xing
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Note that reach is between public road & private road. Shallow riffle run, no real deep pools. 90+% pickup, excellent.

Location_Description: Just US of Stagecoach Rd
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. This is a small stream running through a large, medium-density development. Appears to flood. Mostly low gradient stretch. Riffles run near road. Pick up low in lower part of reach. Better in upper half, near 100%. Low gradient, sandy in lower section.

Location_Description: At Elm St at cemetary
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: Downstream of Quinaquisset Ave & Rt 28 xing
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Heavily vegetated (submerged) islands of plants made for braided stream. Very low efficiency due to plants & stream width/depth (wide & fast).

Location_Description: Just US of Rt 151 crossing
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. A number of "herring" were caught but not positively ID'd. Hurley believes these were Alewives not herring but tough to tell. Lenghts & numbers were not entered in LF data.

Location_Description: ~50m DS of Delaney St. DEP station MA09A-180
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Barge & Backpack used, but effort & fish not seperated by method. 2 datasets included for "upper" & "lower" Elizabeth Br. "Lower" HabAssess data entered, "upper reach" unable to be entered. Lower reach: not much flow, mostly standing water. Upper reach: mostly cobble substrate, higher gradient, 2 channels, no water or little water. Mussels abundant. No water left channel, little water right channel.

Location_Description: 0.4mi DS of Jones Hill Rd, DEP station MA09A-101
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Sampling efficiency fair-poor

Location_Description: ~175ft US of North St, DEP station MAP2-033
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Hay field on left w/ small buffer strip. Some exposed beds, especially at meanders.

Location_Description: 0.8mi US of Rt 2E on-ramp (Holtshire Rd). Access off filration plant access rd. DEP station MAP2-049
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Sand w/ ground water flow. Flow on one braid. Not sure what it is. Few add'l lampreys seen but not collected

Location_Description: ~440ft DS of Gulf Rd
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Upper half reach higher quality than lower reach. Riffles more prevelant in upper reach than lower.

Location_Description: Downstream Tully Rd, nearest Creamery Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: DEP barge survey. Fair efficiency shocking

Location_Description: ~140ft US of Manning St. DEP station TR01
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey

Location_Description: ~160ft US of Rt 190 xing. DEP station MAP2-071
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Shallow riffles predominant but also some nice pools, runs & undercut banks provide good habitat. Riffles & runs provide habitat for dace. Shock efficiency fine. Many BND seen but not captured. Missed a few trout as well.

Location_Description: ~700ft US of River Rd. DEP station MAP2-060
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Lots of large brook trout. Some definitely native, some likely stocked. Missed a number of darters.

Location_Description: Douglas State Forest, 300ft DS of footbridge on eastern extension of High St. DEP reference site RB01
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: 0.4mi US of May Brook Rd. DEP reference site BB01
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Time not recorded, was ~1200+ sec.

Location_Description: ~160ft DS of Kentfield Rd, DEP reference site WB01
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Road along entire right bank. Most fish caught, highest efficiency. A few EBT missed (~3-4).

Location_Description: 0.85mi US of S. Athol Rd, next to golf course. DEP station MAP2-045
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: US of Dennison Cross Rd, near water pump station. DEP station MAP2-075
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.Efficiency fair due to high water levels. Many YOY BND seen, not captured, along w/ a few other EBT. EBT appear to be native

Location_Description: ~510ft DS of Old Stafford Rd. DEP station MAP2-031
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Great clarity for 4 day post-Irene. Efficiency only fair due to high flow. 4 days post-Irene. 3-4add'l EBT seen but not collected

Location_Description: @ Quinebaug R confluence. DEP station MAP2-027
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: ~275ft US of Beech Hill Rd. DEP reference site PB01
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. First 60m riffle, run, pool. Last 30m ledge plunge pool w/ 3 large pools. Most generalists caught in uppermost pools

Location_Description: Sanderson Brook Rd crossing nearest Rt 20. DEP station SB01
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Lower end of reach is fire road on Rt 20. Left riparian zone has parking area. Irene came through, VERY high flows.

Location_Description: ~640ft US of Cooleyville Rd. DEP reference site WSR01
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: 1mi DS of CT state line. DEP station MAP2-015
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Wondering run through old beaver flowage. Habitat is snags & vegetation. Trout were native. Efficiency good.

Location_Description: Downstream of Mill Road Crossing
Habitat_Comment: wide channel, some overhang, gravelly bottom

Location_Description: Downstream of Route 28
Habitat_Comment: slow curent, deep pools in sharp bends only.  Some pools 4 or 5 feet deep.  More overhanging vegetation and organic sediment  than sample #1

Location_Description: Upstream of Route 28
Habitat_Comment: sand/silt bottom, well shaded, mostly straight stretch with a few deep scour pools 15-10 foot wide reach.

Location_Description: Upstream of powerline off Park Street West
Habitat_Comment: narrow channel, overhanging banks, root wads, more current than previous samples

Location_Description: Guaging Station to Main Street
Habitat_Comment: very wide stretch, mostly shallow, both banks vegetated, sand/gravel bottom, silt/detritus in pools, one big, deep pool skipped, fairly straight stretch

Location_Description: Downstream of Chestnut Street (Access off Route 62 park)
Habitat_Comment: Some shallow pools but at least half the stretch was riffles and large boulders.  Godd canopy on both banks

Location_Description: Downstream of Martins Brook junction
Habitat_Comment: Meadow reach, few bends

Location_Description: Main Street upstream to Bostich Dam
Habitat_Comment: Riffle and pool section below dam to Main Street.  Large rock riffles, rock and gravel pools, banks lined with imature forest. Overstory shades most of the reach.

Location_Description: Burley's Corner

There is no LF for the 600 second run since there were no fish.  The seconds are also not included in the seconds total in the boat shocker effort. Actual shoreline shocked is indicated on a pond map in the pond file.

Location_Description: DS of Central St bridge to just US
Habitat_Comment: High flow from rain/storm prev day. Only shocked E bank of river. Along W bank was deep & possibly scoured. Missed some fish, eels, pickerel, sunfish. Few fish shocked. Deep run w/ sandy, rocky substrate. Dark water, slight siltation. Some vegetation. W bank steep from RR tracks. Overgrown on E bank. Shocked up past bridge by 5m. Could not do full 100m, too fast & deep w/ 1 bkpk.

Location_Description: downstream from Stevens St Dam (Marland Pl. Dam)
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Shocked up to bridge below dam. Channelized w/ stone wall lineing both banks (~4-5' H), boulders, sandy substrate w/ some silt. Tannic water. Good flow, high flow, fast water. Lost some eels.lots of eels found & some juv SL, missed some towards end (slipped thru nets). R bank (facing US) deeper than L. river bordered by condo complex w/ landscaped lawns on L bank, condos on R

Location_Description: DS of South St xing
Habitat_Comment: Only one fish. Shocked up to xing. RP found in last 50'. Sm stone arch culvert ~2-3'. Stream runs near RR tracks. Slightly overgrown banks w/ shrubs growing over strm in spots. Sandy, gravel substrate. Purpose of survey was to get pictures of fish for Fish ID Key.

Location_Description: DS of Willis Rd bridge xing
Habitat_Comment: Started survey below trail bridge, worked up to stone bridge @ Willis Rd. Water very tannic, decent flow, but only 2 fish! Boulder, cobble substrate. Salamander & few frogs shocked. In between 2 beaver swamp. Upstream of 1K Acre Pond Dam. Old stone wall along left bank to bridge (wooden), then right bank to stone bridge (Willis Rd). Stone foundation to old mill @ stone bridge. Riparian & canopy in good shape & stream well shaded. WQ issues from res. draw-down or increased temps from the # of beaver ponds causing lack of fish &/or isolated nature of stream (high gradient- natural barrier to fish passage)

Location_Description: Moroney Rd xing US of Rt 140
Habitat_Comment: Silty, low flow, shallow. Moss & vegetation on rocks. Cobble, sand, boulder substrate. Good shaded canopy. Large blowdown @ end of sample reach. Water cloudy (white, not tannic) near road xing. Pool @ DS side of xing, w/ cloudy deep water. Old rock barrier built across stream ~10m from Rd. survey done as a trainig demo for Salmon Seasonals

Location_Description: DS Firecut Ln
Habitat_Comment: Sample requested by Sudbury to check for coldwater spp. Stream riparian swampy w/ deep mud & stream braided throughout. Sampled main channel, some large sand/gravel bars below culvert may be road run-off? Skipped 10-15m section of stream due to swampiness. House close to RB, otherwise riparian area & canopy good.

Location_Description: DS of Bent Rd
Habitat_Comment: Sample requested by Sudbury group to check for coldwater species. US of Bent Rd, ponded & swampy. In residential area but stream was forested riparian & canopy (<10m on RB). Sandy gravel substrate w/ detrital/leaf matter. Woody debris in stream channel. Habitat complexity present (pools, runs, riffle, undercut banks, exposed root wads, etc).

Location_Description: Sandisfield State Forest
Habitat_Comment: Partially cloudy. Wind flowing north. Dark water. Nice structure from submerged root wads, along pond shore line. Interesting fish community, comprised mainly of small white suckers, minnows, & pumpkiseeds

Location_Description: Pittsfield State Forest, off Berry Pond Circuit Rd
Habitat_Comment: Nice edge vegetation. Presence of pumpkinseed red & yellow perch eggs. Sediment is softer towards the east. Slight wind flowing southwest. Sunny day.

Location_Description: October Mtn. State Forest
Habitat_Comment: Overcast w/ mist. Water is dark with limited visibility. Pond is shallow with numerous submerged tree stumps. Healthy & abundant yellow perch population. Scale samples attached to data sheets.

Location_Description: Dirt rd access off Leonhardt Rd - October Mtn State Forest
Habitat_Comment: Spawning redds present. Overcase day with dark water. Limited aquatic vegetation present. Difficult to launch boat

Location_Description: Lake Mansfield Rd
Habitat_Comment: Partly cloudy but mostly sunny. Wind blowing east to southeast. Vegetation around edge of pon. Mucky bottom w/ occasional boulders along the edge. Lesions present on bullheads.

Location_Description: Launched from Daughters of the Amer. Revolutioin State Park
Habitat_Comment: Brown bullhead also present! Partly cloudy. Some technical problems with shock equipment on 2nd pass. Nice aquatic vegetation. Found golden shiners by the dam site. Clear water, easy to see bottom. Spawning redds present for sunfish spp.

Location_Description: Daughters of the American Revolution State Forest
Habitat_Comment: Very foggy, intermittent rain showers. Water is dark & difficult to see fish, may improve with sun. Hard to capture fish with low conductivity. Nice structure along edges of pool from large trees.

Location_Description: West St - Sandisfield State Forest
Habitat_Comment: Could not complete third pass due to problems with 4-stroke engine. Several large colonies of redds dominated by bluegills & pumpkinseed. High wind moving southeast. Warm day, partly cloudy

Location_Description: off Rt 116/Windsor Pond Rd - Windsor State Forest
Habitat_Comment: Very hot day - poor return for sampling. Only saw 1 redd. Boat mainly moving fish out of the way. Very limited aquatic vegetation. Hardly any habitat structure available for fish. Desert like. Observed 4 banded killifish in shore.

Location_Description: access in Veterans Park off Treble Cove Rd.
Habitat_Comment: Selective pickup run from SID 2572. Pickup for LMB. Refer to SID 2572 for remander of comments.

Location_Description: Pine St crossing N (US) ~400' S of Birchwood Dr
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 1 TMT found - 85 (vouchered). 2 AE 460 & 630. Crayfish present. Flow higher than normal (recent rains)

Location_Description: New Boston Rd xing South. West of Royalston Rd south
Habitat_Comment: Barge w/ crew of 7. 1 TT collected 342mm. Sampled up to crossing. Lg crayfish w/ slime on bodies

Location_Description: Donnelly Cross Rd downstream
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed between Donnelly Cross Rd downstream to Sugden Reservoir. Lots of crayfish & frogs.

Location_Description: Bond Rd downstream (north)
Habitat_Comment: Stream impounded by beaver activity directly downstream at river/road crossing. Most fish came from downstream of survey. Debris blocking a lot of river flow on top.

Location_Description: West St crossing, E of West St cemetary
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Sampled short section due to beaver issues (dams & deep silty water) 2 fish: 1-CP, & 1 BB

waterbody: UNT to UNT to East Branch Swift River
Location_Description: Dugway Rd crossing, E of Quabbin Gate
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Multiple sm beaver impoundment. Very silty bottom. BND 100% of fish found. Found unusual salamander (took picture & released)

Location_Description: US of D. Whitney Rd crossing, W of Bernard Whitney Rd
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Warmwater species. All fish @ plunge pool.

Location_Description: Plains Rd crossing (Rt 67) ~1/2mi S of Ravine Rd
Habitat_Comment: 1 GS 103mm.

Location_Description: off Channock Hill Rd, Rail Trail crossing
Habitat_Comment: Sampled upstream from rail-trail crossing. Area was a beaver pond 1-2 years ago. Some mud & siltation. Numerous crayfish present.

Location_Description: Channock Hill Rd @ pond & gris mill, downstream
Habitat_Comment: Downstream from Mill Pond/Gris Mill. Between large waterfalls only BND found. Sampled pool below lower falls, all other fish from here including large CS.

Location_Description: Hale Rd xing, DS
Habitat_Comment: Very nice habitat (visually), plenty of water/flow. Plenty of crayfish, only 2 BB in entire stretch. Water has "swamp" odor, very tannic. Large boulders, pools, riffles; some pools 4' deep.

Location_Description: US of Summer St (Alitto Valito Nature Park)
Habitat_Comment: Barge w/ crew of 5. warm water species only. 2 lamprey found

Location_Description: Elm St xing downstream SE of Horse Farm
Habitat_Comment: Double backpacks. Had to replace battery on one backpacks approx. 80% through survey. Warmwater species only. Crayfish present

Location_Description: Gravel pit crossing, off Elm St
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks w/ rat tails. Sampled up to bridge crossing. Crayfish present. warmwater species only.

Location_Description: @ end of Brookside Dr crossing
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 4 fish found: 1 CP & 3 BB. No voucher taken. Brook very tannic w/ drop down pools. Nice brook - lack of fish found.

Location_Description: Wheeler St crossing
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Sampled area below Cower (Mamjohn) Pond. Warmwater species only. Frogs present. Tannic water

Location_Description: E. Rindge Rd crossing E
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 12 CP found & released. Very tannic water. Surveyed between 2 ponds; 1 natural & 1 beaver impoundmen

Location_Description: Betty Spring Rd crossing S
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 2 fish found BB & CP. No voucher bottle. Very tannic water

Location_Description: Prescott St downstream, parallel to RR tracks
Habitat_Comment: Water flowing very fast

Location_Description: Fairbanks Street upstream
Habitat_Comment: YB found only 128 & 132.

Location_Description: Stone Rd xing downstream, N of Winchendon Rd
Habitat_Comment: Man-made pool at lowest point. Deepest point @ 40 inches. Plunge pools at downstream side of road, containe only bullhead.

Location_Description: Winchendon Rd at Norcross Rd downstream
Habitat_Comment: Downstream crossing, led into beaver swamp. Directly upstream was impounded by beaver activity (dam). This was chosen because priority site #2 was now beaver bog.

Location_Description: Carroll Ave intersection US
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/rattail. No voucher collected. 12 WS only. Crayfish present

Location_Description: W. Main St crossing N
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ 2 probes. High water flow (recent rains). 4 fish collected 3 GS & 1 CP. Area looked like old mill site. Deep corner pool - fish found.

Location_Description: Main St crossing S
Habitat_Comment: Backpacks w/ 2 probes. High flow - recent rains. Good visibility. 2 fish collected. CP-82 & BB-127

Location_Description: Westboro St crossing S, W of Summet Brook xing
Habitat_Comment: Backpack. Water cloudy due to rain on 7/1. Possibly missed fish due to disturbed water.

Location_Description: Rt 30 crossing E
Habitat_Comment: Backpack. Sampled area below dam. Crayfish present. High flow due to recent rains. Used 1 sampled bottle for 2 sites.

Location_Description: @ end of Johnson Rd, US of Swans Pond
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Sampled pools only (lack of water). Looks to dry up in summer months. 2 TD found (45 & 48)

Location_Description: 122A & Naquag St downstream
Habitat_Comment: All fish found in plunge pool @ culvert of 112A

Location_Description: Causeay St- Downstream. <0.2mi W of Claire Ln
Habitat_Comment: Duckweed. Plunge pool at road crossing

Location_Description: Carleton Rd crossing S
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 1 fish - CS 40mm. Crayfish present

Location_Description: Off Ireland Rd, near Rt 112
Habitat_Comment: ~75m below Ireland Rd culvert. Top of site at scour pool immediately above out cropping of bedrock/ledge. Top of site is also below 'island'. Water is very tanic & difficult to see bottom. Substrate contains numerous angular boulders gravel & cobble, some sand & pebbles in pools.

Location_Description: Off of New Marlboro Rd, US of Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Soft substrate and tannic water coming out of pond. Fish species dominated by minnow population. Stream appears to down cutting due to old stone dams down stream. Substrate composed of sand, silt, gravel, pebble, and cobble. Flow is higher from previous days rain. Sunny with some clouds

Location_Description: Cobble Brook Rd xing US
Habitat_Comment: Site starts approx. 30m upstream of the Cobble Brook Rd xing. Stream bed is dark & covered in dark moss. Very few fish. Lots of crayfish & frogs. Substrate is composed of cobble, boulder, sand, & gravel.

Location_Description: Country Rd xing downstream of culvert to confluence
Habitat_Comment: Large CRC have dorsal legions. Substrate is very, very, very dark. Water is not tannic, but dark  organic material has settled. Substrate is composed of sand & cobble with some boulder.

Location_Description: Middle St - Amherst Conservation Land - KC Trail
Habitat_Comment: Muddy, sandy bottom. Multiflora rose - difficult to survey. Pond just upstream of where surveyed.

Location_Description: Amherst Rd - DS of Hawley Reservoir
Habitat_Comment: Looked nice but only GS & WS sampled

Location_Description: Rt 116 xing, N of Glendale Rd
Habitat_Comment: Lot of ag run off, swamp to swamp. Vouchered fish had white tumors (except CM)

Location_Description: Tully Rd - upstream of bridge, 0.7mi N of Royalston Rd
Habitat_Comment: Sandy bottom, tea water. Lack of fish -dead zone? Silt. Probably could use barge or 2 units.

Location_Description: Flagg Rd xing, off Tully Rd
Habitat_Comment: Low water - difficult to see, walk stream

Location_Description: Lake Pleasant Rd, US
Habitat_Comment: Tires. Vouchered WS had no tail (tail was dismembered & healed).

Location_Description: Downstream Rt 7
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: Outlet of Onota Lake (Exact location estimated with coordinates)
Habitat_Comment: Conductivity too high for representative sample in survey area. Beaver presence noted. Coordinates for location are estimated, specific sample site not documented.

Location_Description: Roylston Rd (way in past first brook-UNT)
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed directly above falls (snowmobile bridge crossing) follow trail leading out of Millers River WMA lot (Royalston Rd) past first brook (UNT) to bridge crossing

Location_Description: 101 Old Courthouse Rd, 1/2 way between Scotchmans Rd & Vineyard Have Rd, @ sm pond
101 Courthouse Rd, DS of pond site
101 Old Courthouse Rd, US of pond site
Wachusett Mtn off Echo Lake Rd
Habitat_Comment: Rod & reel during gillnetting survey, done same day/same place. Gill net sample= Sample ID 2209

Location_Description: off Thompson Rd, E of Radio Tower
Habitat_Comment: Sm pond. Rod & reel done during gillnet survey of same day (SID 2210)

Location_Description: Below (DS) Tompson Dr/Talbot Way
Habitat_Comment: Heavy silt, slow moving, yard clearing close to riparian zone.

Location_Description: Cobblestone Ln above (US)
Habitat_Comment: Close to houses, stream bed gravel. Good water flow

Location_Description: Above South Main St (East)
Habitat_Comment: Bridge replaced 2003. Pool above road, then narrow gravel & sand, cobble dam 168'. Frog, ~10 crayfish, pooled above dam. Mowed on N side. Missed numerous eels especially small ones. WP 42-44.

Location_Description: West St above (N)
Habitat_Comment: Clearing up to stream bank, stream bed gravel, very little sediment.

Location_Description: Above Old Kings Highway (east)
Habitat_Comment: WP 149-150. Pooled above culvert on dirt road called Old Kings Highway. Took photo of box turtle on bank.

Location_Description: Below North Main St (DS). From culvert to N. Main St
Habitat_Comment: missed about 10 eels. Clear water. Salamanders present. Bottom sand & cobble, large conglomerate boulders. Fish passage blocked by culvert above RR. Potential for restoration with railroad. From culvert to North Main St

Location_Description: Below Old Kings Highway
Habitat_Comment: *No LF Sheet. 5 eels (~280-340) in stream sample. 2' muck over sand. 1 LMB yoy & eels along pond edge. No water above Old Kings Highway. Very short free flowing shallow area. Former salter brook trout stream, now ponded due to collapsed culvert under bike trail.

Location_Description: Above & below Spring Bars Road (Randolph St)
Habitat_Comment: *No LF Sheet. About 10 american eels 100-400mm. Behind Falmouth Mall. Large silt deposits, overhanging brush & briars. Trees block access.

Location_Description: Below Pine Hill Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Fenced off pasture. Multiflora rose. Cobbles & boulders. Steep evidence of higher flows

Location_Description: Below Old Kings Highway xing, S of Black Pond Rd
Habitat_Comment: Small water flow within sand bottom channel. Cleared of most wood by herring wardens. Sampled to see if different than upstream pooled section. Pickerel frogs & 1 crayfish observed

Location_Description: MP 2.39, off Elm Street DS
Habitat_Comment: Primarily sand/mud, some gravel. Pool/riffle, deep pools, good cover.

Location_Description: off Rockwood Pond St xing, MP 6.03. @ powerlines xing
Habitat_Comment: Silt, mud. Low flow. Ponded

Location_Description: MP 6.9, Access from Stanhope Dr (30 Stanhope)
Habitat_Comment: Very low flows, minor fish habitat. Watercress present at crossing

Location_Description: MP 10.76, (downstream) off of South Street xing, US of powerlines
Habitat_Comment: pool/riffle/run, back water. Silt/gravel/cobble/muck. Unit working great. Missed only a few fish. A lot of crayfish.

Location_Description: From Rt 1 Executive Suites. MP 11.7. US of School Meadow Br confluence
Habitat_Comment: Sand/mud. Many stickes on the bottom. Run/riffle. Below pond outfall.

Location_Description: East of Westdale Rd, I-10 MP 7.19. @ powerline xing
Habitat_Comment: Pool, silt mud. Riffle. Silt & minor habitat. SARIS based on ArcGIS, not by topo.

Location_Description: Mill St, MBTA row. I-10 MP 7.78. between Mill St & Centre St
Habitat_Comment: 50% pools, boulders, sand. 50% riffle, rubble, gravel. Out of reservoir.

Location_Description: off of Union St/Truelson Dr, I-10 MP 8.12. US of Union St
Habitat_Comment: ~3' ditch, not flowing. Mostly pool. Maybe 10% riffle. Mud/sand/gravel. Vertical banks w/ overhanging shrubs.

Location_Description: off of Mack Driver DS. I-10 MP 9.45. @ powerline xing
Habitat_Comment: Polluted. Silt, mud bottom. High iron content. Few pools

Location_Description: MP 12.5, off of Washington St, W of gravel pits
Habitat_Comment: High gradient. Pools. Silt, boulders. Riffle, boulder bedrock. Below small pond

Location_Description: MP 12.86, off of Pleasant St, NW of Wardwell Rd
Habitat_Comment: very low flow. Pools-stone, gravel. Riffles- rubble.

Location_Description: Access road off amtrack. 1st trib crossing from rd (Canton St)
Habitat_Comment: Sand, a little gravel. Run/pool. Overhanging vegetation

Location_Description: Ponded backwater area off Amtrack access rd, MP 16.14
Habitat_Comment: backwater, mud/muck. Highly vegetated elodea

Location_Description: Stream channel off Amtrack access rd. MP 16.14
Habitat_Comment: Run, silt/sand. A little grave, a few boulders. A lot of crayfish. Sampel 2 off Massapoag Brook

Location_Description: MP 17.22, near (West of) Greenbrook Drive, where powerlines cross stream
MP 17.4, off of Greenbrook Drive (upstream)
Habitat_Comment: Pool/riffle habitat. Gravel, rubble.

Location_Description: above & below Main St xing, on W side of Dunstable
Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by outside party w/ collection permit. Genetic study for BM. # of seine hauls varied w/ habitat. They seined until they got the right # of fish or gave up. Data is more presence/absence than rel. abundance. WCS-2670

Location_Description: @ Old Meetinghouse Rd, above (W of) Harbor Pond. 1.4 air miles SE center of Townsend
Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by outside party w/ collection permit. Genetic study for BM. # of seine hauls varied w/ habitat. Seined until they got the right # of fish or gave up. Data is more presence/absence than rel. abundance. WCS-2671

Location_Description: at MA 68 & boat launch site by River Rd, 8.5 air miles SSW of Westiminster
Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by outside party w/ collection permit. Genetic study for BM. # seine hauls varied w/ habitat. Siened until they got the right # of fish or gave up. Data is more presence/absence than rel. abundance. WCS-2673

Location_Description: below Ed Jones Rd & Hayden Pond. 13.1 air miles ENE Great Barrington
Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by outside party w/ collection permit. Genetic study for BM. # seine hauls varies w/ habitat. They seined until they got the right # of fish or gave up. Data is more presence/absence than relative abundance. WCS-2674

Location_Description: along E side of Hawthorne/Mahkeenac Lake Rd, 8.4 air miles SSW of Pittsfield
Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by outside party w/ collection permit. Genetic study for BM. # seine hauls varied w/ habitat. They seined until they got the right # of fish or gave up. Data is more presence/absence than relative abundance. WCS-2675

Location_Description: Middle Basin, Launched from ramp @ Point Grove Rd
Habitat_Comment: Large schools LMB fry. Small LMB w/ good condition factor. Big BB. Alewife present. Abundant aq veg. in coves. Girth measured on LMB over 150mm. Selective pickups for bass. Separate runs were not distinguished on LF sheets.

Location_Description: Reach 3 above Long Pond Rd, in Southern-most bog
Habitat_Comment: spot check with backpack from sides. Cranberry bog channel. Heavy silt. Unable to wade. BM found. Some eels shocked, only one vouchered.

Location_Description: upper most (Southern most) bog above Long Pond Rd
Habitat_Comment: Triple pass of uppermost bog. 3 runs conducted. No fish caught in 3rd run.

Location_Description: Reach 2, upper bogs above Long Pond Rd (2nd furthest south bog)
Habitat_Comment: Triple pass samples.

Location_Description: upper bogs above Long Pond Rd (2nd furthest South bog)
Habitat_Comment: Triple pass samples of upper bogs

Location_Description: Below S. Main St xing, DS
Habitat_Comment: Cobble & boulder. Deep pool below road. Fish passage barrier. Grey water high conductivity. Few crayfish, salamanders

Location_Description: "HR-2" site, US of Mill Br confl. DS of New Lenox Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: 3 surveys done at this site (SID 2838, 2839, 2840). Selective Pickup of species LMB, YP, B  for PCB testing by Arcadis. See attached sheets.

Location_Description: "HR-2" site, US of Mill Br confl, DS of New Lenox Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: One of 3 surveys done at this site. Selective pickup of B for PCB testing by Arcadis. See attached sheets

Habitat_Comment: One of 3 surveys at this site. Selective pickup of B for PCB testing by Arcadis. See attached sheets.

Habitat_Comment: Selective pickup of LMB, YB, B for PCB testing. Survey done by Arcadis. See attached sheets for details.

Habitat_Comment: 2 surveys @ this site (SID 2844 & 2845). Selective pickup of LMB for PCB testing. See attached sheets for details. Surveys by Arcadis.

Habitat_Comment: 2 surveys @ this site. Selective pickup of LMB for PCB testing. See attached sheets for details. Surveys done by Arcadis.

Location_Description: off Woodland Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 surveys conducted on Woods Pond. *see attached letter for details *. Selective pickup of adult LMB for PCB testing. Data submitted by Arcadis.

Location_Description: Station "Rising Pond" on Housatonic R
Habitat_Comment: 3 surveys @ site (SID 2847, 2848, 2849). All selective pickup of adult LMB for PCB testing. Day survey. See attached sheets for details.

Location_Description: Station "Rising Pond" on Housatonic R
Habitat_Comment: 3 surveys @ site. Selective pickup for adult LMB for PCB testing. Night survey. See attached sheets for details.

Location_Description: Station "Rising Pond" on Housatonic R
Habitat_Comment: 3 surveys @ site. Selective pickup of adult LMB for PCB testing. Day survey. See attached sheets for details.

Location_Description: Upstream of Sleepy Hollow Rd
Habitat_Comment: Low gradient stream with dark substrate. Riparian area dominated by ash, alder & sugar maple. Started the site upstream of the six strand barb wire fence. Upstream of road culvert. 10m of stream was diverted off for water cattle crossing. Looks historic.

Location_Description: Downstream of Tamarack Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Started shocking downstream of rd & worked US to ~30m from rd xing. Low gradient, well shaded stream. Wetland upstream of W. Mountain Rd/DS of site. High conductivity. Meandering stream. Lots of bends, undercut banks w/ woody debris. Slight siltation, mostly cobble, gravel, sand substrate. Veg over stream in some places. Root wads present. Frogs & red efts present. Stream splits, took main channel. Other channel dry up ~40m up.

Location_Description: US of Jason St xing ~15m
Habitat_Comment: Shocked US of Rd xing ~15m. Good flow, water slightly murky in spots. Lot of woody debris. Some overgrowth of shrubs over brook. Mostly runs, some pools & riffles. Siltation present in pools & runs. Substrate boulder, cobble, gravel, sand & mud. Decent canopy. Found sm makeshift minnow holding basket-removed from stream, blocking flow.Mostly warmwater species.

Location_Description: DS of Moorewood Lake, from RR tracks to Hous. Confluence
Habitat_Comment: Started shocking @ Housatonic R confluence up to below RR tracks. Wide, muddy, silty, aq vegetation. Fallen trees (big), lots of woody debris. Substrate-mud & sand. Site wide open, lined w/ veg. No real shad. Deep  pools & runs. Muddy banks.

Location_Description: DS of Pond, used private rd from American Institute Economic Research
Habitat_Comment: Upstream of small pond off of Division St in AIER's property & immediately downstream of confluence. Substrate is composed of cobble, gravel, boulder, & sand. Overstory dominated by hemlock & sugar maple. Water is up from previous day's rain.

Location_Description: upstream of Brewer Hill Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Started ~20m upstream of a culvert (culvert did not appear to be affecting stream pattern). About 50/50 under canopy or clear spots, all banks had vegetation. Pools w/ gravel. Sand substrate some cobble rock, rest of stream cobble rock, boulder. 3 sharp bends, rest of meander slight. Little to no LWD. Riparian disturbed in past.

Location_Description: US of Sawmill Rd xing (off Yale Hill Rd), ~20m
Habitat_Comment: Shocked US of resident driveway/rd, US of cascades. Shocked only 90m b/c of dam! Shocked up to base of dam. Higher flows. Water slightly tannic. Dark substrate-made fish hard to see. Boulder, cobble, gravel substrate w/ sand & silt present. 2 lg boulders 1/2 way thru split the channel (1 channel flows under 1 boulder). Canopy decent. Runs along road for a bit but still has shade. Moss covered rocks. Frogs present. Missed some fish due to difficulty seeing & flows. Woody debris present. P found near dam. Dam 5.5-6' high, 42.28511 73.29781.

Location_Description: US of East St xing
Habitat_Comment: Started shocking ~75m up from rd xing. Stream runs along backyard of residence w/ stone wall lining stream bank. Mostly large deep bend pools & deep runs. A few riffles early on. Water tannic w/ good flow. Few fish for the section. Missed a few. Mostly gravel, cobble & sand substrate w/ silt. Some boulders present. Some woody debris present. Canopy cover decent w/ yards nearby. Frogs present. Occasional undercutting beneath tree roots.

Location_Description: DS of Rattlesnake Hill Rd xing ~30m
Habitat_Comment: Sampled DS of rd xing b/c of beaver swamp on US side. Culvert perched ~6". High grad. Lots of exposed bedrock. Stream runs thru/over bedrock. Cascades, plunge pools, deep crevas pools & riffles over rocks. Some woody debris present w/ fallen tree. Good canopy. Water clear but sediment present, esp. in pools. Some gravel, cobble, sand & mud present. Rocks moss-covered. Occasional bend pools in DS section. One lg cascade thru crevas @ 75m. Water flows under bedrock slabs in spots.

Location_Description: Site downstream of Bow Wow Rd
Habitat_Comment: Crew cont'd:Morris-Siegel, Ohman. More of a prominent channel was present at Bow Wow Rd. Work up to Bow Wow Rd corssing. Substrate composed of sand, silt, gravel & occasional cobble & boulder. Stream channel is in a wetland. Mostly shrub overstory. Sunny hazy day.

Location_Description: Along Rt 23/41, behind convience store/restaurant, 500' E of Baldwin Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 Backpacks. Worked from just DS of stores up to foot bridge. Measuring tape broke at end of reach, but length should be fairly accurate. High flow from prev. day's rain. Raining. Channelized lined w/ stone walls on both sides in last 50m. Boulder, gravel, sand substrate w/ boulder too. Canopy ok. Store rear on right bank (facing US). Water slightly cloudy b/c of rains. Missed some fish b/c of flows.

Location_Description: Access off of Rt 102 W. Stockbridge, Crane Lake Camp
Habitat_Comment: Lots of redds present on the camp side of shore. Deep drop of near I-90 side of lake. High diversity of aquatic vegetation with some invasives present. Nice surrounding wetland vegetation. Overall fish do not have any lesions.

Location_Description: Off of Pelham Lake Park
Habitat_Comment: Overcast day. Majority of bass caught in sunken tree on pass 3 and the deeper section of pass 1. The 2nd pass was rather desert like & very shallow. Pumpinseed redds present near the north side of the pond & near Pelham Lake beach.

Location_Description: Boat launch off Bush Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Yellow perch in the 80-90mm size class range had numerous yellow grub infections. Lots of pond weeds throughout entire pond. Shallow for the majority. Difficult to get close to edge. Third pass saw tons of sunfish redds honeycombed throughout the pass.

Location_Description: Off of boat launch DCR
Habitat_Comment: Pass 1 lots of debris from ice storm with trees in water. Pass 2 Nice redbreast sunfish-only found in pass 2. Pass 3- amazing submerged tree root/stump habitat.

Location_Description: Launched off of West Corner Rd
Habitat_Comment: Interesting little pond. Pass 1 had numerous submerged logs & stumps but few fish. Pass 2 had a number of spawning redds. Pass 3 had the yellow perch & black crappie on the east side of the shore.

Location_Description: Chain fenced in gated road off of East Otis Rd
Habitat_Comment: Pass 1 very few fish some aquatic vegetatino & shallow. Pass 2 numerous dead standing & down trees. Pass 3 redds were observed near the shore line. Overall water was very tanic & the color of Coke.

Location_Description: Lower site US of 2nd bridge xing for Poland Br on N. Poland Rd
Habitat_Comment: First 100' of site now all sand, only a few dace.

Location_Description: Launched @ Admin Bldg, Windsor Dam
Habitat_Comment: Set nets from 4:15-9:30pm. Set 3 nets @ a time. Lake trout tagging, also caught LLS, SMB, RB. Caught 2 floy tagged LT. Nets set diagonal to dam. Weather-little chilly, fairly calm w/ slight breeze. Air temp hi 30s-low 40s. All weights incl bucket wt (950g)

Location_Description: Windsor Dam, Launched @ Admin Bldg
Habitat_Comment: Set nets between 1-7pm. Set 3-4 nets on 1st run, then 2 nets connected for remainder of evening. Also caught 1 RT, 1 LLs, & several large SMB. Nets set along dam. Weather nice, calm warm. Air temp high 40s, flat water. All fish weights incl bucket wt (950g)

Location_Description: Windsor Dam, launched @ Admin Bldg
Habitat_Comment: Lake trout tagging. Also caught LLS, SMB, & RB in low 3s. No floy tagged lakers caught. Tied two experimental gill nets together & set diagonal to dam. Set b/w 4:30-7:30pm. Weather nice, light wind. Air temp in low 30s. Most fish caught in last set. All fish weights inc bucket wt (950)

Location_Description: Windsor Dam
Habitat_Comment: Very few fish (LT) caught. LT given to Jen Ayer for VHS Testing. (No fish were tagged) Only 1 tagged fish recaptured, then released. Started setting nets in afternoon until 8pm. No fish caught in last set. All wts do NOT include bucket wt.

Location_Description: Windsor Dam
Habitat_Comment: Set nets for few hrs in evening (4:30-10:15pm) until dark. Very fel LT caught. A few still had some eggs. Fish sacrificed & given to Jen Ayer @ McLaughlin for VHS testing (no LT were tagged). Started setting nets @ 4pm until 10pm.  Only 1 prev. tagged fish caught.

Location_Description: Windsor Dam
Habitat_Comment: Fished ~5-8pm & got only 2 LT, 6 LLS, 25 SMB

Location_Description: Windsor Dam
Habitat_Comment: Sampled 5:30-9:45pm. 3 runs condcuted w/ 1 net ea. Stopped sampling early due to low battery on tag reader. Very windy, made setting of nets difficult (w/ choppy water). Only 1 set @ a time. Set mostly on Northern 1/3 of dam. 2 recaps & 1 floy tagged captured.

Location_Description: Windsor Dam
Habitat_Comment: Runs not shown on LF sheet. 3 morts, 1 recapture (0699-1161).. Fish wts include bucket wt (950g)

Location_Description: Windsor Dam
Habitat_Comment: 5 runs completed. Gillnetting from dusk til after dark for LT

Location_Description: Depot St crossing, DS of Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Sampled area E of crossing. Very few fish collected. Crayfish present. 2 species caught, BND & WS

Location_Description: 200yds below dam (Downtown), off Main St
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed up to 80m below dam (unable to move barge around boulders)

Location_Description: off River Rd, below powerlines
Habitat_Comment: Sample area south of powerlines. Shocked 25 min (no seconds recorded)

Location_Description: off Ponakin Mill Rd, just E of Schumacher Rd
Habitat_Comment: Area sampled very rocky w/ fine sediment. Crayfish present. Deep pools-unable to finish last stretch. Missed large LND.

Location_Description: Rt 190 crossing downstream
Habitat_Comment: Salmon Index Survey

Location_Description: behind Searstown Mall - South of Rt 2 crossing
Habitat_Comment: Area sampled rocky w/ sand & sediment bottom. Straight channel area. Crayfish present.

Location_Description: N of Bemis Rd over NH border. US of confluence w/ Nissitissit R
off Brookline St (DS), Columbo (Niss) WMA
Habitat_Comment: 300' downstream to data logger. Very many fallfish not collected.

Location_Description: Below Pine Brook Reservoir, abandoned cranberry bogs off Grove St
Habitat_Comment: Section below reservoir dam. Abandoned cranberry bogs. Well vegetated section. Large snapping turtle & water snake sighted

Location_Description: Below Hathaway Pond, along Rt 105 (Rochester Rd)
Habitat_Comment: Large pool below dam w/ island & heavy silt. Few fish & deep in this section. Most fish captured in sand & cobble bottomed bypass channel.

Location_Description: upstream from bridge crossing below Leonards Pond, US of Bates Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Fast flowing, rock & cobble bottom. Below pond confined within granite block walls.

Location_Description: 1/4 mile below covered bridge on River Rd
Habitat_Comment: lost 2 (1+) AS. Good habitat, some leaves down. Cool morning. 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: DS of Greenfield swimming hole, along I-91
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Access to site via bike trail (off Nash's Mill Rd) that runs along the river

Location_Description: DS of cemetary, between Rt 9 & W. Cummington Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: off Old State Highway, 0.1mi E of Mica Mill Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: DS of bridge on WMA (off of Rt 112)
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used.

Location_Description: Above Wiley-Russell Dam, off Mead St, Site #1, West Bank
Habitat_Comment: West bank of impoundment. One of 2 surveys done in this section of river, other survey (SID 3007) done on East bank. BND from flowing water at head of pond.

Location_Description: Above Tap & Die Dam (Wiley-Russell), Site #1, East Bank
Habitat_Comment: Entire East bank of impoundment. One of 2 surveys done in this section of river. Other survey (SID 3004) done on West bank. Fathead minnows found! CRCs may have been Fathead minnows.

Location_Description: Winsor Dam
Habitat_Comment: Calm, very warm. Wind picked up ~10pm, we quit. Caught some LLS, couple of nice SMB, 2 bullheads. Started @ 6pm, ended around 10pm. Did 4 sets of 2 nets = 8 total net sets. Nets were set for 30-45min. 2 morts, 3 recaps, 1 floy tag (5350). Caught large LT- 859mm, bottomed out the scale. All weights include weight of bucket (1000g)

Location_Description: Winsor Dam
Habitat_Comment: Surface temp 13. All weights include bucket weight (1000g)

Location_Description: Winsor Dam
Habitat_Comment: 2 nets set @ a time. Started w/ 2 100-150' nets nearby to each other. Changed out the snorter net (100') for a 200' net after its 2nd set. A total of 13 net sets. Some sets were sparse w/ LT (2-3 caught) while others were plentiful (10+). Seemed like it was getting toward the end of spawning. Started ~6pm, ended @ 10pm. Little to no wind, cool (40's). Set nets on last 1/3 of dam (opposite end of intake), up to end of dam. Some lg LLS caught.

Location_Description: Lagoon #1, Between outlet bridge & 2nd to last bridge @ Esplanade
Habitat_Comment: Survey targeting Nile Tilapia, requested by Harvard MCZ. Rip-rap shore up to knee deep. Pulled seine along edge of rip-rap. No Nile Tilapia. DCR contact (located at Hatch Shell on Esplanade) Angelo Tillis or Mike 617-227-0627

Location_Description: US of 2nd bridge upstream from outlet, @ Esplanade
Habitat_Comment: Lagoon in Esplanade. Pulled seine down middle of channel. Too much riprap on side, made footing difficult. Not able to confirm Nile Tilapia sightings/capture by Harvard student (Willy Goldsmith). Possibly continue discussion on boat shocking for next year. Caught a tire though.

Location_Description: Launched @ boat ramp
Habitat_Comment: Shockboat test run. Lots of YOY sunfish (B & P), TNTC (too numerous to count). Did not measure them. Nice lg LMB. 3 Runs: Run 1 (SID 3014) total pickup. Run 2 & 3 (SID 3015) selective pickup.

Location_Description: Launched @ boat ramp
Habitat_Comment: These are the 2 selective pickups from SID 3014. Looking for trout, bass, & pickerel. Run 2: 458 sec, Run 3: 1976. Ended run 2 early due to generator problems.

Location_Description: Launched @ access point off Lyman Rd
Habitat_Comment: Sunny day. Water very murky with heavy weeds present, both lily pads & submerged. Used gillnets (SID 3021) & rod & reel (SID 3022). 10 fish total caught. 7 came from shaded west of pond. 7+ hours of nets w/ 2 fish caught. 2 runs performed

Location_Description: Launched @ access point off Lyman Rd
Habitat_Comment: Same as SID 3021. fished for 9 man hours w/ 8 fish caught.

Location_Description: State Park access
Habitat_Comment: Requested rod & reel (SID 3023) & gillnet (SID 3024). Fish activity is to the southern end of the fishery with greater fish densities within the small coves. Chain pickerel active on surface bait. Some YP's, one small largemouth various other panfish caught & observed. Water is very turbid & densly vegitative, around the edges. Fished for 3 hr 45 min.

Location_Description: State park access
Habitat_Comment: Comments same as for SID 3023.

Location_Description: Stafford Rd crossing -downstream
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks w/ rattails. Rocky w/ ledge outcrops. Warmwater species only. Passed on late fish due to full crate. Only kept addes species. (double to triple #s passed on common species.

Location_Description: Rt 56 crossing upstream. @ Leicester St/Comins Rd intersection

Location_Description: Clara Barton Rd crossing (downstream)

Location_Description: Hammond Hill Rd crossing (downstream)

Location_Description: Lancaster Rd crossing, upstream

Location_Description: Rt 56 crossing (downstream) E, US of Comins Rd xing

Location_Description: Clara Barton Rd crossing (upstream) N

All warmwater species. Variety of habitats: riffles, pools, runs. Moss-covered rocks. Water flow moderate. Dark water made visibility difficult. Side pools present. Appears to flood at times over banks. 1 B had worms under gillplate. Stream runs next to RR tracks ~15m.

Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Shallow stretch sampled. Warmwater species only. Nice section of stream w/ excellent canopy.

Location_Description: Launched from ramp on Torrey Rd
Habitat_Comment: Selective pickup for SMB, LMB only. Shocked shoreline w/ 3 runs. Shallow & very rocky! Some weed cover present in coves but sparse. Low conductivity made for poor shocking, fish swimming out of field. GS & CP found in northern cove. Larger LMB caught in & near that cove. Amps between 4-8. No schools of sm juv bass seen or shocked. Scales taken from indiv >305mm (12") (6fish)

Location_Description: OFBA ramp @ Rt 111/119 xing
Habitat_Comment: Selective pickup for all LMB. Large #s of YOY & 1+ LMB not sampled. 3 runs conducted. Very heavy vegetation. Shocked US of Rt 111/119xing up through the Ox Bow. Cows in river off meadow grazing area.

Location_Description: White Pond Rd, Assabet R NWR

Observed: YP, NP, B, P, BB. Young bass, young AE. Muddy, weedy, difficult shocking. Carp also. GS not measured. Refer to attached email correspondence.

Location_Description: Launched off ramp on Mill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Selective pickup for LMB & GS. Survey to collect LMB & GS for biological analysis for USFWS, US EPA. Coordinated w/ Katrina Kipp. Seconds not recorded. GS were not measured. Other species observed: B, P, bullhead, BC(lots of them, different age classes), YP, CP. Lots of turtles incl. a very large snapper. HOT!

Location_Description: DS of 1st dam, US of Shattuck Rd xing

Location_Description: DS of Middle dam

Some cat tails along stream banks, but stream bottom is solid (not swampy). Some spots w/ algal mat. Rust colored sediment in upper reach of sample. Stopped a base pool DS from dam. Some milfoil in stream.

Location_Description: High St xing US, just E of Hunt Rd
Windsor Dam, launched @ Admin Bldg
Habitat_Comment: First night of 2010 LT tagging. Only caught 7 LT in 2 hrs & 6 sets of netting. Caught just as many LLS, few SMB, RB, 1 BB. Weather calm, cool. Temp not taken but water not too cold (~mid-high 50's). 3 recaps. Maybe the beginning of spawn, fish seemed not quite ready.

Location_Description: Windsor Dam, launched @ Admin Bldg
Habitat_Comment: Lake Trout Tagging night #2. Weights include bucket (900g). Netted from 6:30-10:45pm. Caught fair amount of LLS. Had 9 LT morts due to strangulation in nets. Most seemed ready to spawn though #s of those caught were not very high. Slight breeze, light rain got heavier as we ended. 30 Tagged fish, 5 recaps, 9 morts.

Location_Description: Windsor Dam, launched @ Admin Bldg
Habitat_Comment: LT tagging night #4. Started by setting 2 nets, had same trouble w/ 2nd net as night before (net stuck in rocks @ deep end). Had to cut net to free it (removed net, it was not left behind). Used 1 net after that. Lots of nice LT & LLS. Caught HUGE LT=834mm, bottomed out scale, no girth taken. Otter swam by boat. Cold, mid-high 30's, little to no wind. 67 total LT caught: 58 tagged fish, 1 mort, 8 recaps. Weights incl bucket (900g)

Location_Description: Coalkiln Rd crossing US, 0.6mi S of Whitaker Ln

Sampled US of driveway xing to Mossman Rd. Decent mix of riffles/runs & pools. Could probably support coldwater spp. But suspect connectivity issues may be preventing it. Significant persistent & ongoing stream bank erosion evident on both banks.

Windsor Dam, NE portion & 1/2 way
Habitat_Comment: First & only night of LT pit tagging for 2011. First set @ 6:20pm, 2nd @ 6:35, 7pm, 7:30, 7:45, 8pm. (1 net per set,) 6 net runs (a total of 6 nets set over the course of the night). Only 6 LT caught & tagged. Average about 2 LLS per net haul. 1 RB & 1 SMB caught as well. PERFECT conditions! Flat water, no wind, mid 40's, just no fish! Ended @ 8:30pm. No LT in net #1 or #6. No recaps

Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Low gradient hardbottom w/ silt on top 2-4".

Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Warmwater species only. Site surveyed between 2 marshes. 6 AE observed up to 2'.

Location_Description: Along Rt 117 (Horton Memorial Trail), just NE of Meadow Rd
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Warmwater species only. Crayfish present. Rocky bottom w/ sediment. Water cloudy, slow-moving

Location_Description: Emerald Rd off Rt 56 (dirt road), 700ft E of Rt 56
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Warmwater species only. Frogs & crayfish present.

Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Sampled between beaver dams up to culvert crossing. Warmwater species only.

Location_Description: Clifford St crossing DS

Location_Description: Chestnut Hill Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. RP only. Channelized whole length. Soft silty bottom

Location_Description: Providence Rd crossing DS, just N of townline
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 1 CS only

Location_Description: Quisset Rd crossing DS
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 2 CS only. Frogs present

Location_Description: Milk St crossing DS, 1/3mi W of Mendon St
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. RP only. Crayfish present

Location_Description: Pine St crossing US, just E of Orange St
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. CS only. Frogs present. Sampled up to pond 30m & above pond 34m. Pond too deep to survey

Location_Description: Northeast corner of pond
Habitat_Comment: Runs 1-3=total pickup, Run 4=selective pickup (SID 3837). Large schools of YP fry. Water murky, limited depth visibility. School of K seen. Carp present evenly throughout shorline. Run 1 & 2 = 600 sec each, Run 3 = no seconds recorded.

Location_Description: SW end Sear's Island/ramp
Habitat_Comment: 4th run of Sample ID 3836. Selective pickup for LMB. SW to start point.

Location_Description: Behind Whitmanville Reservoir
Habitat_Comment: Angling & Gillnetting (SID 3839) done on same day. Small pond located southwest of Whitmanville Res. Is AKA "Stump Pond". Rod & reel for 2.5 hrs.

Location_Description: Behind Whitmanville Reservoir
Habitat_Comment: Survey done in conjunction with angling (SID 3838) on same day. Set 2 gillnets for 2 hours. Poor results in nets, 2 fish total.

Location_Description: Access at town ramp
Habitat_Comment: Survey at request of local cable access of Westboro (demonstration of boat electrofishing)

Location_Description: US of River Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Very high gradient! Started just above culvert. Relatively flat then gradient gets very steep. Bedrock/ledge cascades w/ little to no pools. All fish found in bottom flat section. Lots of frogs & salamanders. Runs next to a backyard, mostly shaded. Bottom section pools & riffles, cobbles. Clear water, light flow. Very slick up top. Only could do 210ft b/c of gradient & lack of fish at top. DS of rd clsoe to CT River.

Location_Description: DS of Old North Dana Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Sampled between 2 swamps, influenced by beavers. GS only fish found. Sandy, boulder, cobble substrate w/ sections of mud. Only decent section between the 2 ponds. Shaded deciduous canopy w/ lightly vegetated banks. Some undercutting of banks. Frogs & crayfish present.

Location_Description: Rt 117 crossing DS
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ 2 probes. Survey is DS of Bartlett Pond. Request from Lancaster ConCom. Follow up survey in Summer 2012.

Location_Description: Sun Valley Golf Club below Summer St
between Tide Meadows Dr & Townley Dr
Habitat_Comment: Looks tidal, may be low tide.

Location_Description: North St downstream of xing
off Hobart St, E of Cross St ~700ft
Habitat_Comment: Low water. Some boulders & moss, but mostly sand & fine gravel. 1-6' wide. Max depth about 6'. Shurbs overhang stream.

Location_Description: Above Fresh River Ave xing
Habitat_Comment: from road up to railroad culvert w/ burreed. Gravel & cobble bottom, stained water. Low overhangning shrubs. Old trash & tires & shoe.

Location_Description: upstream of Rt 8 & 20, 1/3mi W of Farmstread Rd
Habitat_Comment: Tanic stream upstream of the Rt 8 & 20 bridge. Substrate dominated by cobble & gravel. Large population of crayfish.

Location_Description: Upstream f Rt 20 xing, 2/3mi E of Rt 8
Habitat_Comment: Very wetland stream. Attempted to survey at Bonny Rigg rd but no stream channel was aparent. Very low gradient stream w/ a soft sand & mud stream bottom. Sulfur bubbling up from stream. Boulders are present in stream but only occasional. Not much shade in stream. Old dam remnant by Rt 8.

Location_Description: Behind farm house off of Higgins Rd
Habitat_Comment: Nasty looking water in stream. Stream appears to have a grey murkey hue in the sunlight. Very low productivity. Substrate is very black w/ lots of silt, composed of cobble, boulder, sand, much & silt. Canopy cover composed of hemlock, maple, birch

Location_Description: Downstream of Willcut Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Stream flows through several small wetlands. One nice ledge pool toward the top of site. Water is slightly tannic. Silt gets suspended easily in the water column. Substrate is composed of sand, silt, muck, gravel, cobble & some boulders & ledge. Stream is between low & high gradient. Canopy cover is hemlock, birch & maple.

Location_Description: DS of Windsor Pond at end of Windsor Pond Rd (private road)
Habitat_Comment: Approx 200-300m downtstream of outflow of Windsor Pond. Stream is a cross between high & low gradient. Substrate composed of sand, cobble, gravel & some large boulders. Some nice large wood habitat scattered throughout stream. Lots of scour w/in stream bank, may be result of pond draw down.

Location_Description: Downstream of Sturtevant Rd
Habitat_Comment: Dark dark substrate. Could only survey between wetland & pond. Lots of silt in stream. Tannic water. Substrate composed of cobble, sand, silt, some boulder & lots of sticks. Canopy composed of baslam fir, yellow birch, ash, hemlock.

Location_Description: Downstrem of ATV road, 1/4mi S of Kirby Rd/Shepard Rd
Habitat_Comment: Nasty stream with orange water! Very silty. Narrow, low gradient stream w/ washed out ATV bridge. Substrate composed of muck, silt, boulder, sand. Canopy cover composed of red maple & birch.

Location_Description: Downstream of Windy Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: Stream has anumber of legacy impacts. A number of remnants of several odl dams. Stream channel is still unstable following these historic impacts. Stream is very silty. Substrate has cobble, gravel, sand, boulder & ledge. Lots of silt & detritus. Canopy dominated by hemlock, white birch & some cherry.

Location_Description: End of Tidmarsh Farm Bogs (in Manomet)
Habitat_Comment: Triple pass of cranberry bog area. # runs at 974s, 833s, 829s. For Master's thesis study, reference area for Eel River restoration

Location_Description: Downstream from Rt 44, 1/4mi W of Mill St
Habitat_Comment: Sampling in conjunction w/ permitting @ request of Kurt Young. Next to nice holly grove on upland. Muck bottom 2-3' deep. Lots of woody branches & overhangning brush.

Location_Description: DS of Vernon St/Richmond St xing
Habitat_Comment: Crayfish captured @ stream xing (Vernon St). Sample started DS of Vernon St, skipped section w/ large pool. Sampled thru both sides of culvert. Flat rocks in culvert. Adult salamander-red back, no lines on back. Evidence of sand on banks, below road due to high flows.

Location_Description: DS of Rt 44xing, W of Mill St
Habitat_Comment: Below Rt 44 crossing. Too deep to sample in culvert & above 44. numerous downed trees. Sand & muck bottom

Location_Description: Above Long Pond Rd, Bog #5 lower end
Habitat_Comment: Restored area within fenced area, surrounded by low marshland. Difficult to sample. Sand over silt or muck, had to stick to side for most of sample. Some large trees.

Location_Description: Old Ocean St DS side, just S of Mt. Skirgo St
Launched at boat ramp Rt 183
Habitat_Comment: Killifish observed at boat ramp. Redds observed along Western shore. No redds observed on easter shore. No fish were observed on spawning redds. Sunny w/ few clouds. Alsko known as Lake Mahkeenac. 1st 2 passes around island, 3rd pass just rigth of boat ramp.

Location_Description: Launched off public boat ramp
Habitat_Comment: Fish survey along the northern basin. Tons of fish! Very little aquatic vegetation observed, only cattails & floating lily pads in small quantity. Lots of fish in vegetation.

Location_Description: Launched boat off public boat ramp on Rt 20
Habitat_Comment: Nice evening w/ light winds, clear. Low ambient air temp ~75F

Location_Description: Launched boat off public boat ramp on Rt 20
Habitat_Comment: Nice evening w/ light winds, clear. Low ambient air temp ~75F. Interesting fly hatches from surface of water that were attracted to lights. 2 gillnet sets, nets ~75ft longs. Net 1: 6:06pm-8:50pm. Net 2: 6:28-10pm.

Location_Description: Outlet of Hatchet Pond, @ trail xing off Crawford Rd on CT state line. See attached map.
Habitat_Comment: First site of 4 done in area (2 on this UNT (SID 3967, 3968) & 2 on Hatchet Br (SID 3970)). See attached map. Normally dry, been flowing since spring. Site was originally mistaken as Hatchet Br.

Location_Description: DS of Lake Mattawa Rd, straight out of L. Mattawa
Habitat_Comment: No Cover Sheet included with LF sheet (also front page of Hab. Assessment form is missing).

Location_Description: Between Reservoirs #3 & #4 in Southbridge Reservoir system
Habitat_Comment: 3rd of of 4 done in area. No seconds or survey length recorded. Also checked between Reservoirs #4 & #5: dry.

Location_Description: Reach 5A (see map), from Pomeroy Ave DS to townline

Location_Description: Reach 5C (see map), from below New Lenox Rd to Woods Pond

Location_Description: Reach 5C (see map), from below New Lenox Rd to Woods Pond
Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by ARCADIS. Selective pickup for adult largemouth bass, 1 caught.

Habitat_Comment: Survey conducted by ARCADIS. Selective pickup for adult largemouth bass, 15 caught.

LMB annual survey. Numerous schools of bass fry. Alewives noted. Sunfish on beds. Selective pick-up on all runs. Lengths & girths taken on LMB.
Run #1-1904s, Run #2-1965s, Run #3-3064s, Run #4-4027s.

Location_Description: Between Holyoke Dam & Rt 116 bridge, Transect: Middle Channel #2

Location_Description: Between Holyoke Dam & Rt 116 bridge. Transect: Middle Channel #3 upper
Habitat_Comment: Kleinschmidt Consultants performed survey on 9 transects between Holyoke Dam & Rt 116 bridge. 2 larger SMBs found in 3ft+ holes. 50% capture rate AE, 70% capture rate SMG, Abbrev. HNS on LF sheets = Spottail shiner?

Location_Description: Between Holyoke Dam & Rt 116 bridge, along Holyoke shoreline/turbine outlet canal. Transect: Holyoke Channel 1.

Location_Description: Along turbine outlet canal, between Holyoke Dam & Rt 116 bridge. Transect: Holyoke Channel 2.
Habitat_Comment: Kleinschmidt Consultants performed survey on 9 transects between Holyoke Dam & Rt 116 bridge. 50% capture rate AE, 40% capture rate TD, 70% capture rate SMB. Pool 15%, riffle 60%, pocket eddies 25%

Location_Description: Between Holyoke Dam & Rt 116 bridge along S. Hadley shoreline. Transect: S. Hadley Channel 1.
Habitat_Comment: Kleinschmidt Consultants performed survey on 9 transects between Holyoke Dam & Rt 116 bridge. E-boat first section. (Second section used backpack wand from boat. Effort was not seperated from boat effort:. 25% capture rate AE (30%), 60% capture rate TD, LND, WS (15%), 30% capture rate SMB (25%).

Location_Description: Between Holyoke Dam & Rt 116 bridge. Transect: South Hadley Channel 2
Habitat_Comment: Kleinschmidt Consultants performed survey on 9 transects between Holyoke Dam & Rt 116 bridge.25% capture rate AE, 10% capture rate SMB, 10% capture rate LND. Difficult to sample, fast current, deep holes. Thunderstorm came through.

Location_Description: Between Holyoke Dam & Rt 116 bridge. Transect: South Hadley chanel 3
Habitat_Comment: Kleinschmidt Consultants performed survey on 9 transects between Holyoke Dam & Rt 116 bridge. Difficult to sample, deep pools decreased effic of backpack shocker. <5% capture rate TD, LND, 20% AE, 20% SMB. Water depth, velocity, large substrate made sampling difficult.

Location_Description: US of Mill Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Survey done as demonstration for Dr Van Roo's ENV SCI class. Started above pool US of culvert. Good flow, water cool. Visibility good, though dark substrate. Rocky. Boulder, cobble, gravel & sand, some fine sediment. Some woody debris present in pool edges. Diversity of habitats available (pool, run, riffle). Lots of crayfish & mayflies

Location_Description: US of Maynard St xing

Surveyd from road crossing to small riffle. Lots of mayflies (larvae & adults present). Channelized throughout reach (above & below xing), riprap banks. Considerable alteration to streambank vegetation.

Location_Description: Launched from Lakeshore Drive
Habitat_Comment: Surveyed pond & 2 reaches of Charles R (inlet & outlet) @ request of OFBA for proposed fishing platforms along river in Medway. First run-total pickup, 2nd run-(SID 3997) selective pickup for bass (LMB), 2 lg carp caught too.

Location_Description: Launched from Lakeshore Dr

Habitat_Comment: Survey @ request of OFBA for proposed fish platforms in Medway. Total pickup. Motored US from Populatic Pond as far as possible & surveyed from that point down to confl. w/ the pond. Launched at the pond.
