Habitat_Comment: Loose mud, fairly shallow. Survey done at request of Town of Sudbury & Sudbury Valley Trustees.

Location_Description: Off Tall Pines Dr, US of Horse Pond Rd
Habitat_Comment: Silt, mud bottom, lots of aquatic vegetation.

Location_Description: Rt 228 xing upstream, just S of Rosemary Ln, South Junior HS
Habitat_Comment: Prospect St 42.19123, 70.86514 is dry. Rt 228: narrow, rocky bottom, shallow.

Location_Description: Adams St xing downstream, ~600ft W of Morrison Rd
Habitat_Comment: Shallow, large rocks, water stained. Misseld a lot of eels. Other spots too deep or fenced off.

Location_Description: Needham St downstream, E of intersection w/ Pond St & North St
Habitat_Comment: Nice brook, very clear.

Location_Description: End of Ernest Dr, upstream, off Riverbend Dr
Rt 30 (Pleasant St) crossing at townline
Winter St upstream, between Spruce Rd & Lasalle Rd
Habitat_Comment: Very dark, tannic stained water

Location_Description: Off end of Daly Dr, just W of Sullivan Rd
Habitat_Comment: Large nubmers of pickerel swimming out of range of probe. Few snags or obstructions.

Location_Description: Along Old Rt 9, ~0.4mi S of Rt 9
Habitat_Comment: Open channel. Evident Irene flood. Some good shade from trees at E bank edge. Algae in the shallows. Some good LWD. Lots of instream sedimentation.

Location_Description: Off Rt 20 @ pulloff (fry stocking staging point) across from doctors offices @ townline
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Terrible efficiency w/ 2 backpakcs. Lost a lot. Some of the CS were probably spottail shiners, no formalin (not vouchered). May have to resample in fall. Not a salmon index site.

Location_Description: Off of Swift R Rd
Habitat_Comment: Lg boulder, cobble. Long riffles, few step pools. Dark, shaded by hemlock. Some LWD

Location_Description: River Rd @ powerlines
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks usedl. Usual start section ( 150ft) completely a pool. Moved to riffle US. Good pockets & edgewater. Missed 500 (20mm) BND.

Location_Description: East River Rd US of Clarkwright Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Riffle habitat above bedrock pools. Wide, shallow, 1/2' depth. Pocket water. Pulledo ut 8 AS on back pass.

Location_Description: Along Rt 112 N, 3/4mi N of Franklin Hill Rd
Habitat_Comment: 2 backpacks used. Wide, shallow. Missed a lot of fish. Overcast, light rain.

Location_Description: US of Crowley Rd xing
Habitat_Comment: Raining. Lots of deep pools & lg wood. Upstream of where we usually sample.

Location_Description: Upstream of old bridge/stone dam, off rt 140, 600ft S of N. Oakdale Cutoff
Access Rd (Bridle Rd) via reservoir property
Habitat_Comment: No water from reservoir up almost a mile cross powerlines. Entire stream in roadside canal until crossing. Beaver dam upstream of end of reach. Very small & shallow. Bedrock & silt, small pool above xing.

Location_Description: Below & above Rt 70 crossing, 1/2 mi NE of Cross St
Habitat_Comment: 50m above & below Rt 70 crossing. The stream is armored & channelized. All fish came from above the channelized upstream section

Location_Description: Off Mechanic St, 0.2mi N of Rt 32A
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Sampled pools among rocks & boulders up to dam (breached). Frogs present.

Location_Description: Royalston Rd crossing US
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Surveyd at crossing US. Very silty due to beaver issues at crossing. US became normal brook w/ hard bottom. Only 3 fish, 1 CRC at 125

Location_Description: Laurel Lk Rd crossing, 0.3mi S of NH state line
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Surveyed pools only thing water between pools

Location_Description: Rt 202 crossing US, near townline
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Rocky w/ multiple pools. Crayfish present. Good canopy.

Location_Description: Sawyer St crossing DS
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Sampled pool only. Frogs & crayfish present. Good canopy.

Location_Description: Upstream of Rt 140
Habitat_Comment: Heavy deposit of brown/orange (iron) sediment. Easily suspended when disturbed

Location_Description: W Shore Dr crossing US
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. 1 fish - GS. Frogs & crayfish present

Location_Description: E. Rindge Rd crossing DS, ~0.1mi N of Tuckerman Rd
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. Very tannic water. Good canopy. Crayfish & frogs present.

Location_Description: Central St crossing US
Habitat_Comment: Backpack w/ rattail. All rock w/ drop down pools. Good canopy. WW species only. Crayfish present.

Location_Description: Green Rd crossing, 400ft W of Sampson Rd
Habitat_Comment: Large settling pond US from crossing with zero fish passage due to raised culvert. Very little flow. Heavy vegetation. Broken rocky ledge with very limited pools.

Location_Description: South Royalston St
Habitat_Comment: Fishing time 10:30-12:45pm by canoe. Day started bright & sunny by 12:30pm thunderstorm rolled in. fishign productivity increased last 2 hours. Clear, deep water, little weeds. Fish spread out throughout edges around pond. Fished around perimeter. 1.5 times little success 1st lap from southeast corner. 2nd lap-better fishing.

Location_Description: Middle Basin
Habitat_Comment: Annual survey, selective pickup for bass. Low water (~2'). Heavy vegetation/algae. Schools of fry & 1" LMB. Very windy. Missed part of eastern shoreline due to impending storms. South basin surveyed at same time by CT Valley district.

Location_Description: South pond
Habitat_Comment: Sampling efficiency good. Windy & some canoeists/skiers. Water green & algae seemed above average. Selective pickup for bass. Saw one alewife, lots of bullhead. Total shoreline shocking.

Location_Description: Access behind cemetary off West St
Habitat_Comment: Survey in search of ninespine stickleback found in 2007 @ a downstream site. One NSS found & pickled! Very low gradient. Stream has cut banks, meandering, shallow runs w/ minor riffles over small woody debris. Substrate sand & mud w/ silt. Shaded flood plain w/ vegetation & small woody debris brush lining stream banks. Detritus in some spots-likely habitat for NSS. Did not realized we caught NSS until we finished the survey. No deep pools.Survey was difficult due to vegetation overgrowth.

Location_Description: DS of West St xing
Habitat_Comment: Survey in search of NSS. Surveyd DS of West St. Stream runs along resident's backyard, yard manicured to stream's edge. Low flow, sand, mud substrate w/ detritus & silt. Lots of NSS! Mostly shallow runs w/ deeper bend pools that cut under banks. Mostly shaded except for lower section. Vegetated banks w/ shrubs as well. Rocky substrate at culvert pipe. Stopped before that. pH very high! Low DO (0.83ppm)!

Location_Description: Kellog St xing downstream
Habitat_Comment: Survey in search of NSS. 12 NSS found! Survey done in sections due to overgrowth of brush & thorns. Very muddy, deep mud. Low flow. Survey length is estimated. Lots more mud at culvert/bridge end this year, very deep mud. Difficult to survey. Shallow habitat, low flow, very few deep pools.

Location_Description: US of Pleasant St xing
Habitat_Comment: In search of NSS. Shocked US of road xing, just to see if there's any NSS. Only 3 BND shocked, not measured so no LF sheet. No NSS seen. Only shocked ~5m upstream. Very swampy & overgrown, meandering & braided. Difficult to access & shock.

Location_Description: Private/utility road xing off Rt 202
Habitat_Comment: In search of NSS. Shocked DS side of xing. Very deep pools either side, swamp on both sides of road. Shocked edge of pool to determine NSS presence- presence confirmed. A full survey would be next to impossible, due to depth & habitat. No LF sheet.

Location_Description: Upstream Plymouth St
Habitat_Comment: Too muddy to get full 100m

Location_Description: Head of Town Cove, off of Sweet William Way
Habitat_Comment: numerous seeps. Wide stream. Burreed patches. Sand/silt, some cobble. Note: AE not properly measured, therefore entered as blanks in database. Also AE efficiency was poor (less than half of AE were caught).

Location_Description: Launched from boat ramp on Rt 20. Seines set in different areas on lake
Habitat_Comment: Seine #1: 42.32256, 73.26254, across from boat ramp. Seine #2: 42.321005, 73.260363, SE corner of eastern cove. Seine #2: 42.327396, 73.273394, most western point. 1st seine was tough w/ woody debris in way, only 1 fish caught. 2nd seine better, weedy cove & muddy. 3rd seine had some issues w/ hauling it.

Location_Description: Launched from ramp, 3 areas on lake gillnets were set
Habitat_Comment: Set 1, set at 3:55pm, 42.837406, 73.27294721, 150' 1.5" mesh. Pulled at 7:30pm. Set 2, set at 4:07pm, 42.3242689, 73.265282, pulled at 7:55pm, 125' experimental mesh, no fish. Set 3, set at 4:30pm, 42.3232027, 73.2717865, pulled at 8:07pm, 125' graduated experimental mesh, no fish. Extensino lines used on marker buoys could have caused nets to lie flat resulting in no fish

Location_Description: Launched from Rt 20 ramp
Habitat_Comment: Hot, humid 90's. full sunlight. 1st run not very effective. Secchi-276". We caught more fish as it got later in evening. Red squirrel swamp by boat.

Location_Description: Trailer lot, 350m downstream of Park Rd, located between on-ramp on I-90 & South Ave
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Brook follows major interstate interchange. Evidence of large amounts of stormwater impacting brook. Large storm pipe

Location_Description: Upstream of Chestnut St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Little to no flow, stagnant water. Silt/muck in water. Collection efficiencies poor. AE observed (3-4 large, ~8 small others).

Location_Description: Downstream of Howley St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Efficiency very low, wide shallow, rocky (pebbles). Hundreds of mummichogs not collected/sampled

Location_Description: Upstream from Central St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. 21 eels noted/seen. Efficiency good. Est reach length 80m. Many fish observed but not collected/counted (for killifish). Essentially a straight channel with hard granite block bottom & boulder side walls

Location_Description: Near Marshalls, at mall entrance south of Lynn Falls Parkway & east of Forest St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Good collection efficiency. Habitat was average, mostly aquatic plants. Very developed area, roadway or lots, both sides of stream along entire length. Storm drains empties into most of reach.

Location_Description: Just below Glen Ave upstream to dilapitated dam just below Williams St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Black spot trematode on almost all CS. Black spot on small number of GS.

Location_Description: Upstream from Totman Dr
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: ~80m DS of Olympia Ave
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: Upstream of Washington St to low head dam
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: @ USGS gaging station US of low head dam, W of Mystic Valley Parkway across from Mystic Ave
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: Upstreams of Mystic Parkway at Mt Pleasant Cemetary.
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Large # of AE (100+) of approx size 100-350mm. Very sandy meandering low gradient stream. High conductivity. Fish habitat primarily snags, some aquatic macrophytes and undercuts

Location_Description: Upstream from Lake Ave & Wedge Pond, along Horn Pond Brook Rd
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Essentially a straight channelized run. Very hig flows on day of sampling. High velocity, homogenious.

Location_Description: Just US of Mill Brook Rd, crossing nearest Nebo St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. YOY EBT observed but not captured. Upstream of sampled reach, we collected 4 EBT (180-200mm), Banded sunfish (2), RP, CP.

Location_Description: Downstream from Draper St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Basically sandy. Water supply wellheads along stream left side. Low flow on day of sampling.

Location_Description: Downstream of Everett St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Lower part of reach was low gradient. Very sandy w/ some silt on stream margin. Habitat in the form of overhanging vegetation. Upper half of reach reduces gradient w/ good fish habitat, undercut banks, boulders & such.

Location_Description: Upstream of Maskwonicut St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Lower half of reach was low gradient. Heavily sedimented bottom. Upper half moderate gradient, riffle/run habitat. Abundant sunfish seen but not captured. No other fish species observed. Snapping turtle, crayfish.

Location_Description: Off Tamarack Rd, US of Maple Ln
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Looks to be a straight channel. May have been channelized historically. Very homogenious.

Location_Description: Trailside Dr (downstream side)
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Although area is residential, there is a very good buffer between river & houses. Low flows, 80% efficiency

Location_Description: Upstream & downstream of Elm St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Low gradient stream. Lower reach, right side in yard w/ stone wall. Upper part of reach is pasture on right. Decent buffere on left side between pasture & stream.

Location_Description: Upstream of Martin St ~100yds
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Dark, low gradient stream. Lots of moss. Decent fish habitat. Boulders, blowdowns. !50% pickup, tough to see. Lots of moss, dark water.

Location_Description: DS of Danforth St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Excellent habitat. Nice undercuts, overhanging branches, decent pools. EBT seen but not captured, possible BT as well. Very hard to collect darters. Many eels seen but not collected, many darters as well

Location_Description: At end of Joyce Circle
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Houses all along right side w/ steep bank & minimal riparian protection. Dark orange/brown color. Trash. Otherwise decent habitat. Color made visibility a potential problem. However we caught most of what we saw. Est pickup >80%

Location_Description: US of Rt 228, above foot bridge,
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Seems to be an old channelized stream through farmland. Straight, fast run. Very dark orange water. Many of eels observed but not captured. 1 additional sunfish observed but not captured. Mostly fast run habitat, not much stable structure. Pickup ~60% on eels.

Location_Description: @ Ralph Talbot St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: ~200m DS of Buck Island Rd, @ end of Pondview Ave
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Narrow stream w 2'. High banks through scrub oak, lowland forest. Meandering, sand dominated. Forested wetland around all of reach. Very good efficiency, just not many fish at all. No obvious reasons for reduced numbers.

Location_Description: Just US from flow structure at Sandwich Rd crossing. Past little park area (private home w/ bridges & water pools)
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Low efficiency due to depth & lots of plants submerged in area. Darters were easiest & eels but lot of cover for fish. Qualitative data only. Sampled ~70m before too choked to do any more.

Location_Description: End of Shirley Dr cul de sac.
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Slow moving, murky, lowland stream. Great eel habitat. Just above head of tide. Efficiency of fish sampling low, instream visibility low.

Location_Description: Upstream of Rt 6A xing
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. This narrow stream is an old channelized stream from a cranberry bog. Side of stream are ~3ft vertically almost as if stream was cut into the groung. Lower 80m of reach are in forested wetlands & upper 20m were in a long abandoned bog area past a culvert. Waters were high in tannins & quite shallow for the entire length.

Location_Description: Just US of Main St
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Good efficiency. All species seen were collected. Many eels seen but not collected (~50-75). Fairly wide, quick-flowing stream. Average 1ft depth, sandy bottom. Plenty of overhanging shrubs. Herring run.

Location_Description: ~50ft DS of Farm St, DEP station MA109A-134
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: ~300m US of Winthrop St, DEP station MA09A-164
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: ~1/2km DS of Sudbury Res, DEP station MA09A-186
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Appears that flow depends on outflor from reservoir. very little flow on date of sampling. Very rocky stable substrate.

Location_Description: just US of Wheeler Rd, DEP station MA09A-152
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Riffle run section to start, fair efficiency. Huge pool in middle, poor to very poor efficiency. Moderate run to end, fair eff. May be affected by downstream dam. Good fish habitat however few stream fish observed. Lg pool in middle of reach looks to have been enhanced historically

Location_Description: just US of Crawford St. DEP station MA09A-105
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Old mill upstream of sampling reach. Impoundment still there. Split channel, historic channel dry. Leakage from impoundment fills auxillary channel.

Location_Description: ~100m US of I-290. DEP station MA09A- 185
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. This is a totally removed reach between 290 on-ramp & 290 overpass. Armored prevents erosion & sedimentation, only 1 deep pool really near 290 on ramp w/ placed rocks

Location_Description: ~550ft US of Robinwood Rd, DEP station MA09A-172
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Large plunge pool just DS of raod. Sample reach braided. Low flow thru residential subdivision.

Location_Description: ~500ft DS of Ledge Rd, DEP station MA109A-118
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: E of Hansom Dr, 1/2km DS of Harriman Rd. DEP station MA09A-128
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Efficiency good. Very heavy silt both center stream & banks. Other AE observed but not captured. Most fish in deeper pools. 2 habitat assessment forms filled out, a high & low gradient. Low gradient entered in database.

Location_Description: 1/4mi US of Main St, just DS of road to gravel pit. DEP station MA09A-158
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Looks like spring floods have affected this reach & apparently subsequent flooding could be problematic. Numerous eels observed but not collected. Efficiency fair due to deep poosl & obstructions such as blowdowns. Stream overwidened in proportion to depth. Seconds not recorded

Location_Description: 60m DS of Caller St. DEP station MA09A-143
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. 100+ eels observed but not captured, all size classes from elvers to adults. Essentially channelized reach w/ stone walls on both sides. Old RR bed & other commercial in riparian zone. Lots of trash in stream. Upper reach may be tidal/backwater. 100+ eels observed but not collected, all size classes from elvers to adults

Location_Description: ~1200ft Upstream of School St. DEP station MA09A-154
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. straight channel & obvious flashy streambed impact. Lots of trash. Riparian zone minimal on right. Could be scored on low gradient sheet?

Location_Description: ~600ft upstream of School St. DEP station MA09A-154
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Poor sample, will resample (SID 4559). Very dirty, oil filters, car parts, glass, trash, signs.

Location_Description: ~100m US of Summer St. MA09A-107
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: <0.5MI us OF Rt 2A/119. DEP station MA09A-144
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Great efficiency early, poor late. High water, deep pool at end of reach. Flowe were much higher on Thurs than Tues recon. Interestingly the flow were very high which definitely changed many habitat scoring scores.

Location_Description: ~275m DS of Salem St. DEP station MA09A-159
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Much of reach sandy runs, much of it deep sedimented pools. Residents on right bank impact riparian zone, one shed actually on bank w/ aggregates spilling into brook. Dog waste evident.

Location_Description: ~50m DS of Maple St. DEP station MA09A-148
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Efficiency fair to good. Missed a number of YB, not much else. On right bank, very top of reach has residence. On left, 1/2 of zone narrow, partial commercial/industrial land use.

Location_Description: ~600m DS of Rt 16. Newton lower falls. DEP station MA09A-145
Habitat_Comment: DEP barge survey. Straight reach w/ mostly run habitat upgradient of a dam. Most fish habitat in formof overhanging shrubs.

Location_Description: ~170m DS of Rt 129. DEP station MA09A-115
Habitat_Comment: DEP barge survey. Electrofishing efficiency poor. New equipment, gas ran out right near end. Essentially a straight channel. Middlesex canal just upstream may have been manipulated at that time. Seconds not recorded.

Location_Description: 0.5mi DS of Rt 114. DEP station MA09A-111
Habitat_Comment: DEP barge survey. Evidence of braiding under high flow. Sand deposition evident.

Location_Description: ~15m DS of Mill St. DEP station MA09A-181
Habitat_Comment: DEP barge survey. This stream reach contained a large run & a riffle pool run segment. Many other AE seen but not collected. TD found in a LMB mouth.

Location_Description: ~100m US of Middlesex turnpike. DEP station MA09A-149
Habitat_Comment: DEP barge survey. Straight channel along road. Very little diversity of habitat. Mostly slow moving run, muddy bottom.

Location_Description: 0.5mi DS of Peakham Rd. DEP station MA09A-170
Habitat_Comment: DEP barge survey. Sample reach length & width not recorded.

Location_Description: ~300m US of I-495. DEP station MA09A-174
Habitat_Comment: DEP barge survey. Essentially a straight reach mostly pool or slow run, almost no current. Beaver dam upstream & within reach.

Location_Description: ~230ft US of Norcross Rd. DEP station MAP2-077
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: ~340ft DS of Betty Spring Rd. DEP station MAP2-002
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Very sandy, silty. Much wood debris. Low flow.

Location_Description: ~70ft DS of Cross Rd. DEP station: MAP2-037
Habitat_Comment: DEP backpack survey. Top of reach mostly new type habitat. Lower end mosly pool & plunge pool habitat. Very few fish for habitat available.

Location_Description: Potato Hill Rd. DEP station MAP2-067
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Low end of reach went between road & lawn. Collection was only fair.

Location_Description: Downstream Rt 2A behind liquor store US of WQ station. DEP station MAP2-030
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Road on left riparian zone. Beavers have continue to impact habitat at this location. 2 active beaver dams. Seconds not recorded

Location_Description: ~475ft DS of Mechanic St. DEP station MAP2-007
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Effeciency good. Add'l YOY WS & BND observed. Mostly channelized reach w/ bedrock substrate. Very thin riparian zone on right w/ erosion. Sedimentation above due to high gradient & substrate type.

Location_Description: ~40ft US of Pond St. DEP station MAP2-023
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Beavers active in reach. Reach essentially split between riffle in lower & middle, & pool run in upper.

Location_Description: ~830ft DS of W. Lancaster County Rd. DEP station MAP2-055
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey

Location_Description: ~425ft US of Stafford St. DEP station MAP2-066
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.

Location_Description: ~1/2mi DS of Main St. DEP station MAP2-012
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Very old beaver flowage. Hard to sample due to deep wide channel

Location_Description: 1200ft DS of Fremont St. DEP station MAP2-050
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Barge operation was problematic. Anode #2 was not working consistantly. One WS & TD observed but not collected.

Location_Description: ~600ft US of Rt 20. DEP station MAP2-043
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Flea market antique dealer fields dominate riparian zone

Location_Description: ~900ft US of I-90. DEP station MAP2-059
Habitat_Comment: DEP backpack survey. Nice stream. Good flow, 4 days post-Irene. Many other YOY observed but not captured. Efficiency good.

Location_Description: ~650ft US of I-90. DEP station MAP2-047
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. 2 LMB approx 12" caught, not measured. High flow & dark water made efficiency only fair. May have missed some BND

Location_Description: 1/4mi US of Rt 12. DEP station MAP2-072
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey.Efficiency good. Awesome site. Good flow & variety of habitat. Most of reach low gradient, top of reach moderate.

Location_Description: ~140ft from Granite Reservoir outlet. DEP station MAP2-024
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey

Location_Description: 1/2mi DS of Pond St. DEP station MAP2-068
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Many other WS observed but not collected. Fair capture efficiency due to high flows & colored water

Location_Description: 440ft DS of Roy Ave. DEP station MAP2-004
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Very low gradient. Lots of overhanging brush on stream edges. Snags provided habitat.

Location_Description: 200ft DS from Mill Pond #1. DEP station MAP2-046
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Terrible footing. Efficiency very poor due to depth, footing, boulders & culvert flow. Old mill poperty on both sides of reach

Location_Description: Brigham Hill Rd, DEP station MAP2-026
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Efficiency only fair, wide shallow & dark. Probably missed many darters. Area near dam & road channelized. Very developed reach. Lacking deep pools or other stable habitat

Location_Description: <1/2mi US of Chapin Rd. DEP reference site SC01
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Dark, deep, soft. Efficiency only fair. Essentially deep run w/ a few deep pools. Overhanging vegetation provides habitat margins. Shallow & muddy in some areas.

Location_Description: 1/4mi US of Wrentham Rd. DEP station MAP2-032
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Numerous lamprey & TDs seen but missed. Deep dark water made collection difficult. 1" rain last night, brook way up. Essemblage a run, flooded on day of sample

Location_Description: 50ft US of Whitman Rd. DEP station MAP2-035
Habitat_Comment: DEP survey. Sampling effort was fair. Very lower part of reach narrow on right.

Location_Description: South pond. Launched from South ramp on Middle Basin
Habitat_Comment: Selective pickup for bass. Sampling efficiency good. Windy & some canoeists/skiers. Water green & algae seemed above average. Saw 1 alewife & lots of bullheads
